294 /*
295  * Backport std::make_unique from C++14.
296  *
297  * NOTE: This code came up with the following stackoverflow post:
298  * https://stackoverflow.com/questions/10149840/c-arrays-and-make-unique
299  *
300  */
301 
302 template <class T, class... Args>
303 typename std::enable_if<!std::is_array<T>::value, std::unique_ptr<T>>::type
304 make_unique(Args &&...args) {
305  return std::unique_ptr<T>(new T(std::forward<Args>(args)...));
306 }
307 
308 template <class T>
309 typename std::enable_if<std::is_array<T>::value, std::unique_ptr<T>>::type
310 make_unique(std::size_t n) {
311  typedef typename std::remove_extent<T>::type RT;
312  return std::unique_ptr<T>(new RT[n]);
313 }
314 
315 struct ci {
316  bool operator()(const std::string &s1, const std::string &s2) const {
317  return std::lexicographical_compare(s1.begin(), s1.end(), s2.begin(),
318  s2.end(),
319  [](unsigned char c1, unsigned char c2) {
320  return ::tolower(c1) < ::tolower(c2);
321  });
322  }
323 };
324 
325 // This is based on
326 // "http://www.open-std.org/jtc1/sc22/wg21/docs/papers/2014/n4189".
327 
328 struct scope_exit {
329  explicit scope_exit(std::function<void(void)> &&f)
330  : exit_function(std::move(f)), execute_on_destruction{true} {}
331 
332  scope_exit(scope_exit &&rhs) noexcept
333  : exit_function(std::move(rhs.exit_function)),
334  execute_on_destruction{rhs.execute_on_destruction} {
335  rhs.release();
336  }
337 
338  ~scope_exit() {
339  if (execute_on_destruction) { this->exit_function(); }
340  }
341 
342  void release() { this->execute_on_destruction = false; }
343 
344 private:
345  scope_exit(const scope_exit &) = delete;
346  void operator=(const scope_exit &) = delete;
347  scope_exit &operator=(scope_exit &&) = delete;
348 
349  std::function<void(void)> exit_function;
350  bool execute_on_destruction;
351 };
352

449 class DataSink {
450 public:
451  DataSink() : os(&sb_), sb_(*this) {}
452 
453  DataSink(const DataSink &) = delete;
454  DataSink &operator=(const DataSink &) = delete;
455  DataSink(DataSink &&) = delete;
456  DataSink &operator=(DataSink &&) = delete;
457 
458  std::function<bool(const char *data, size_t data_len)> write;
459  std::function<bool()> is_writable;
460  std::function<void()> done;
461  std::function<void(const Headers &trailer)> done_with_trailer;
462  std::ostream os;
463 
464 private:
465  class data_sink_streambuf : public std::streambuf {
466  public:
467  explicit data_sink_streambuf(DataSink &sink) : sink_(sink) {}
468 
469  protected:
470  std::streamsize xsputn(const char *s, std::streamsize n) override {
471  sink_.write(s, static_cast<size_t>(n));
472  return n;
473  }
474 
475  private:
476  DataSink &sink_;
477  };
478 
479  data_sink_streambuf sb_;
480 };

508 class ContentReader {
509 public:
510  using Reader = std::function<bool(ContentReceiver receiver)>;
511  using MultipartReader = std::function<bool(MultipartContentHeader header,
512  ContentReceiver receiver)>;
513 
514  ContentReader(Reader reader, MultipartReader multipart_reader)
515  : reader_(std::move(reader)),
516  multipart_reader_(std::move(multipart_reader)) {}
517 
518  bool operator()(MultipartContentHeader header,
519  ContentReceiver receiver) const {
520  return multipart_reader_(std::move(header), std::move(receiver));
521  }
522 
523  bool operator()(ContentReceiver receiver) const {
524  return reader_(std::move(receiver));
525  }
526 
527  Reader reader_;
528  MultipartReader multipart_reader_;
529 };

586 struct Response {
587  std::string version;
588  int status = -1;
589  std::string reason;
590  Headers headers;
591  std::string body;
592  std::string location; // Redirect location
593 
594  bool has_header(const std::string &key) const;
595  std::string get_header_value(const std::string &key, size_t id = 0) const;
596  uint64_t get_header_value_u64(const std::string &key, size_t id = 0) const;
597  size_t get_header_value_count(const std::string &key) const;
598  void set_header(const std::string &key, const std::string &val);
599 
600  void set_redirect(const std::string &url, int status = StatusCode::Found_302);
601  void set_content(const char *s, size_t n, const std::string &content_type);
602  void set_content(const std::string &s, const std::string &content_type);
603  void set_content(std::string &&s, const std::string &content_type);
604 
605  void set_content_provider(
606  size_t length, const std::string &content_type, ContentProvider provider,
607  ContentProviderResourceReleaser resource_releaser = nullptr);
608 
609  void set_content_provider(
610  const std::string &content_type, ContentProviderWithoutLength provider,
611  ContentProviderResourceReleaser resource_releaser = nullptr);
612 
613  void set_chunked_content_provider(
614  const std::string &content_type, ContentProviderWithoutLength provider,
615  ContentProviderResourceReleaser resource_releaser = nullptr);
616 
617  Response() = default;
618  Response(const Response &) = default;
619  Response &operator=(const Response &) = default;
620  Response(Response &&) = default;
621  Response &operator=(Response &&) = default;
622  ~Response() {
623  if (content_provider_resource_releaser_) {
624  content_provider_resource_releaser_(content_provider_success_);
625  }
626  }
627 
628  // private members...
629  size_t content_length_ = 0;
630  ContentProvider content_provider_;
631  ContentProviderResourceReleaser content_provider_resource_releaser_;
632  bool is_chunked_content_provider_ = false;
633  bool content_provider_success_ = false;
634 };

655 class TaskQueue {
656 public:
657  TaskQueue() = default;
658  virtual ~TaskQueue() = default;
659 
660  virtual bool enqueue(std::function<void()> fn) = 0;
661  virtual void shutdown() = 0;
662 
663  virtual void on_idle() {}
664 };
665 
666 class ThreadPool : public TaskQueue {
667 public:
668  explicit ThreadPool(size_t n, size_t mqr = 0)
669  : shutdown_(false), max_queued_requests_(mqr) {
670  while (n) {
671  threads_.emplace_back(worker(*this));
672  n--;
673  }
674  }
675 
676  ThreadPool(const ThreadPool &) = delete;
677  ~ThreadPool() override = default;
678 
679  bool enqueue(std::function<void()> fn) override {
680  {
681  std::unique_lock<std::mutex> lock(mutex_);
682  if (max_queued_requests_ > 0 && jobs_.size() >= max_queued_requests_) {
683  return false;
684  }
685  jobs_.push_back(std::move(fn));
686  }
687 
688  cond_.notify_one();
689  return true;
690  }
691 
692  void shutdown() override {
693  // Stop all worker threads...
694  {
695  std::unique_lock<std::mutex> lock(mutex_);
696  shutdown_ = true;
697  }
698 
699  cond_.notify_all();
700 
701  // Join...
702  for (auto &t : threads_) {
703  t.join();
704  }
705  }
706 
707 private:
708  struct worker {
709  explicit worker(ThreadPool &pool) : pool_(pool) {}
710 
711  void operator()() {
712  for (;;) {
713  std::function<void()> fn;
714  {
715  std::unique_lock<std::mutex> lock(pool_.mutex_);
716 
717  pool_.cond_.wait(
718  lock, [&] { return !pool_.jobs_.empty() || pool_.shutdown_; });
719 
720  if (pool_.shutdown_ && pool_.jobs_.empty()) { break; }
721 
722  fn = std::move(pool_.jobs_.front());
723  pool_.jobs_.pop_front();
724  }
725 
726  assert(true == static_cast<bool>(fn));
727  fn();
728  }
729  }
730 
731  ThreadPool &pool_;
732  };
733  friend struct worker;
734 
735  std::vector<std::thread> threads_;
736  std::list<std::function<void()>> jobs_;
737 
738  bool shutdown_;
739  size_t max_queued_requests_ = 0;
740 
741  std::condition_variable cond_;
742  std::mutex mutex_;
743 };
744

783 class PathParamsMatcher : public MatcherBase {
784 public:
785  PathParamsMatcher(const std::string &pattern);
786 
787  bool match(Request &request) const override;
788 
789 private:
790  static constexpr char marker = ':';
791  // Treat segment separators as the end of path parameter capture
792  // Does not need to handle query parameters as they are parsed before path
793  // matching
794  static constexpr char separator = '/';
795 
796  // Contains static path fragments to match against, excluding the '/' after
797  // path params
798  // Fragments are separated by path params
799  std::vector<std::string> static_fragments_;
800  // Stores the names of the path parameters to be used as keys in the
801  // Request::path_params map
802  std::vector<std::string> param_names_;
803 };

1053 class Result {
1054 public:
1055  Result() = default;
1056  Result(std::unique_ptr<Response> &&res, Error err,
1057  Headers &&request_headers = Headers{})
1058  : res_(std::move(res)), err_(err),
1059  request_headers_(std::move(request_headers)) {}
1060  // Response
1061  operator bool() const { return res_ != nullptr; }
1062  bool operator==(std::nullptr_t) const { return res_ == nullptr; }
1063  bool operator!=(std::nullptr_t) const { return res_ != nullptr; }
1064  const Response &value() const { return *res_; }
1065  Response &value() { return *res_; }
1066  const Response &operator*() const { return *res_; }
1067  Response &operator*() { return *res_; }
1068  const Response *operator->() const { return res_.get(); }
1069  Response *operator->() { return res_.get(); }
1070 
1071  // Error
1072  Error error() const { return err_; }
1073 
1074  // Request Headers
1075  bool has_request_header(const std::string &key) const;
1076  std::string get_request_header_value(const std::string &key,
1077  size_t id = 0) const;
1078  uint64_t get_request_header_value_u64(const std::string &key,
1079  size_t id = 0) const;
1080  size_t get_request_header_value_count(const std::string &key) const;
1081 
1082 private:
1083  std::unique_ptr<Response> res_;
1084  Error err_ = Error::Unknown;
1085  Headers request_headers_;
1086 };

1800 namespace detail {
1801 
1802 template <typename T, typename U>
1803 inline void duration_to_sec_and_usec(const T &duration, U callback) {
1804  auto sec = std::chrono::duration_cast<std::chrono::seconds>(duration).count();
1805  auto usec = std::chrono::duration_cast<std::chrono::microseconds>(
1806  duration - std::chrono::seconds(sec))
1807  .count();
1808  callback(static_cast<time_t>(sec), static_cast<time_t>(usec));
1809 }
1810 
1811 inline uint64_t get_header_value_u64(const Headers &headers,
1812  const std::string &key, size_t id,
1813  uint64_t def) {
1814  auto rng = headers.equal_range(key);
1815  auto it = rng.first;
1816  std::advance(it, static_cast<ssize_t>(id));
1817  if (it != rng.second) {
1818  return std::strtoull(it->second.data(), nullptr, 10);
1819  }
1820  return def;
1821 }
1822 
1823 } // namespace detail
1824 
1825 inline uint64_t Request::get_header_value_u64(const std::string &key,
1826  size_t id) const {
1827  return detail::get_header_value_u64(headers, key, id, 0);
1828 }
1829 
1830 inline uint64_t Response::get_header_value_u64(const std::string &key,
1831  size_t id) const {
1832  return detail::get_header_value_u64(headers, key, id, 0);
1833 }
1834 
1835 template <typename... Args>
1836 inline ssize_t Stream::write_format(const char *fmt, const Args &...args) {
1837  const auto bufsiz = 2048;
1838  std::array<char, bufsiz> buf{};
1839 
1840  auto sn = snprintf(buf.data(), buf.size() - 1, fmt, args...);
1841  if (sn <= 0) { return sn; }
1842 
1843  auto n = static_cast<size_t>(sn);
1844 
1845  if (n >= buf.size() - 1) {
1846  std::vector<char> glowable_buf(buf.size());
1847 
1848  while (n >= glowable_buf.size() - 1) {
1849  glowable_buf.resize(glowable_buf.size() * 2);
1850  n = static_cast<size_t>(
1851  snprintf(&glowable_buf[0], glowable_buf.size() - 1, fmt, args...));
1852  }
1853  return write(&glowable_buf[0], n);
1854  } else {
1855  return write(buf.data(), n);
1856  }
1857 }
1858 
1859 inline void default_socket_options(socket_t sock) {
1860  int yes = 1;
1861 #ifdef _WIN32
1862  setsockopt(sock, SOL_SOCKET, SO_REUSEADDR,
1863  reinterpret_cast<const char *>(&yes), sizeof(yes));
1864  setsockopt(sock, SOL_SOCKET, SO_EXCLUSIVEADDRUSE,
1865  reinterpret_cast<const char *>(&yes), sizeof(yes));
1866 #else
1867 #ifdef SO_REUSEPORT
1868  setsockopt(sock, SOL_SOCKET, SO_REUSEPORT,
1869  reinterpret_cast<const void *>(&yes), sizeof(yes));
1870 #else
1871  setsockopt(sock, SOL_SOCKET, SO_REUSEADDR,
1872  reinterpret_cast<const void *>(&yes), sizeof(yes));
1873 #endif
1874 #endif
1875 }
1876 
1877 inline const char *status_message(int status) {
1878  switch (status) {
1879  case StatusCode::Continue_100: return "Continue";
1880  case StatusCode::SwitchingProtocol_101: return "Switching Protocol";
1881  case StatusCode::Processing_102: return "Processing";
1882  case StatusCode::EarlyHints_103: return "Early Hints";
1883  case StatusCode::OK_200: return "OK";
1884  case StatusCode::Created_201: return "Created";
1885  case StatusCode::Accepted_202: return "Accepted";
1886  case StatusCode::NonAuthoritativeInformation_203:
1887  return "Non-Authoritative Information";
1888  case StatusCode::NoContent_204: return "No Content";
1889  case StatusCode::ResetContent_205: return "Reset Content";
1890  case StatusCode::PartialContent_206: return "Partial Content";
1891  case StatusCode::MultiStatus_207: return "Multi-Status";
1892  case StatusCode::AlreadyReported_208: return "Already Reported";
1893  case StatusCode::IMUsed_226: return "IM Used";
1894  case StatusCode::MultipleChoices_300: return "Multiple Choices";
1895  case StatusCode::MovedPermanently_301: return "Moved Permanently";
1896  case StatusCode::Found_302: return "Found";
1897  case StatusCode::SeeOther_303: return "See Other";

2290 inline bool is_hex(char c, int &v) {
2291  if (0x20 <= c && isdigit(c)) {
2292  v = c - '0';
2293  return true;
2294  } else if ('A' <= c && c <= 'F') {
2295  v = c - 'A' + 10;
2296  return true;
2297  } else if ('a' <= c && c <= 'f') {
2298  v = c - 'a' + 10;
2299  return true;
2300  }
2301  return false;
2302 }
2303 
2304 inline bool from_hex_to_i(const std::string &s, size_t i, size_t cnt,
2305  int &val) {
2306  if (i >= s.size()) { return false; }
2307 
2308  val = 0;
2309  for (; cnt; i++, cnt--) {
2310  if (!s[i]) { return false; }
2311  auto v = 0;
2312  if (is_hex(s[i], v)) {
2313  val = val * 16 + v;
2314  } else {
2315  return false;
2316  }
2317  }
2318  return true;
2319 }
2320 
2321 inline std::string from_i_to_hex(size_t n) {
2322  static const auto charset = "0123456789abcdef";
2323  std::string ret;
2324  do {
2325  ret = charset[n & 15] + ret;
2326  n >>= 4;
2327  } while (n > 0);
2328  return ret;
2329 }
2330 
2331 inline size_t to_utf8(int code, char *buff) {
2332  if (code < 0x0080) {
2333  buff[0] = static_cast<char>(code & 0x7F);
2334  return 1;
2335  } else if (code < 0x0800) {
2336  buff[0] = static_cast<char>(0xC0 | ((code >> 6) & 0x1F));
2337  buff[1] = static_cast<char>(0x80 | (code & 0x3F));
2338  return 2;
2339  } else if (code < 0xD800) {
2340  buff[0] = static_cast<char>(0xE0 | ((code >> 12) & 0xF));
2341  buff[1] = static_cast<char>(0x80 | ((code >> 6) & 0x3F));
2342  buff[2] = static_cast<char>(0x80 | (code & 0x3F));
2343  return 3;
2344  } else if (code < 0xE000) { // D800 - DFFF is invalid...
2345  return 0;
2346  } else if (code < 0x10000) {
2347  buff[0] = static_cast<char>(0xE0 | ((code >> 12) & 0xF));
2348  buff[1] = static_cast<char>(0x80 | ((code >> 6) & 0x3F));
2349  buff[2] = static_cast<char>(0x80 | (code & 0x3F));
2350  return 3;
2351  } else if (code < 0x110000) {
2352  buff[0] = static_cast<char>(0xF0 | ((code >> 18) & 0x7));
2353  buff[1] = static_cast<char>(0x80 | ((code >> 12) & 0x3F));
2354  buff[2] = static_cast<char>(0x80 | ((code >> 6) & 0x3F));
2355  buff[3] = static_cast<char>(0x80 | (code & 0x3F));
2356  return 4;
2357  }
2358 
2359  // NOTREACHED
2360  return 0;
2361 }
2362 
2363 // NOTE: This code came up with the following stackoverflow post:
2364 // https://stackoverflow.com/questions/180947/base64-decode-snippet-in-c
2365 inline std::string base64_encode(const std::string &in) {
2366  static const auto lookup =
2367  "ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZabcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz0123456789+/";
2368 
2369  std::string out;
2370  out.reserve(in.size());
2371 
2372  auto val = 0;
2373  auto valb = -6;
2374 
2375  for (auto c : in) {
2376  val = (val << 8) + static_cast<uint8_t>(c);
2377  valb += 8;
2378  while (valb >= 0) {
2379  out.push_back(lookup[(val >> valb) & 0x3F]);
2380  valb -= 6;
2381  }
2382  }
2383 
2384  if (valb > -6) { out.push_back(lookup[((val << 8) >> (valb + 8)) & 0x3F]); }
2385 
2386  while (out.size() % 4) {
2387  out.push_back('=');
2388  }
2389 
2390  return out;
2391 }

2393 inline bool is_file(const std::string &path) {
2394 #ifdef _WIN32
2395  return _access_s(path.c_str(), 0) == 0;
2396 #else
2397  struct stat st;
2398  return stat(path.c_str(), &st) >= 0 && S_ISREG(st.st_mode);
2399 #endif
2400 }
2401 
2402 inline bool is_dir(const std::string &path) {
2403  struct stat st;
2404  return stat(path.c_str(), &st) >= 0 && S_ISDIR(st.st_mode);
2405 }
2406 
2407 inline bool is_valid_path(const std::string &path) {
2408  size_t level = 0;
2409  size_t i = 0;
2410 
2411  // Skip slash
2412  while (i < path.size() && path[i] == '/') {
2413  i++;
2414  }
2415 
2416  while (i < path.size()) {
2417  // Read component
2418  auto beg = i;
2419  while (i < path.size() && path[i] != '/') {
2420  if (path[i] == '\0') {
2421  return false;
2422  } else if (path[i] == '\\') {
2423  return false;
2424  }
2425  i++;
2426  }
2427 
2428  auto len = i - beg;
2429  assert(len > 0);
2430 
2431  if (!path.compare(beg, len, ".")) {
2432  ;
2433  } else if (!path.compare(beg, len, "..")) {
2434  if (level == 0) { return false; }
2435  level--;
2436  } else {
2437  level++;
2438  }
2439 
2440  // Skip slash
2441  while (i < path.size() && path[i] == '/') {
2442  i++;
2443  }
2444  }
2445 
2446  return true;
2447 }
2448 
2449 inline std::string encode_query_param(const std::string &value) {
2450  std::ostringstream escaped;
2451  escaped.fill('0');
2452  escaped << std::hex;
2453 
2454  for (auto c : value) {
2455  if (std::isalnum(static_cast<uint8_t>(c)) || c == '-' || c == '_' ||
2456  c == '.' || c == '!' || c == '~' || c == '*' || c == '\'' || c == '(' ||
2457  c == ')') {
2458  escaped << c;
2459  } else {
2460  escaped << std::uppercase;
2461  escaped << '%' << std::setw(2)
2462  << static_cast<int>(static_cast<unsigned char>(c));
2463  escaped << std::nouppercase;
2464  }
2465  }
2466 
2467  return escaped.str();
2468 }
2469 
2470 inline std::string encode_url(const std::string &s) {
2471  std::string result;
2472  result.reserve(s.size());
2473 
2474  for (size_t i = 0; s[i]; i++) {
2475  switch (s[i]) {
2476  case ' ': result += "%20"; break;
2477  case '+': result += "%2B"; break;
2478  case '\r': result += "%0D"; break;
2479  case '\n': result += "%0A"; break;
2480  case '\'': result += "%27"; break;
2481  case ',': result += "%2C"; break;
2482  // case ':': result += "%3A"; break; // ok? probably...
2483  case ';': result += "%3B"; break;
2484  default:
2485  auto c = static_cast<uint8_t>(s[i]);
2486  if (c >= 0x80) {
2487  result += '%';
2488  char hex[4];
2489  auto len = snprintf(hex, sizeof(hex) - 1, "%02X", c);
2490  assert(len == 2);
2491  result.append(hex, static_cast<size_t>(len));
2492  } else {
2493  result += s[i];
2494  }
2495  break;
2496  }
2497  }
2498 
2499  return result;
2500 }
2501 
2502 inline std::string decode_url(const std::string &s,
2503  bool convert_plus_to_space) {
2504  std::string result;
2505 
2506  for (size_t i = 0; i < s.size(); i++) {
2507  if (s[i] == '%' && i + 1 < s.size()) {
2508  if (s[i + 1] == 'u') {
2509  auto val = 0;
2510  if (from_hex_to_i(s, i + 2, 4, val)) {
2511  // 4 digits Unicode codes
2512  char buff[4];
2513  size_t len = to_utf8(val, buff);
2514  if (len > 0) { result.append(buff, len); }
2515  i += 5; // 'u0000'
2516  } else {
2517  result += s[i];
2518  }
2519  } else {
2520  auto val = 0;
2521  if (from_hex_to_i(s, i + 1, 2, val)) {
2522  // 2 digits hex codes
2523  result += static_cast<char>(val);
2524  i += 2; // '00'
2525  } else {
2526  result += s[i];
2527  }
2528  }
2529  } else if (convert_plus_to_space && s[i] == '+') {
2530  result += ' ';
2531  } else {
2532  result += s[i];
2533  }
2534  }
2535 
2536  return result;
2537 }

2539 inline void read_file(const std::string &path, std::string &out) {
2540  std::ifstream fs(path, std::ios_base::binary);
2541  fs.seekg(0, std::ios_base::end);
2542  auto size = fs.tellg();
2543  fs.seekg(0);
2544  out.resize(static_cast<size_t>(size));
2545  fs.read(&out[0], static_cast<std::streamsize>(size));
2546 }

2548 inline std::string file_extension(const std::string &path) {
2549  std::smatch m;
2550  static auto re = std::regex("\\.([a-zA-Z0-9]+)$");
2551  if (std::regex_search(path, m, re)) { return m[1].str(); }
2552  return std::string();

2555 inline bool is_space_or_tab(char c) { return c == ' ' || c == '\t'; }
2556 
2557 inline std::pair<size_t, size_t> trim(const char *b, const char *e, size_t left,
2558  size_t right) {
2559  while (b + left < e && is_space_or_tab(b[left])) {
2560  left++;
2561  }
2562  while (right > 0 && is_space_or_tab(b[right - 1])) {
2563  right--;
2564  }
2565  return std::make_pair(left, right);
2566 }

2568 inline std::string trim_copy(const std::string &s) {
2569  auto r = trim(s.data(), s.data() + s.size(), 0, s.size());
2570  return s.substr(r.first, r.second - r.first);
2571 }
2572 
2573 inline std::string trim_double_quotes_copy(const std::string &s) {
2574  if (s.length() >= 2 && s.front() == '"' && s.back() == '"') {
2575  return s.substr(1, s.size() - 2);
2576  }
2577  return s;
2578 }

2580 inline void split(const char *b, const char *e, char d,
2581  std::function<void(const char *, const char *)> fn) {
2582  return split(b, e, d, (std::numeric_limits<size_t>::max)(), std::move(fn));
2583 }
2584 
2585 inline void split(const char *b, const char *e, char d, size_t m,
2586  std::function<void(const char *, const char *)> fn) {
2587  size_t i = 0;
2588  size_t beg = 0;
2589  size_t count = 1;
2590 
2591  while (e ? (b + i < e) : (b[i] != '\0')) {
2592  if (b[i] == d && count < m) {
2593  auto r = trim(b, e, beg, i);
2594  if (r.first < r.second) { fn(&b[r.first], &b[r.second]); }
2595  beg = i + 1;
2596  count++;
2597  }
2598  i++;
2599  }
2600 
2601  if (i) {
2602  auto r = trim(b, e, beg, i);
2603  if (r.first < r.second) { fn(&b[r.first], &b[r.second]); }
2604  }
2605 }

2633 inline bool stream_line_reader::getline() {
2634  fixed_buffer_used_size_ = 0;
2635  glowable_buffer_.clear();
2636 
2637  for (size_t i = 0;; i++) {
2638  char byte;
2639  auto n = strm_.read(&byte, 1);
2640 
2641  if (n < 0) {
2642  return false;
2643  } else if (n == 0) {
2644  if (i == 0) {
2645  return false;
2646  } else {
2647  break;
2648  }
2649  }
2650 
2651  append(byte);
2652 
2653  if (byte == '\n') { break; }
2654  }
2655 
2656  return true;
2657 }

2659 inline void stream_line_reader::append(char c) {
2660  if (fixed_buffer_used_size_ < fixed_buffer_size_ - 1) {
2661  fixed_buffer_[fixed_buffer_used_size_++] = c;
2662  fixed_buffer_[fixed_buffer_used_size_] = '\0';
2663  } else {
2664  if (glowable_buffer_.empty()) {
2665  assert(fixed_buffer_[fixed_buffer_used_size_] == '\0');
2666  glowable_buffer_.assign(fixed_buffer_, fixed_buffer_used_size_);
2667  }
2668  glowable_buffer_ += c;
2669  }
2670 }

2685 inline bool mmap::open(const char *path) {
2686  close();
2687 
2688 #if defined(_WIN32)
2689  std::wstring wpath;
2690  for (size_t i = 0; i < strlen(path); i++) {
2691  wpath += path[i];
2692  }
2693 
2694  hFile_ = ::CreateFile2(wpath.c_str(), GENERIC_READ, FILE_SHARE_READ,
2695  OPEN_EXISTING, NULL);
2696 
2697  if (hFile_ == INVALID_HANDLE_VALUE) { return false; }
2698 
2699  LARGE_INTEGER size{};
2700  if (!::GetFileSizeEx(hFile_, &size)) { return false; }
2701  size_ = static_cast<size_t>(size.QuadPart);
2702 
2703  hMapping_ = ::CreateFileMappingFromApp(hFile_, NULL, PAGE_READONLY, size_,
2704  NULL);
2705 
2706  if (hMapping_ == NULL) {
2707  close();
2708  return false;
2709  }
2710 
2711  addr_ = ::MapViewOfFileFromApp(hMapping_, FILE_MAP_READ, 0, 0);
2712 #else
2713  fd_ = ::open(path, O_RDONLY);
2714  if (fd_ == -1) { return false; }
2715 
2716  struct stat sb;
2717  if (fstat(fd_, &sb) == -1) {
2718  close();
2719  return false;
2720  }
2721  size_ = static_cast<size_t>(sb.st_size);
2722 
2723  addr_ = ::mmap(NULL, size_, PROT_READ, MAP_PRIVATE, fd_, 0);
2724 #endif
2725 
2726  if (addr_ == nullptr) {
2727  close();
2728  return false;
2729  }
2730 
2731  return true;
2732 }

2766  fd_ = -1;
2767  }

2779 template <typename T> inline ssize_t handle_EINTR(T fn) {
2780  ssize_t res = 0;
2781  while (true) {
2782  res = fn();
2783  if (res < 0 && errno == EINTR) { continue; }
2784  break;
2785  }
2786  return res;
2787 }

2814 inline ssize_t select_read(socket_t sock, time_t sec, time_t usec) {
2815 #ifdef CPPHTTPLIB_USE_POLL
2816  struct pollfd pfd_read;
2817  pfd_read.fd = sock;
2818  pfd_read.events = POLLIN;
2819 
2820  auto timeout = static_cast<int>(sec * 1000 + usec / 1000);
2821 
2822  return handle_EINTR([&]() { return poll(&pfd_read, 1, timeout); });
2823 #else
2824 #ifndef _WIN32
2825  if (sock >= FD_SETSIZE) { return -1; }
2826 #endif
2827 
2828  fd_set fds;
2829  FD_ZERO(&fds);
2830  FD_SET(sock, &fds);
2831 
2832  timeval tv;
2833  tv.tv_sec = static_cast<long>(sec);
2834  tv.tv_usec = static_cast<decltype(tv.tv_usec)>(usec);
2835 
2836  return handle_EINTR([&]() {
2837  return select(static_cast<int>(sock + 1), &fds, nullptr, nullptr, &tv);
2838  });
2839 #endif
2840 }
2841 
2842 inline ssize_t select_write(socket_t sock, time_t sec, time_t usec) {
2843 #ifdef CPPHTTPLIB_USE_POLL
2844  struct pollfd pfd_read;
2845  pfd_read.fd = sock;
2846  pfd_read.events = POLLOUT;
2847 
2848  auto timeout = static_cast<int>(sec * 1000 + usec / 1000);
2849 
2850  return handle_EINTR([&]() { return poll(&pfd_read, 1, timeout); });
2851 #else
2852 #ifndef _WIN32
2853  if (sock >= FD_SETSIZE) { return -1; }
2854 #endif
2855 
2856  fd_set fds;
2857  FD_ZERO(&fds);
2858  FD_SET(sock, &fds);
2859 
2860  timeval tv;
2861  tv.tv_sec = static_cast<long>(sec);
2862  tv.tv_usec = static_cast<decltype(tv.tv_usec)>(usec);
2863 
2864  return handle_EINTR([&]() {
2865  return select(static_cast<int>(sock + 1), nullptr, &fds, nullptr, &tv);
2866  });
2867 #endif
2868 }
2869 
2870 inline Error wait_until_socket_is_ready(socket_t sock, time_t sec,
2871  time_t usec) {
2872 #ifdef CPPHTTPLIB_USE_POLL
2873  struct pollfd pfd_read;
2874  pfd_read.fd = sock;
2875  pfd_read.events = POLLIN | POLLOUT;
2876 
2877  auto timeout = static_cast<int>(sec * 1000 + usec / 1000);
2878 
2879  auto poll_res = handle_EINTR([&]() { return poll(&pfd_read, 1, timeout); });
2880 
2881  if (poll_res == 0) { return Error::ConnectionTimeout; }
2882 
2883  if (poll_res > 0 && pfd_read.revents & (POLLIN | POLLOUT)) {
2884  auto error = 0;
2885  socklen_t len = sizeof(error);
2886  auto res = getsockopt(sock, SOL_SOCKET, SO_ERROR,
2887  reinterpret_cast<char *>(&error), &len);
2888  auto successful = res >= 0 && !error;
2889  return successful ? Error::Success : Error::Connection;
2890  }
2891 
2892  return Error::Connection;
2893 #else
2894 #ifndef _WIN32
2895  if (sock >= FD_SETSIZE) { return Error::Connection; }
2896 #endif
2897 
2898  fd_set fdsr;
2899  FD_ZERO(&fdsr);
2900  FD_SET(sock, &fdsr);
2901 
2902  auto fdsw = fdsr;
2903  auto fdse = fdsr;
2904 
2905  timeval tv;
2906  tv.tv_sec = static_cast<long>(sec);
2907  tv.tv_usec = static_cast<decltype(tv.tv_usec)>(usec);
2908 
2909  auto ret = handle_EINTR([&]() {
2910  return select(static_cast<int>(sock + 1), &fdsr, &fdsw, &fdse, &tv);
2911  });
2912 
2913  if (ret == 0) { return Error::ConnectionTimeout; }
2914 
2915  if (ret > 0 && (FD_ISSET(sock, &fdsr) || FD_ISSET(sock, &fdsw))) {
2916  auto error = 0;
2917  socklen_t len = sizeof(error);
2918  auto res = getsockopt(sock, SOL_SOCKET, SO_ERROR,
2919  reinterpret_cast<char *>(&error), &len);
2920  auto successful = res >= 0 && !error;
2921  return successful ? Error::Success : Error::Connection;
2922  }
2923  return Error::Connection;
2924 #endif
2925 }

2927 inline bool is_socket_alive(socket_t sock) {
2928  const auto val = detail::select_read(sock, 0, 0);
2929  if (val == 0) {
2930  return true;
2931  } else if (val < 0 && errno == EBADF) {
2932  return false;
2933  }
2934  char buf[1];
2935  return detail::read_socket(sock, &buf[0], sizeof(buf), MSG_PEEK) > 0;
2936 }

2992 inline bool keep_alive(socket_t sock, time_t keep_alive_timeout_sec) {
2993  using namespace std::chrono;
2994  auto start = steady_clock::now();
2995  while (true) {
2996  auto val = select_read(sock, 0, 10000);
2997  if (val < 0) {
2998  return false;
2999  } else if (val == 0) {
3000  auto current = steady_clock::now();
3001  auto duration = duration_cast<milliseconds>(current - start);
3002  auto timeout = keep_alive_timeout_sec * 1000;
3003  if (duration.count() > timeout) { return false; }
3004  std::this_thread::sleep_for(std::chrono::milliseconds(1));
3005  } else {
3006  return true;
3007  }
3008  }
3009 }

3011 template <typename T>
3012 inline bool
3013 process_server_socket_core(const std::atomic<socket_t> &svr_sock, socket_t sock,
3014  size_t keep_alive_max_count,
3015  time_t keep_alive_timeout_sec, T callback) {
3016  assert(keep_alive_max_count > 0);
3017  auto ret = false;
3018  auto count = keep_alive_max_count;
3019  while (svr_sock != INVALID_SOCKET && count > 0 &&
3020  keep_alive(sock, keep_alive_timeout_sec)) {
3021  auto close_connection = count == 1;
3022  auto connection_closed = false;
3023  ret = callback(close_connection, connection_closed);
3024  if (!ret || connection_closed) { break; }
3025  count--;
3026  }
3027  return ret;
3028 }

3036  time_t write_timeout_usec, T callback) {

3040  SocketStream strm(sock, read_timeout_sec, read_timeout_usec,
3041  write_timeout_sec, write_timeout_usec);

3064 template <typename BindOrConnect>
3065 socket_t create_socket(const std::string &host, const std::string &ip, int port,
3066  int address_family, int socket_flags, bool tcp_nodelay,
3067  SocketOptions socket_options,
3068  BindOrConnect bind_or_connect) {
3069  // Get address info
3070  const char *node = nullptr;
3071  struct addrinfo hints;
3072  struct addrinfo *result;
3073 
3074  memset(&hints, 0, sizeof(struct addrinfo));
3075  hints.ai_socktype = SOCK_STREAM;
3076  hints.ai_protocol = 0;
3077 
3078  if (!ip.empty()) {
3079  node = ip.c_str();
3080  // Ask getaddrinfo to convert IP in c-string to address
3081  hints.ai_family = AF_UNSPEC;
3082  hints.ai_flags = AI_NUMERICHOST;
3083  } else {
3084  if (!host.empty()) { node = host.c_str(); }
3085  hints.ai_family = address_family;
3086  hints.ai_flags = socket_flags;
3087  }
3088 
3089 #ifndef _WIN32
3090  if (hints.ai_family == AF_UNIX) {
3091  const auto addrlen = host.length();
3092  if (addrlen > sizeof(sockaddr_un::sun_path)) { return INVALID_SOCKET; }
3093 
3094  auto sock = socket(hints.ai_family, hints.ai_socktype, hints.ai_protocol);
3095  if (sock != INVALID_SOCKET) {
3096  sockaddr_un addr{};
3097  addr.sun_family = AF_UNIX;
3098  std::copy(host.begin(), host.end(), addr.sun_path);
3099 
3100  hints.ai_addr = reinterpret_cast<sockaddr *>(&addr);
3101  hints.ai_addrlen = static_cast<socklen_t>(
3102  sizeof(addr) - sizeof(addr.sun_path) + addrlen);
3103 
3104  fcntl(sock, F_SETFD, FD_CLOEXEC);
3105  if (socket_options) { socket_options(sock); }
3106 
3107  if (!bind_or_connect(sock, hints)) {
3108  close_socket(sock);
3109  sock = INVALID_SOCKET;
3110  }
3111  }
3112  return sock;
3113  }
3114 #endif
3115 
3116  auto service = std::to_string(port);
3117 
3118  if (getaddrinfo(node, service.c_str(), &hints, &result)) {
3119 #if defined __linux__ && !defined __ANDROID__
3120  res_init();
3121 #endif
3122  return INVALID_SOCKET;
3123  }
3124 
3125  for (auto rp = result; rp; rp = rp->ai_next) {
3126  // Create a socket
3127 #ifdef _WIN32
3128  auto sock =
3129  WSASocketW(rp->ai_family, rp->ai_socktype, rp->ai_protocol, nullptr, 0,
3130  WSA_FLAG_NO_HANDLE_INHERIT | WSA_FLAG_OVERLAPPED);
3145  if (sock == INVALID_SOCKET) {
3146  sock = socket(rp->ai_family, rp->ai_socktype, rp->ai_protocol);
3147  }
3148 #else
3149  auto sock = socket(rp->ai_family, rp->ai_socktype, rp->ai_protocol);
3150 #endif
3151  if (sock == INVALID_SOCKET) { continue; }
3152 
3153 #ifndef _WIN32
3154  if (fcntl(sock, F_SETFD, FD_CLOEXEC) == -1) {
3155  close_socket(sock);
3156  continue;
3157  }
3158 #endif
3159 
3160  if (tcp_nodelay) {
3161  auto yes = 1;
3162 #ifdef _WIN32
3163  setsockopt(sock, IPPROTO_TCP, TCP_NODELAY,
3164  reinterpret_cast<const char *>(&yes), sizeof(yes));
3165 #else
3166  setsockopt(sock, IPPROTO_TCP, TCP_NODELAY,
3167  reinterpret_cast<const void *>(&yes), sizeof(yes));
3168 #endif
3169  }
3170 
3171  if (socket_options) { socket_options(sock); }
3172 
3173  if (rp->ai_family == AF_INET6) {
3174  auto no = 0;
3175 #ifdef _WIN32
3176  setsockopt(sock, IPPROTO_IPV6, IPV6_V6ONLY,
3177  reinterpret_cast<const char *>(&no), sizeof(no));
3178 #else
3179  setsockopt(sock, IPPROTO_IPV6, IPV6_V6ONLY,
3180  reinterpret_cast<const void *>(&no), sizeof(no));
3181 #endif
3182  }
3183 
3184  // bind or connect
3185  if (bind_or_connect(sock, *rp)) {
3186  freeaddrinfo(result);
3187  return sock;
3188  }
3189 
3190  close_socket(sock);
3191  }
3192 
3193  freeaddrinfo(result);
3194  return INVALID_SOCKET;
3195 }
3196 
3197 inline void set_nonblocking(socket_t sock, bool nonblocking) {
3198 #ifdef _WIN32
3199  auto flags = nonblocking ? 1UL : 0UL;
3200  ioctlsocket(sock, FIONBIO, &flags);
3201 #else
3202  auto flags = fcntl(sock, F_GETFL, 0);
3203  fcntl(sock, F_SETFL,
3204  nonblocking ? (flags | O_NONBLOCK) : (flags & (~O_NONBLOCK)));
3205 #endif
3206 }

3208 inline bool is_connection_error() {
3209 #ifdef _WIN32
3210  return WSAGetLastError() != WSAEWOULDBLOCK;
3211 #else
3212  return errno != EINPROGRESS;
3213 #endif
3214 }

3216 inline bool bind_ip_address(socket_t sock, const std::string &host) {
3217  struct addrinfo hints;
3218  struct addrinfo *result;
3219 
3220  memset(&hints, 0, sizeof(struct addrinfo));
3221  hints.ai_family = AF_UNSPEC;
3222  hints.ai_socktype = SOCK_STREAM;
3223  hints.ai_protocol = 0;
3224 
3225  if (getaddrinfo(host.c_str(), "0", &hints, &result)) { return false; }
3226 
3227  auto ret = false;
3228  for (auto rp = result; rp; rp = rp->ai_next) {
3229  const auto &ai = *rp;
3230  if (!::bind(sock, ai.ai_addr, static_cast<socklen_t>(ai.ai_addrlen))) {
3231  ret = true;
3232  break;
3233  }
3234  }
3235 
3236  freeaddrinfo(result);
3237  return ret;
3238 }
3239 
3240 #if !defined _WIN32 && !defined ANDROID && !defined _AIX && !defined __MVS__
3241 #define USE_IF2IP
3242 #endif
3243 
3244 #ifdef USE_IF2IP
3245 inline std::string if2ip(int address_family, const std::string &ifn) {
3246  struct ifaddrs *ifap;
3247  getifaddrs(&ifap);
3248  std::string addr_candidate;
3249  for (auto ifa = ifap; ifa; ifa = ifa->ifa_next) {
3250  if (ifa->ifa_addr && ifn == ifa->ifa_name &&
3251  (AF_UNSPEC == address_family ||
3252  ifa->ifa_addr->sa_family == address_family)) {
3253  if (ifa->ifa_addr->sa_family == AF_INET) {
3254  auto sa = reinterpret_cast<struct sockaddr_in *>(ifa->ifa_addr);
3255  char buf[INET_ADDRSTRLEN];
3256  if (inet_ntop(AF_INET, &sa->sin_addr, buf, INET_ADDRSTRLEN)) {
3257  freeifaddrs(ifap);
3258  return std::string(buf, INET_ADDRSTRLEN);
3259  }
3260  } else if (ifa->ifa_addr->sa_family == AF_INET6) {
3261  auto sa = reinterpret_cast<struct sockaddr_in6 *>(ifa->ifa_addr);
3262  if (!IN6_IS_ADDR_LINKLOCAL(&sa->sin6_addr)) {
3263  char buf[INET6_ADDRSTRLEN] = {};
3264  if (inet_ntop(AF_INET6, &sa->sin6_addr, buf, INET6_ADDRSTRLEN)) {
3265  // equivalent to mac's IN6_IS_ADDR_UNIQUE_LOCAL
3266  auto s6_addr_head = sa->sin6_addr.s6_addr[0];
3267  if (s6_addr_head == 0xfc || s6_addr_head == 0xfd) {
3268  addr_candidate = std::string(buf, INET6_ADDRSTRLEN);
3269  } else {
3270  freeifaddrs(ifap);
3271  return std::string(buf, INET6_ADDRSTRLEN);
3272  }
3273  }
3274  }
3275  }
3276  }
3277  }
3278  freeifaddrs(ifap);
3279  return addr_candidate;
3280 }
3281 #endif
3282 
3283 inline socket_t create_client_socket(
3284  const std::string &host, const std::string &ip, int port,
3285  int address_family, bool tcp_nodelay, SocketOptions socket_options,
3286  time_t connection_timeout_sec, time_t connection_timeout_usec,
3287  time_t read_timeout_sec, time_t read_timeout_usec, time_t write_timeout_sec,
3288  time_t write_timeout_usec, const std::string &intf, Error &error) {
3289  auto sock = create_socket(
3290  host, ip, port, address_family, 0, tcp_nodelay, std::move(socket_options),
3291  [&](socket_t sock2, struct addrinfo &ai) -> bool {
3292  if (!intf.empty()) {
3293 #ifdef USE_IF2IP
3294  auto ip_from_if = if2ip(address_family, intf);
3295  if (ip_from_if.empty()) { ip_from_if = intf; }
3296  if (!bind_ip_address(sock2, ip_from_if)) {
3297  error = Error::BindIPAddress;
3298  return false;
3299  }
3300 #endif
3301  }
3302 
3303  set_nonblocking(sock2, true);
3304 
3305  auto ret =
3306  ::connect(sock2, ai.ai_addr, static_cast<socklen_t>(ai.ai_addrlen));
3307 
3308  if (ret < 0) {
3309  if (is_connection_error()) {
3310  error = Error::Connection;
3311  return false;
3312  }
3313  error = wait_until_socket_is_ready(sock2, connection_timeout_sec,
3314  connection_timeout_usec);
3315  if (error != Error::Success) { return false; }
3316  }
3317 
3318  set_nonblocking(sock2, false);
3319 
3320  {
3321 #ifdef _WIN32
3322  auto timeout = static_cast<uint32_t>(read_timeout_sec * 1000 +
3323  read_timeout_usec / 1000);
3324  setsockopt(sock2, SOL_SOCKET, SO_RCVTIMEO,
3325  reinterpret_cast<const char *>(&timeout), sizeof(timeout));
3326 #else
3327  timeval tv;
3328  tv.tv_sec = static_cast<long>(read_timeout_sec);
3329  tv.tv_usec = static_cast<decltype(tv.tv_usec)>(read_timeout_usec);
3330  setsockopt(sock2, SOL_SOCKET, SO_RCVTIMEO,
3331  reinterpret_cast<const void *>(&tv), sizeof(tv));
3332 #endif
3333  }
3334  {
3335 
3336 #ifdef _WIN32
3337  auto timeout = static_cast<uint32_t>(write_timeout_sec * 1000 +
3338  write_timeout_usec / 1000);
3339  setsockopt(sock2, SOL_SOCKET, SO_SNDTIMEO,
3340  reinterpret_cast<const char *>(&timeout), sizeof(timeout));
3341 #else
3342  timeval tv;
3343  tv.tv_sec = static_cast<long>(write_timeout_sec);
3344  tv.tv_usec = static_cast<decltype(tv.tv_usec)>(write_timeout_usec);
3345  setsockopt(sock2, SOL_SOCKET, SO_SNDTIMEO,
3346  reinterpret_cast<const void *>(&tv), sizeof(tv));
3347 #endif
3348  }
3349 
3350  error = Error::Success;
3351  return true;
3352  });
3353 
3354  if (sock != INVALID_SOCKET) {
3355  error = Error::Success;
3356  } else {
3357  if (error == Error::Success) { error = Error::Connection; }
3358  }
3359 
3360  return sock;
3361 }
3362 
3363 inline bool get_ip_and_port(const struct sockaddr_storage &addr,
3364  socklen_t addr_len, std::string &ip, int &port) {
3365  if (addr.ss_family == AF_INET) {
3366  port = ntohs(reinterpret_cast<const struct sockaddr_in *>(&addr)->sin_port);
3367  } else if (addr.ss_family == AF_INET6) {
3368  port =
3369  ntohs(reinterpret_cast<const struct sockaddr_in6 *>(&addr)->sin6_port);
3370  } else {
3371  return false;
3372  }
3373 
3374  std::array<char, NI_MAXHOST> ipstr{};
3375  if (getnameinfo(reinterpret_cast<const struct sockaddr *>(&addr), addr_len,
3376  ipstr.data(), static_cast<socklen_t>(ipstr.size()), nullptr,
3377  0, NI_NUMERICHOST)) {
3378  return false;
3379  }
3380 
3381  ip = ipstr.data();
3382  return true;
3383 }
3384 
3385 inline void get_local_ip_and_port(socket_t sock, std::string &ip, int &port) {
3386  struct sockaddr_storage addr;
3387  socklen_t addr_len = sizeof(addr);
3388  if (!getsockname(sock, reinterpret_cast<struct sockaddr *>(&addr),
3389  &addr_len)) {
3390  get_ip_and_port(addr, addr_len, ip, port);
3391  }
3392 }
3393 
3394 inline void get_remote_ip_and_port(socket_t sock, std::string &ip, int &port) {
3395  struct sockaddr_storage addr;
3396  socklen_t addr_len = sizeof(addr);
3397 
3398  if (!getpeername(sock, reinterpret_cast<struct sockaddr *>(&addr),
3399  &addr_len)) {
3400 #ifndef _WIN32
3401  if (addr.ss_family == AF_UNIX) {
3402 #if defined(__linux__)
3403  struct ucred ucred;
3404  socklen_t len = sizeof(ucred);
3405  if (getsockopt(sock, SOL_SOCKET, SO_PEERCRED, &ucred, &len) == 0) {
3406  port = ucred.pid;
3407  }
3408 #elif defined(SOL_LOCAL) && defined(SO_PEERPID) // __APPLE__
3409  pid_t pid;
3410  socklen_t len = sizeof(pid);
3411  if (getsockopt(sock, SOL_LOCAL, SO_PEERPID, &pid, &len) == 0) {
3412  port = pid;
3413  }
3414 #endif
3415  return;
3416  }
3417 #endif
3418  get_ip_and_port(addr, addr_len, ip, port);
3419  }
3420 }

3422 inline constexpr unsigned int str2tag_core(const char *s, size_t l,
3423  unsigned int h) {
3424  return (l == 0)
3425  ? h
3426  : str2tag_core(
3427  s + 1, l - 1,
3428  // Unsets the 6 high bits of h, therefore no overflow happens
3429  (((std::numeric_limits<unsigned int>::max)() >> 6) &
3430  h * 33) ^
3431  static_cast<unsigned char>(*s));
3432 }
3433 
3434 inline unsigned int str2tag(const std::string &s) {
3435  return str2tag_core(s.data(), s.size(), 0);
3436 }

3512 inline bool can_compress_content_type(const std::string &content_type) {
3513  using udl::operator""_t;
3514 
3515  auto tag = str2tag(content_type);
3516 
3517  switch (tag) {
3518  case "image/svg+xml"_t:
3519  case "application/javascript"_t:
3520  case "application/json"_t:
3521  case "application/xml"_t:
3522  case "application/protobuf"_t:
3523  case "application/xhtml+xml"_t: return true;
3524 
3525  default:
3526  return !content_type.rfind("text/", 0) && tag != "text/event-stream"_t;
3527  }
3528 }

3530 inline EncodingType encoding_type(const Request &req, const Response &res) {
3531  auto ret =
3532  detail::can_compress_content_type(res.get_header_value("Content-Type"));
3533  if (!ret) { return EncodingType::None; }
3534 
3535  const auto &s = req.get_header_value("Accept-Encoding");
3536  (void)(s);
3537 
3538 #ifdef CPPHTTPLIB_BROTLI_SUPPORT
3539  // TODO: 'Accept-Encoding' has br, not br;q=0
3540  ret = s.find("br") != std::string::npos;
3541  if (ret) { return EncodingType::Brotli; }
3542 #endif
3543 
3544 #ifdef CPPHTTPLIB_ZLIB_SUPPORT
3545  // TODO: 'Accept-Encoding' has gzip, not gzip;q=0
3546  ret = s.find("gzip") != std::string::npos;
3547  if (ret) { return EncodingType::Gzip; }
3548 #endif
3549 
3550  return EncodingType::None;
3551 }

3559 #ifdef CPPHTTPLIB_ZLIB_SUPPORT
3560 inline gzip_compressor::gzip_compressor() {
3561  std::memset(&strm_, 0, sizeof(strm_));
3562  strm_.zalloc = Z_NULL;
3563  strm_.zfree = Z_NULL;
3564  strm_.opaque = Z_NULL;
3565 
3566  is_valid_ = deflateInit2(&strm_, Z_DEFAULT_COMPRESSION, Z_DEFLATED, 31, 8,
3567  Z_DEFAULT_STRATEGY) == Z_OK;
3568 }
3569 
3570 inline gzip_compressor::~gzip_compressor() { deflateEnd(&strm_); }
3571 
3572 inline bool gzip_compressor::compress(const char *data, size_t data_length,
3573  bool last, Callback callback) {
3574  assert(is_valid_);
3575 
3576  do {
3577  constexpr size_t max_avail_in =
3578  (std::numeric_limits<decltype(strm_.avail_in)>::max)();
3579 
3580  strm_.avail_in = static_cast<decltype(strm_.avail_in)>(
3581  (std::min)(data_length, max_avail_in));
3582  strm_.next_in = const_cast<Bytef *>(reinterpret_cast<const Bytef *>(data));
3583 
3584  data_length -= strm_.avail_in;
3585  data += strm_.avail_in;
3586 
3587  auto flush = (last && data_length == 0) ? Z_FINISH : Z_NO_FLUSH;
3588  auto ret = Z_OK;
3589 
3590  std::array<char, CPPHTTPLIB_COMPRESSION_BUFSIZ> buff{};
3591  do {
3592  strm_.avail_out = static_cast<uInt>(buff.size());
3593  strm_.next_out = reinterpret_cast<Bytef *>(buff.data());
3594 
3595  ret = deflate(&strm_, flush);
3596  if (ret == Z_STREAM_ERROR) { return false; }
3597 
3598  if (!callback(buff.data(), buff.size() - strm_.avail_out)) {
3599  return false;
3600  }
3601  } while (strm_.avail_out == 0);
3602 
3603  assert((flush == Z_FINISH && ret == Z_STREAM_END) ||
3604  (flush == Z_NO_FLUSH && ret == Z_OK));
3605  assert(strm_.avail_in == 0);
3606  } while (data_length > 0);
3607 
3608  return true;
3609 }

3611 inline gzip_decompressor::gzip_decompressor() {
3612  std::memset(&strm_, 0, sizeof(strm_));
3613  strm_.zalloc = Z_NULL;
3614  strm_.zfree = Z_NULL;
3615  strm_.opaque = Z_NULL;
3616 
3617  // 15 is the value of wbits, which should be at the maximum possible value
3618  // to ensure that any gzip stream can be decoded. The offset of 32 specifies
3619  // that the stream type should be automatically detected either gzip or
3620  // deflate.
3621  is_valid_ = inflateInit2(&strm_, 32 + 15) == Z_OK;
3622 }
3623 
3624 inline gzip_decompressor::~gzip_decompressor() { inflateEnd(&strm_); }
3625 
3626 inline bool gzip_decompressor::is_valid() const { return is_valid_; }
3627 
3628 inline bool gzip_decompressor::decompress(const char *data, size_t data_length,
3629  Callback callback) {
3630  assert(is_valid_);
3631 
3632  auto ret = Z_OK;
3633 
3634  do {
3635  constexpr size_t max_avail_in =
3636  (std::numeric_limits<decltype(strm_.avail_in)>::max)();
3637 
3638  strm_.avail_in = static_cast<decltype(strm_.avail_in)>(
3639  (std::min)(data_length, max_avail_in));
3640  strm_.next_in = const_cast<Bytef *>(reinterpret_cast<const Bytef *>(data));
3641 
3642  data_length -= strm_.avail_in;
3643  data += strm_.avail_in;
3644 
3645  std::array<char, CPPHTTPLIB_COMPRESSION_BUFSIZ> buff{};
3646  while (strm_.avail_in > 0 && ret == Z_OK) {
3647  strm_.avail_out = static_cast<uInt>(buff.size());
3648  strm_.next_out = reinterpret_cast<Bytef *>(buff.data());
3649 
3650  ret = inflate(&strm_, Z_NO_FLUSH);
3651 
3652  assert(ret != Z_STREAM_ERROR);
3653  switch (ret) {
3654  case Z_NEED_DICT:
3655  case Z_DATA_ERROR:
3656  case Z_MEM_ERROR: inflateEnd(&strm_); return false;
3657  }
3658 
3659  if (!callback(buff.data(), buff.size() - strm_.avail_out)) {
3660  return false;
3661  }
3662  }
3663 
3664  if (ret != Z_OK && ret != Z_STREAM_END) { return false; }
3665 
3666  } while (data_length > 0);
3667 
3668  return true;
3669 }
3670 #endif

3672 #ifdef CPPHTTPLIB_BROTLI_SUPPORT
3673 inline brotli_compressor::brotli_compressor() {

3675 }

3678  BrotliEncoderDestroyInstance(state_);
3679 }
3680 
3681 inline bool brotli_compressor::compress(const char *data, size_t data_length,
3682  bool last, Callback callback) {
3683  std::array<uint8_t, CPPHTTPLIB_COMPRESSION_BUFSIZ> buff{};
3684 
3685  auto operation = last ? BROTLI_OPERATION_FINISH : BROTLI_OPERATION_PROCESS;
3686  auto available_in = data_length;
3687  auto next_in = reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t *>(data);
3688 
3689  for (;;) {
3690  if (last) {
3691  if (BrotliEncoderIsFinished(state_)) { break; }
3692  } else {
3693  if (!available_in) { break; }
3694  }
3695 
3696  auto available_out = buff.size();
3697  auto next_out = buff.data();
3698 
3699  if (!BrotliEncoderCompressStream(state_, operation, &available_in, &next_in,
3700  &available_out, &next_out, nullptr)) {
3701  return false;
3702  }
3703 
3704  auto output_bytes = buff.size() - available_out;
3705  if (output_bytes) {
3706  callback(reinterpret_cast<const char *>(buff.data()), output_bytes);
3707  }
3708  }
3709 
3710  return true;
3711 }

3715  decoder_r = decoder_s ? BROTLI_DECODER_RESULT_NEEDS_MORE_INPUT
3716  : BROTLI_DECODER_RESULT_ERROR;
3717 }

3721 }
3722 
3723 inline bool brotli_decompressor::is_valid() const { return decoder_s; }
3724 
3725 inline bool brotli_decompressor::decompress(const char *data,
3726  size_t data_length,
3727  Callback callback) {
3728  if (decoder_r == BROTLI_DECODER_RESULT_SUCCESS ||
3729  decoder_r == BROTLI_DECODER_RESULT_ERROR) {
3730  return 0;
3731  }
3732 
3733  auto next_in = reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t *>(data);
3734  size_t avail_in = data_length;
3735  size_t total_out;
3736 
3737  decoder_r = BROTLI_DECODER_RESULT_NEEDS_MORE_OUTPUT;
3738 
3739  std::array<char, CPPHTTPLIB_COMPRESSION_BUFSIZ> buff{};
3740  while (decoder_r == BROTLI_DECODER_RESULT_NEEDS_MORE_OUTPUT) {
3741  char *next_out = buff.data();
3742  size_t avail_out = buff.size();
3743 
3744  decoder_r = BrotliDecoderDecompressStream(
3745  decoder_s, &avail_in, &next_in, &avail_out,
3746  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t **>(&next_out), &total_out);
3747 
3748  if (decoder_r == BROTLI_DECODER_RESULT_ERROR) { return false; }
3749 
3750  if (!callback(buff.data(), buff.size() - avail_out)) { return false; }
3751  }
3752 
3753  return decoder_r == BROTLI_DECODER_RESULT_SUCCESS ||
3754  decoder_r == BROTLI_DECODER_RESULT_NEEDS_MORE_INPUT;
3755 }
3756 #endif
3757 
3758 inline bool has_header(const Headers &headers, const std::string &key) {
3759  return headers.find(key) != headers.end();
3760 }
3761 
3762 inline const char *get_header_value(const Headers &headers,
3763  const std::string &key, size_t id,
3764  const char *def) {
3765  auto rng = headers.equal_range(key);
3766  auto it = rng.first;
3767  std::advance(it, static_cast<ssize_t>(id));
3768  if (it != rng.second) { return it->second.c_str(); }
3769  return def;
3770 }

3772 inline bool compare_case_ignore(const std::string &a, const std::string &b) {
3773  if (a.size() != b.size()) { return false; }
3774  for (size_t i = 0; i < b.size(); i++) {
3775  if (::tolower(a[i]) != ::tolower(b[i])) { return false; }
3776  }
3777  return true;
3778 }
3779 
3780 template <typename T>
3781 inline bool parse_header(const char *beg, const char *end, T fn) {
3782  // Skip trailing spaces and tabs.
3783  while (beg < end && is_space_or_tab(end[-1])) {
3784  end--;
3785  }
3786 
3787  auto p = beg;
3788  while (p < end && *p != ':') {
3789  p++;
3790  }
3791 
3792  if (p == end) { return false; }
3793 
3794  auto key_end = p;
3795 
3796  if (*p++ != ':') { return false; }
3797 
3798  while (p < end && is_space_or_tab(*p)) {
3799  p++;
3800  }
3801 
3802  if (p < end) {
3803  auto key_len = key_end - beg;
3804  if (!key_len) { return false; }
3805 
3806  auto key = std::string(beg, key_end);
3807  auto val = compare_case_ignore(key, "Location")
3808  ? std::string(p, end)
3809  : decode_url(std::string(p, end), false);
3810  fn(std::move(key), std::move(val));
3811  return true;
3812  }
3813 
3814  return false;
3815 }
3816 
3817 inline bool read_headers(Stream &strm, Headers &headers) {
3818  const auto bufsiz = 2048;
3819  char buf[bufsiz];
3820  stream_line_reader line_reader(strm, buf, bufsiz);
3821 
3822  for (;;) {
3823  if (!line_reader.getline()) { return false; }
3824 
3825  // Check if the line ends with CRLF.
3826  auto line_terminator_len = 2;
3827  if (line_reader.end_with_crlf()) {
3828  // Blank line indicates end of headers.
3829  if (line_reader.size() == 2) { break; }
3830 #ifdef CPPHTTPLIB_ALLOW_LF_AS_LINE_TERMINATOR
3831  } else {
3832  // Blank line indicates end of headers.
3833  if (line_reader.size() == 1) { break; }
3834  line_terminator_len = 1;
3835  }
3836 #else
3837  } else {
3838  continue; // Skip invalid line.
3839  }
3840 #endif
3841 
3842  if (line_reader.size() > CPPHTTPLIB_HEADER_MAX_LENGTH) { return false; }
3843 
3844  // Exclude line terminator
3845  auto end = line_reader.ptr() + line_reader.size() - line_terminator_len;
3846 
3847  parse_header(line_reader.ptr(), end,
3848  [&](std::string &&key, std::string &&val) {
3849  headers.emplace(std::move(key), std::move(val));
3850  });
3851  }
3852 
3853  return true;
3854 }
3855 
3856 inline bool read_content_with_length(Stream &strm, uint64_t len,
3857  Progress progress,
3858  ContentReceiverWithProgress out) {
3859  char buf[CPPHTTPLIB_RECV_BUFSIZ];
3860 
3861  uint64_t r = 0;
3862  while (r < len) {
3863  auto read_len = static_cast<size_t>(len - r);
3864  auto n = strm.read(buf, (std::min)(read_len, CPPHTTPLIB_RECV_BUFSIZ));
3865  if (n <= 0) { return false; }
3866 
3867  if (!out(buf, static_cast<size_t>(n), r, len)) { return false; }
3868  r += static_cast<uint64_t>(n);
3869 
3870  if (progress) {
3871  if (!progress(r, len)) { return false; }
3872  }
3873  }
3874 
3875  return true;
3876 }
3877 
3878 inline void skip_content_with_length(Stream &strm, uint64_t len) {
3879  char buf[CPPHTTPLIB_RECV_BUFSIZ];
3880  uint64_t r = 0;
3881  while (r < len) {
3882  auto read_len = static_cast<size_t>(len - r);
3883  auto n = strm.read(buf, (std::min)(read_len, CPPHTTPLIB_RECV_BUFSIZ));
3884  if (n <= 0) { return; }
3885  r += static_cast<uint64_t>(n);
3886  }
3887 }
3888 
3889 inline bool read_content_without_length(Stream &strm,
3890  ContentReceiverWithProgress out) {
3891  char buf[CPPHTTPLIB_RECV_BUFSIZ];
3892  uint64_t r = 0;
3893  for (;;) {
3894  auto n = strm.read(buf, CPPHTTPLIB_RECV_BUFSIZ);
3895  if (n <= 0) { return true; }
3896 
3897  if (!out(buf, static_cast<size_t>(n), r, 0)) { return false; }
3898  r += static_cast<uint64_t>(n);
3899  }
3900 
3901  return true;
3902 }

3904 template <typename T>
3905 inline bool read_content_chunked(Stream &strm, T &x,
3906  ContentReceiverWithProgress out) {
3907  const auto bufsiz = 16;
3908  char buf[bufsiz];
3909 
3910  stream_line_reader line_reader(strm, buf, bufsiz);
3911 
3912  if (!line_reader.getline()) { return false; }
3913 
3914  unsigned long chunk_len;
3915  while (true) {
3916  char *end_ptr;
3917 
3918  chunk_len = std::strtoul(line_reader.ptr(), &end_ptr, 16);
3919 
3920  if (end_ptr == line_reader.ptr()) { return false; }
3921  if (chunk_len == ULONG_MAX) { return false; }
3922 
3923  if (chunk_len == 0) { break; }
3924 
3925  if (!read_content_with_length(strm, chunk_len, nullptr, out)) {
3926  return false;
3927  }
3928 
3929  if (!line_reader.getline()) { return false; }
3930 
3931  if (strcmp(line_reader.ptr(), "\r\n") != 0) { return false; }
3932 
3933  if (!line_reader.getline()) { return false; }
3934  }
3935 
3936  assert(chunk_len == 0);
3937 
3938  // Trailer
3939  if (!line_reader.getline()) { return false; }
3940 
3941  while (strcmp(line_reader.ptr(), "\r\n") != 0) {
3942  if (line_reader.size() > CPPHTTPLIB_HEADER_MAX_LENGTH) { return false; }
3943 
3944  // Exclude line terminator
3945  constexpr auto line_terminator_len = 2;
3946  auto end = line_reader.ptr() + line_reader.size() - line_terminator_len;
3947 
3948  parse_header(line_reader.ptr(), end,
3949  [&](std::string &&key, std::string &&val) {
3950  x.headers.emplace(std::move(key), std::move(val));
3951  });
3952 
3953  if (!line_reader.getline()) { return false; }
3954  }
3955 
3956  return true;
3957 }

3959 inline bool is_chunked_transfer_encoding(const Headers &headers) {
3960  return compare_case_ignore(
3961  get_header_value(headers, "Transfer-Encoding", 0, ""), "chunked");
3962 }

3964 template <typename T, typename U>
3965 bool prepare_content_receiver(T &x, int &status,
3966  ContentReceiverWithProgress receiver,
3967  bool decompress, U callback) {
3968  if (decompress) {
3969  std::string encoding = x.get_header_value("Content-Encoding");
3970  std::unique_ptr<decompressor> decompressor;
3971 
3972  if (encoding == "gzip" || encoding == "deflate") {
3973 #ifdef CPPHTTPLIB_ZLIB_SUPPORT
3974  decompressor = detail::make_unique<gzip_decompressor>();
3975 #else
3976  status = StatusCode::UnsupportedMediaType_415;
3977  return false;
3978 #endif
3979  } else if (encoding.find("br") != std::string::npos) {
3980 #ifdef CPPHTTPLIB_BROTLI_SUPPORT
3981  decompressor = detail::make_unique<brotli_decompressor>();
3982 #else
3983  status = StatusCode::UnsupportedMediaType_415;
3984  return false;
3985 #endif
3986  }
3987 
3988  if (decompressor) {
3989  if (decompressor->is_valid()) {
3990  ContentReceiverWithProgress out = [&](const char *buf, size_t n,
3991  uint64_t off, uint64_t len) {
3992  return decompressor->decompress(buf, n,
3993  [&](const char *buf2, size_t n2) {
3994  return receiver(buf2, n2, off, len);
3995  });
3996  };
3997  return callback(std::move(out));
3998  } else {
3999  status = StatusCode::InternalServerError_500;
4000  return false;
4001  }
4002  }
4003  }
4004 
4005  ContentReceiverWithProgress out = [&](const char *buf, size_t n, uint64_t off,
4006  uint64_t len) {
4007  return receiver(buf, n, off, len);
4008  };
4009  return callback(std::move(out));
4010 }

4012 template <typename T>
4013 bool read_content(Stream &strm, T &x, size_t payload_max_length, int &status,
4014  Progress progress, ContentReceiverWithProgress receiver,
4015  bool decompress) {
4016  return prepare_content_receiver(
4017  x, status, std::move(receiver), decompress,
4018  [&](const ContentReceiverWithProgress &out) {
4019  auto ret = true;
4020  auto exceed_payload_max_length = false;
4021 
4022  if (is_chunked_transfer_encoding(x.headers)) {
4023  ret = read_content_chunked(strm, x, out);
4024  } else if (!has_header(x.headers, "Content-Length")) {
4025  ret = read_content_without_length(strm, out);
4026  } else {
4027  auto len = get_header_value_u64(x.headers, "Content-Length", 0, 0);
4028  if (len > payload_max_length) {
4029  exceed_payload_max_length = true;
4030  skip_content_with_length(strm, len);
4031  ret = false;
4032  } else if (len > 0) {
4033  ret = read_content_with_length(strm, len, std::move(progress), out);
4034  }
4035  }
4036 
4037  if (!ret) {
4038  status = exceed_payload_max_length ? StatusCode::PayloadTooLarge_413
4039  : StatusCode::BadRequest_400;
4040  }
4041  return ret;
4042  });
4043 } // namespace detail

4045 inline ssize_t write_headers(Stream &strm, const Headers &headers) {
4046  ssize_t write_len = 0;
4047  for (const auto &x : headers) {
4048  auto len =
4049  strm.write_format("%s: %s\r\n", x.first.c_str(), x.second.c_str());
4050  if (len < 0) { return len; }
4051  write_len += len;
4052  }
4053  auto len = strm.write("\r\n");
4054  if (len < 0) { return len; }
4055  write_len += len;
4056  return write_len;
4057 }

4059 inline bool write_data(Stream &strm, const char *d, size_t l) {
4060  size_t offset = 0;
4061  while (offset < l) {
4062  auto length = strm.write(d + offset, l - offset);
4063  if (length < 0) { return false; }
4064  offset += static_cast<size_t>(length);
4065  }
4066  return true;
4067 }

4069 template <typename T>
4070 inline bool write_content(Stream &strm, const ContentProvider &content_provider,
4071  size_t offset, size_t length, T is_shutting_down,
4072  Error &error) {
4073  size_t end_offset = offset + length;
4074  auto ok = true;
4075  DataSink data_sink;
4076 
4077  data_sink.write = [&](const char *d, size_t l) -> bool {
4078  if (ok) {
4079  if (strm.is_writable() && write_data(strm, d, l)) {
4080  offset += l;
4081  } else {
4082  ok = false;
4083  }
4084  }
4085  return ok;
4086  };
4087 
4088  data_sink.is_writable = [&]() -> bool { return strm.is_writable(); };
4089 
4090  while (offset < end_offset && !is_shutting_down()) {
4091  if (!strm.is_writable()) {
4092  error = Error::Write;
4093  return false;
4094  } else if (!content_provider(offset, end_offset - offset, data_sink)) {
4095  error = Error::Canceled;
4096  return false;
4097  } else if (!ok) {
4098  error = Error::Write;
4099  return false;
4100  }
4101  }
4102 
4103  error = Error::Success;
4104  return true;
4105 }

4111  auto error = Error::Success;
4112  return write_content(strm, content_provider, offset, length, is_shutting_down,
4113  error);

4116 template <typename T>
4117 inline bool
4118 write_content_without_length(Stream &strm,
4119  const ContentProvider &content_provider,
4120  const T &is_shutting_down) {
4121  size_t offset = 0;
4122  auto data_available = true;
4123  auto ok = true;
4124  DataSink data_sink;
4125 
4126  data_sink.write = [&](const char *d, size_t l) -> bool {
4127  if (ok) {
4128  offset += l;
4129  if (!strm.is_writable() || !write_data(strm, d, l)) { ok = false; }
4130  }
4131  return ok;
4132  };
4133 
4134  data_sink.is_writable = [&]() -> bool { return strm.is_writable(); };
4135 
4136  data_sink.done = [&](void) { data_available = false; };
4137 
4138  while (data_available && !is_shutting_down()) {
4139  if (!strm.is_writable()) {
4140  return false;
4141  } else if (!content_provider(offset, 0, data_sink)) {
4142  return false;
4143  } else if (!ok) {
4144  return false;
4145  }
4146  }
4147  return true;
4148 }

4150 template <typename T, typename U>
4151 inline bool
4152 write_content_chunked(Stream &strm, const ContentProvider &content_provider,
4153  const T &is_shutting_down, U &compressor, Error &error) {
4154  size_t offset = 0;
4155  auto data_available = true;
4156  auto ok = true;
4157  DataSink data_sink;
4158 
4159  data_sink.write = [&](const char *d, size_t l) -> bool {
4160  if (ok) {
4161  data_available = l > 0;
4162  offset += l;
4163 
4164  std::string payload;
4165  if (compressor.compress(d, l, false,
4166  [&](const char *data, size_t data_len) {
4167  payload.append(data, data_len);
4168  return true;
4169  })) {
4170  if (!payload.empty()) {
4171  // Emit chunked response header and footer for each chunk
4172  auto chunk =
4173  from_i_to_hex(payload.size()) + "\r\n" + payload + "\r\n";
4174  if (!strm.is_writable() ||
4175  !write_data(strm, chunk.data(), chunk.size())) {
4176  ok = false;
4177  }
4178  }
4179  } else {
4180  ok = false;
4181  }
4182  }
4183  return ok;
4184  };
4185 
4186  data_sink.is_writable = [&]() -> bool { return strm.is_writable(); };
4187 
4188  auto done_with_trailer = [&](const Headers *trailer) {
4189  if (!ok) { return; }
4190 
4191  data_available = false;
4192 
4193  std::string payload;
4194  if (!compressor.compress(nullptr, 0, true,
4195  [&](const char *data, size_t data_len) {
4196  payload.append(data, data_len);
4197  return true;
4198  })) {
4199  ok = false;
4200  return;
4201  }
4202 
4203  if (!payload.empty()) {
4204  // Emit chunked response header and footer for each chunk
4205  auto chunk = from_i_to_hex(payload.size()) + "\r\n" + payload + "\r\n";
4206  if (!strm.is_writable() ||
4207  !write_data(strm, chunk.data(), chunk.size())) {
4208  ok = false;
4209  return;
4210  }
4211  }
4212 
4213  static const std::string done_marker("0\r\n");
4214  if (!write_data(strm, done_marker.data(), done_marker.size())) {
4215  ok = false;
4216  }
4217 
4218  // Trailer
4219  if (trailer) {
4220  for (const auto &kv : *trailer) {
4221  std::string field_line = kv.first + ": " + kv.second + "\r\n";
4222  if (!write_data(strm, field_line.data(), field_line.size())) {
4223  ok = false;
4224  }
4225  }
4226  }
4227 
4228  static const std::string crlf("\r\n");
4229  if (!write_data(strm, crlf.data(), crlf.size())) { ok = false; }
4230  };
4231 
4232  data_sink.done = [&](void) { done_with_trailer(nullptr); };
4233 
4234  data_sink.done_with_trailer = [&](const Headers &trailer) {
4235  done_with_trailer(&trailer);
4236  };
4237 
4238  while (data_available && !is_shutting_down()) {
4239  if (!strm.is_writable()) {
4240  error = Error::Write;
4241  return false;
4242  } else if (!content_provider(offset, 0, data_sink)) {
4243  error = Error::Canceled;
4244  return false;
4245  } else if (!ok) {
4246  error = Error::Write;
4247  return false;
4248  }
4249  }
4250 
4251  error = Error::Success;
4252  return true;
4253 }
4254 
4255 template <typename T, typename U>
4256 inline bool write_content_chunked(Stream &strm,
4257  const ContentProvider &content_provider,
4258  const T &is_shutting_down, U &compressor) {
4259  auto error = Error::Success;
4260  return write_content_chunked(strm, content_provider, is_shutting_down,
4261  compressor, error);
4262 }

4264 template <typename T>
4265 inline bool redirect(T &cli, Request &req, Response &res,
4266  const std::string &path, const std::string &location,
4267  Error &error) {
4268  Request new_req = req;
4269  new_req.path = path;
4270  new_req.redirect_count_ -= 1;
4271 
4272  if (res.status == StatusCode::SeeOther_303 &&
4273  (req.method != "GET" && req.method != "HEAD")) {
4274  new_req.method = "GET";
4275  new_req.body.clear();
4276  new_req.headers.clear();
4277  }
4278 
4279  Response new_res;
4280 
4281  auto ret = cli.send(new_req, new_res, error);
4282  if (ret) {
4283  req = new_req;
4284  res = new_res;
4285 
4286  if (res.location.empty()) { res.location = location; }
4287  }
4288  return ret;
4289 }

4291 inline std::string params_to_query_str(const Params &params) {
4292  std::string query;
4293 
4294  for (auto it = params.begin(); it != params.end(); ++it) {
4295  if (it != params.begin()) { query += "&"; }
4296  query += it->first;
4297  query += "=";
4298  query += encode_query_param(it->second);
4299  }

4303 inline void parse_query_text(const std::string &s, Params &params) {
4304  std::set<std::string> cache;
4305  split(s.data(), s.data() + s.size(), '&', [&](const char *b, const char *e) {
4306  std::string kv(b, e);
4307  if (cache.find(kv) != cache.end()) { return; }
4308  cache.insert(kv);
4309 
4310  std::string key;
4311  std::string val;
4312  split(b, e, '=', [&](const char *b2, const char *e2) {
4313  if (key.empty()) {
4314  key.assign(b2, e2);
4315  } else {
4316  val.assign(b2, e2);
4317  }
4318  });
4319 
4320  if (!key.empty()) {
4321  params.emplace(decode_url(key, true), decode_url(val, true));
4322  }
4323  });
4324 }

4326 inline bool parse_multipart_boundary(const std::string &content_type,
4327  std::string &boundary) {
4328  auto boundary_keyword = "boundary=";
4329  auto pos = content_type.find(boundary_keyword);
4330  if (pos == std::string::npos) { return false; }
4331  auto end = content_type.find(';', pos);
4332  auto beg = pos + strlen(boundary_keyword);
4333  boundary = trim_double_quotes_copy(content_type.substr(beg, end - beg));
4334  return !boundary.empty();
4335 }

4361 #ifdef CPPHTTPLIB_NO_EXCEPTIONS
4362 inline bool parse_range_header(const std::string &s, Ranges &ranges) {
4363 #else
4364 inline bool parse_range_header(const std::string &s, Ranges &ranges) try {
4365 #endif
4366  static auto re_first_range = std::regex(R"(bytes=(\d*-\d*(?:,\s*\d*-\d*)*))");
4367  std::smatch m;
4368  if (std::regex_match(s, m, re_first_range)) {
4369  auto pos = static_cast<size_t>(m.position(1));
4370  auto len = static_cast<size_t>(m.length(1));
4371  auto all_valid_ranges = true;
4372  split(&s[pos], &s[pos + len], ',', [&](const char *b, const char *e) {
4373  if (!all_valid_ranges) { return; }
4374  static auto re_another_range = std::regex(R"(\s*(\d*)-(\d*))");
4375  std::cmatch cm;
4376  if (std::regex_match(b, e, cm, re_another_range)) {
4377  ssize_t first = -1;
4378  if (!cm.str(1).empty()) {
4379  first = static_cast<ssize_t>(std::stoll(cm.str(1)));
4380  }
4381 
4382  ssize_t last = -1;
4383  if (!cm.str(2).empty()) {
4384  last = static_cast<ssize_t>(std::stoll(cm.str(2)));
4385  }
4386 
4387  if (first != -1 && last != -1 && first > last) {
4388  all_valid_ranges = false;
4389  return;
4390  }
4391  ranges.emplace_back(std::make_pair(first, last));
4392  }
4393  });
4394  return all_valid_ranges;
4395  }
4396  return false;
4397 #ifdef CPPHTTPLIB_NO_EXCEPTIONS
4398 }
4399 #else
4400 } catch (...) { return false; }
4401 #endif
4402 
4403 class MultipartFormDataParser {
4404 public:
4405  MultipartFormDataParser() = default;
4406 
4407  void set_boundary(std::string &&boundary) {
4408  boundary_ = boundary;
4409  dash_boundary_crlf_ = dash_ + boundary_ + crlf_;
4410  crlf_dash_boundary_ = crlf_ + dash_ + boundary_;
4411  }
4412 
4413  bool is_valid() const { return is_valid_; }
4414 
4415  bool parse(const char *buf, size_t n, const ContentReceiver &content_callback,
4416  const MultipartContentHeader &header_callback) {
4417 
4418  buf_append(buf, n);
4419 
4420  while (buf_size() > 0) {
4421  switch (state_) {
4422  case 0: { // Initial boundary
4423  buf_erase(buf_find(dash_boundary_crlf_));
4424  if (dash_boundary_crlf_.size() > buf_size()) { return true; }
4425  if (!buf_start_with(dash_boundary_crlf_)) { return false; }
4426  buf_erase(dash_boundary_crlf_.size());
4427  state_ = 1;
4428  break;
4429  }
4430  case 1: { // New entry
4431  clear_file_info();
4432  state_ = 2;
4433  break;
4434  }
4435  case 2: { // Headers
4436  auto pos = buf_find(crlf_);
4437  if (pos > CPPHTTPLIB_HEADER_MAX_LENGTH) { return false; }
4438  while (pos < buf_size()) {
4439  // Empty line
4440  if (pos == 0) {
4441  if (!header_callback(file_)) {
4442  is_valid_ = false;
4443  return false;
4444  }
4445  buf_erase(crlf_.size());
4446  state_ = 3;
4447  break;
4448  }
4449 
4450  const auto header = buf_head(pos);
4451 
4452  if (!parse_header(header.data(), header.data() + header.size(),
4453  [&](std::string &&, std::string &&) {})) {
4454  is_valid_ = false;
4455  return false;
4456  }
4457 
4458  static const std::string header_content_type = "Content-Type:";
4459 
4460  if (start_with_case_ignore(header, header_content_type)) {
4461  file_.content_type =
4462  trim_copy(header.substr(header_content_type.size()));
4463  } else {
4464  static const std::regex re_content_disposition(
4465  R"~(^Content-Disposition:\s*form-data;\s*(.*)$)~",
4466  std::regex_constants::icase);
4467 
4468  std::smatch m;
4469  if (std::regex_match(header, m, re_content_disposition)) {
4470  Params params;
4471  parse_disposition_params(m[1], params);
4472 
4473  auto it = params.find("name");
4474  if (it != params.end()) {
4475  file_.name = it->second;
4476  } else {
4477  is_valid_ = false;
4478  return false;
4479  }
4480 
4481  it = params.find("filename");
4482  if (it != params.end()) { file_.filename = it->second; }
4483 
4484  it = params.find("filename*");
4485  if (it != params.end()) {
4486  // Only allow UTF-8 enconnding...
4487  static const std::regex re_rfc5987_encoding(
4488  R"~(^UTF-8''(.+?)$)~", std::regex_constants::icase);
4489 
4490  std::smatch m2;
4491  if (std::regex_match(it->second, m2, re_rfc5987_encoding)) {
4492  file_.filename = decode_url(m2[1], false); // override...
4493  } else {
4494  is_valid_ = false;
4495  return false;
4496  }
4497  }
4498  }
4499  }
4500  buf_erase(pos + crlf_.size());
4501  pos = buf_find(crlf_);
4502  }
4503  if (state_ != 3) { return true; }
4504  break;
4505  }
4506  case 3: { // Body
4507  if (crlf_dash_boundary_.size() > buf_size()) { return true; }
4508  auto pos = buf_find(crlf_dash_boundary_);
4509  if (pos < buf_size()) {
4510  if (!content_callback(buf_data(), pos)) {
4511  is_valid_ = false;
4512  return false;
4513  }
4514  buf_erase(pos + crlf_dash_boundary_.size());
4515  state_ = 4;
4516  } else {
4517  auto len = buf_size() - crlf_dash_boundary_.size();
4518  if (len > 0) {
4519  if (!content_callback(buf_data(), len)) {
4520  is_valid_ = false;
4521  return false;
4522  }
4523  buf_erase(len);
4524  }
4525  return true;
4526  }
4527  break;
4528  }
4529  case 4: { // Boundary
4530  if (crlf_.size() > buf_size()) { return true; }
4531  if (buf_start_with(crlf_)) {
4532  buf_erase(crlf_.size());
4533  state_ = 1;
4534  } else {
4535  if (dash_.size() > buf_size()) { return true; }
4536  if (buf_start_with(dash_)) {
4537  buf_erase(dash_.size());
4538  is_valid_ = true;
4539  buf_erase(buf_size()); // Remove epilogue
4540  } else {
4541  return true;
4542  }
4543  }
4544  break;
4545  }
4546  }
4547  }
4548 
4549  return true;
4550  }
4551 
4552 private:
4553  void clear_file_info() {
4554  file_.name.clear();
4555  file_.filename.clear();
4556  file_.content_type.clear();
4557  }
4558 
4559  bool start_with_case_ignore(const std::string &a,
4560  const std::string &b) const {
4561  if (a.size() < b.size()) { return false; }
4562  for (size_t i = 0; i < b.size(); i++) {
4563  if (::tolower(a[i]) != ::tolower(b[i])) { return false; }
4564  }
4565  return true;
4566  }
4567 
4568  const std::string dash_ = "--";
4569  const std::string crlf_ = "\r\n";
4570  std::string boundary_;
4571  std::string dash_boundary_crlf_;
4572  std::string crlf_dash_boundary_;
4573 
4574  size_t state_ = 0;
4575  bool is_valid_ = false;
4576  MultipartFormData file_;
4577 
4578  // Buffer
4579  bool start_with(const std::string &a, size_t spos, size_t epos,
4580  const std::string &b) const {
4581  if (epos - spos < b.size()) { return false; }
4582  for (size_t i = 0; i < b.size(); i++) {
4583  if (a[i + spos] != b[i]) { return false; }
4584  }
4585  return true;
4586  }
4587 
4588  size_t buf_size() const { return buf_epos_ - buf_spos_; }
4589 
4590  const char *buf_data() const { return &buf_[buf_spos_]; }
4591 
4592  std::string buf_head(size_t l) const { return buf_.substr(buf_spos_, l); }
4593 
4594  bool buf_start_with(const std::string &s) const {
4595  return start_with(buf_, buf_spos_, buf_epos_, s);
4596  }
4597 
4598  size_t buf_find(const std::string &s) const {
4599  auto c = s.front();
4600 
4601  size_t off = buf_spos_;
4602  while (off < buf_epos_) {
4603  auto pos = off;
4604  while (true) {
4605  if (pos == buf_epos_) { return buf_size(); }
4606  if (buf_[pos] == c) { break; }
4607  pos++;
4608  }
4609 
4610  auto remaining_size = buf_epos_ - pos;
4611  if (s.size() > remaining_size) { return buf_size(); }
4612 
4613  if (start_with(buf_, pos, buf_epos_, s)) { return pos - buf_spos_; }
4614 
4615  off = pos + 1;
4616  }
4617 
4618  return buf_size();
4619  }
4620 
4621  void buf_append(const char *data, size_t n) {
4622  auto remaining_size = buf_size();
4623  if (remaining_size > 0 && buf_spos_ > 0) {
4624  for (size_t i = 0; i < remaining_size; i++) {
4625  buf_[i] = buf_[buf_spos_ + i];
4626  }
4627  }
4628  buf_spos_ = 0;
4629  buf_epos_ = remaining_size;
4630 
4631  if (remaining_size + n > buf_.size()) { buf_.resize(remaining_size + n); }
4632 
4633  for (size_t i = 0; i < n; i++) {
4634  buf_[buf_epos_ + i] = data[i];
4635  }
4636  buf_epos_ += n;
4637  }
4638 
4639  void buf_erase(size_t size) { buf_spos_ += size; }
4640 
4641  std::string buf_;
4642  size_t buf_spos_ = 0;
4643  size_t buf_epos_ = 0;
4644 };
4645 
4646 inline std::string to_lower(const char *beg, const char *end) {
4647  std::string out;
4648  auto it = beg;
4649  while (it != end) {
4650  out += static_cast<char>(::tolower(*it));
4651  it++;
4652  }
4653  return out;
4654 }

4656 inline std::string random_string(size_t length) {
4657  static const char data[] =
4658  "0123456789ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZabcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz";
4659 
4660  // std::random_device might actually be deterministic on some
4661  // platforms, but due to lack of support in the c++ standard library,
4662  // doing better requires either some ugly hacks or breaking portability.
4663  static std::random_device seed_gen;
4664 
4665  // Request 128 bits of entropy for initialization
4666  static std::seed_seq seed_sequence{seed_gen(), seed_gen(), seed_gen(),
4667  seed_gen()};
4668 
4669  static std::mt19937 engine(seed_sequence);
4670 
4671  std::string result;
4672  for (size_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
4673  result += data[engine() % (sizeof(data) - 1)];
4674  }
4675  return result;
4676 }

4682 inline bool is_multipart_boundary_chars_valid(const std::string &boundary) {
4683  auto valid = true;
4684  for (size_t i = 0; i < boundary.size(); i++) {
4685  auto c = boundary[i];
4686  if (!std::isalnum(c) && c != '-' && c != '_') {
4687  valid = false;
4688  break;
4689  }
4690  }
4691  return valid;
4692 }

4694 template <typename T>

4697  const std::string &boundary) {

4699  body += "Content-Disposition: form-data; name=\"" + item.name + "\"";
4700  if (!item.filename.empty()) {
4701  body += "; filename=\"" + item.filename + "\"";
4702  }
4703  body += "\r\n";
4704  if (!item.content_type.empty()) {
4705  body += "Content-Type: " + item.content_type + "\r\n";
4706  }
4707  body += "\r\n";
4708 
4709  return body;
4710 }

4724 inline std::string
4725 serialize_multipart_formdata(const MultipartFormDataItems &items,
4726  const std::string &boundary, bool finish = true) {
4727  std::string body;
4728 
4729  for (const auto &item : items) {
4730  body += serialize_multipart_formdata_item_begin(item, boundary);
4731  body += item.content + serialize_multipart_formdata_item_end();
4732  }
4733 
4734  if (finish) { body += serialize_multipart_formdata_finish(boundary); }
4735 
4736  return body;
4737 }

4739 inline bool range_error(Request &req, Response &res) {
4740  if (!req.ranges.empty() && 200 <= res.status && res.status < 300) {
4741  ssize_t contant_len = static_cast<ssize_t>(
4742  res.content_length_ ? res.content_length_ : res.body.size());
4743 
4744  ssize_t prev_first_pos = -1;
4745  ssize_t prev_last_pos = -1;
4746  size_t overwrapping_count = 0;
4747 
4748  // NOTE: The following Range check is based on '14.2. Range' in RFC 9110
4749  // 'HTTP Semantics' to avoid potential denial-of-service attacks.
4750  // https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc9110#section-14.2
4751 
4752  // Too many ranges
4753  if (req.ranges.size() > CPPHTTPLIB_RANGE_MAX_COUNT) { return true; }
4754 
4755  for (auto &r : req.ranges) {
4756  auto &first_pos = r.first;
4757  auto &last_pos = r.second;
4758 
4759  if (first_pos == -1 && last_pos == -1) {
4760  first_pos = 0;
4761  last_pos = contant_len;
4762  }
4763 
4764  if (first_pos == -1) {
4765  first_pos = contant_len - last_pos;
4766  last_pos = contant_len - 1;
4767  }
4768 
4769  if (last_pos == -1) { last_pos = contant_len - 1; }
4770 
4771  // Range must be within content length
4772  if (!(0 <= first_pos && first_pos <= last_pos &&
4773  last_pos <= contant_len - 1)) {
4774  return true;
4775  }
4776 
4777  // Ranges must be in ascending order
4778  if (first_pos <= prev_first_pos) { return true; }
4779 
4780  // Request must not have more than two overlapping ranges
4781  if (first_pos <= prev_last_pos) {
4782  overwrapping_count++;
4783  if (overwrapping_count > 2) { return true; }
4784  }
4785 
4786  prev_first_pos = (std::max)(prev_first_pos, first_pos);
4787  prev_last_pos = (std::max)(prev_last_pos, last_pos);
4788  }
4789  }
4790 
4791  return false;
4792 }
4793 
4794 inline std::pair<size_t, size_t>
4795 get_range_offset_and_length(Range r, size_t content_length) {
4796  assert(r.first != -1 && r.second != -1);
4797  assert(0 <= r.first && r.first < static_cast<ssize_t>(content_length));
4798  assert(r.first <= r.second &&
4799  r.second < static_cast<ssize_t>(content_length));
4800 
4801  return std::make_pair(r.first, static_cast<size_t>(r.second - r.first) + 1);
4802 }
4803 
4804 inline std::string make_content_range_header_field(
4805  const std::pair<size_t, size_t> &offset_and_length, size_t content_length) {
4806  auto st = offset_and_length.first;
4807  auto ed = st + offset_and_length.second - 1;
4808 
4809  std::string field = "bytes ";
4810  field += std::to_string(st);
4811  field += "-";
4812  field += std::to_string(ed);
4813  field += "/";
4814  field += std::to_string(content_length);
4815  return field;
4816 }
