4818 template <typename SToken, typename CToken, typename Content>
4819 bool process_multipart_ranges_data(const Request &req,
4820  const std::string &boundary,
4821  const std::string &content_type,
4822  size_t content_length, SToken stoken,
4823  CToken ctoken, Content content) {
4824  for (size_t i = 0; i < req.ranges.size(); i++) {
4825  ctoken("--");
4826  stoken(boundary);
4827  ctoken("\r\n");
4828  if (!content_type.empty()) {
4829  ctoken("Content-Type: ");
4830  stoken(content_type);
4831  ctoken("\r\n");
4832  }
4833 
4834  auto offset_and_length =
4835  get_range_offset_and_length(req.ranges[i], content_length);
4836 
4837  ctoken("Content-Range: ");
4838  stoken(make_content_range_header_field(offset_and_length, content_length));
4839  ctoken("\r\n");
4840  ctoken("\r\n");
4841 
4842  if (!content(offset_and_length.first, offset_and_length.second)) {
4843  return false;
4844  }
4845  ctoken("\r\n");
4846  }
4847 
4848  ctoken("--");
4849  stoken(boundary);
4850  ctoken("--");
4851 
4852  return true;
4853 }
4854 
4855 inline void make_multipart_ranges_data(const Request &req, Response &res,
4856  const std::string &boundary,
4857  const std::string &content_type,
4858  size_t content_length,
4859  std::string &data) {
4860  process_multipart_ranges_data(
4861  req, boundary, content_type, content_length,
4862  [&](const std::string &token) { data += token; },
4863  [&](const std::string &token) { data += token; },
4864  [&](size_t offset, size_t length) {
4865  assert(offset + length <= content_length);
4866  data += res.body.substr(offset, length);
4867  return true;
4868  });
4869 }
4870 
4871 inline size_t get_multipart_ranges_data_length(const Request &req,
4872  const std::string &boundary,
4873  const std::string &content_type,
4874  size_t content_length) {
4875  size_t data_length = 0;
4876 
4877  process_multipart_ranges_data(
4878  req, boundary, content_type, content_length,
4879  [&](const std::string &token) { data_length += token.size(); },
4880  [&](const std::string &token) { data_length += token.size(); },
4881  [&](size_t /*offset*/, size_t length) {
4882  data_length += length;
4883  return true;
4884  });
4885 
4886  return data_length;
4887 }

4889 template <typename T>

4923 #ifdef CPPHTTPLIB_OPENSSL_SUPPORT
4924 inline std::string message_digest(const std::string &s, const EVP_MD *algo) {
4925  auto context = std::unique_ptr<EVP_MD_CTX, decltype(&EVP_MD_CTX_free)>(
4926  EVP_MD_CTX_new(), EVP_MD_CTX_free);
4927 
4928  unsigned int hash_length = 0;
4929  unsigned char hash[EVP_MAX_MD_SIZE];
4930 
4931  EVP_DigestInit_ex(context.get(), algo, nullptr);
4932  EVP_DigestUpdate(context.get(), s.c_str(), s.size());
4933  EVP_DigestFinal_ex(context.get(), hash, &hash_length);
4934 
4935  std::stringstream ss;
4936  for (auto i = 0u; i < hash_length; ++i) {
4937  ss << std::hex << std::setw(2) << std::setfill('0')
4938  << static_cast<unsigned int>(hash[i]);
4939  }
4940 
4941  return ss.str();
4942 }

4958 #ifdef _WIN32
4959 // NOTE: This code came up with the following stackoverflow post:
4960 // https://stackoverflow.com/questions/9507184/can-openssl-on-windows-use-the-system-certificate-store
4961 inline bool load_system_certs_on_windows(X509_STORE *store) {
4962  auto hStore = CertOpenSystemStoreW((HCRYPTPROV_LEGACY)NULL, L"ROOT");
4963  if (!hStore) { return false; }
4964 
4965  auto result = false;
4966  PCCERT_CONTEXT pContext = NULL;
4967  while ((pContext = CertEnumCertificatesInStore(hStore, pContext)) !=
4968  nullptr) {
4969  auto encoded_cert =
4970  static_cast<const unsigned char *>(pContext->pbCertEncoded);
4971 
4972  auto x509 = d2i_X509(NULL, &encoded_cert, pContext->cbCertEncoded);
4973  if (x509) {
4974  X509_STORE_add_cert(store, x509);
4975  X509_free(x509);
4976  result = true;
4977  }
4978  }
4979 
4980  CertFreeCertificateContext(pContext);
4981  CertCloseStore(hStore, 0);
4982 
4983  return result;
4984 }

4986 #if TARGET_OS_OSX

4995 inline bool retrieve_certs_from_keychain(CFObjectPtr<CFArrayRef> &certs) {
4996  CFStringRef keys[] = {kSecClass, kSecMatchLimit, kSecReturnRef};
4997  CFTypeRef values[] = {kSecClassCertificate, kSecMatchLimitAll,
4998  kCFBooleanTrue};
4999 
5000  CFObjectPtr<CFDictionaryRef> query(
5001  CFDictionaryCreate(nullptr, reinterpret_cast<const void **>(keys), values,
5002  sizeof(keys) / sizeof(keys[0]),
5003  &kCFTypeDictionaryKeyCallBacks,
5004  &kCFTypeDictionaryValueCallBacks),
5005  cf_object_ptr_deleter);
5006 
5007  if (!query) { return false; }
5008 
5009  CFTypeRef security_items = nullptr;
5010  if (SecItemCopyMatching(query.get(), &security_items) != errSecSuccess ||
5011  CFArrayGetTypeID() != CFGetTypeID(security_items)) {
5012  return false;
5013  }
5014 
5015  certs.reset(reinterpret_cast<CFArrayRef>(security_items));
5016  return true;
5017 }
5018 
5019 inline bool retrieve_root_certs_from_keychain(CFObjectPtr<CFArrayRef> &certs) {
5020  CFArrayRef root_security_items = nullptr;
5021  if (SecTrustCopyAnchorCertificates(&root_security_items) != errSecSuccess) {
5022  return false;
5023  }
5024 
5025  certs.reset(root_security_items);
5026  return true;
5027 }
5028 
5029 inline bool add_certs_to_x509_store(CFArrayRef certs, X509_STORE *store) {
5030  auto result = false;
5031  for (auto i = 0; i < CFArrayGetCount(certs); ++i) {
5032  const auto cert = reinterpret_cast<const __SecCertificate *>(
5033  CFArrayGetValueAtIndex(certs, i));
5034 
5035  if (SecCertificateGetTypeID() != CFGetTypeID(cert)) { continue; }
5036 
5037  CFDataRef cert_data = nullptr;
5038  if (SecItemExport(cert, kSecFormatX509Cert, 0, nullptr, &cert_data) !=
5039  errSecSuccess) {
5040  continue;
5041  }
5042 
5043  CFObjectPtr<CFDataRef> cert_data_ptr(cert_data, cf_object_ptr_deleter);
5044 
5045  auto encoded_cert = static_cast<const unsigned char *>(
5046  CFDataGetBytePtr(cert_data_ptr.get()));
5047 
5048  auto x509 =
5049  d2i_X509(NULL, &encoded_cert, CFDataGetLength(cert_data_ptr.get()));
5050 
5051  if (x509) {
5052  X509_STORE_add_cert(store, x509);
5053  X509_free(x509);
5054  result = true;
5055  }
5056  }
5057 
5058  return result;
5059 }
5060 
5061 inline bool load_system_certs_on_macos(X509_STORE *store) {
5062  auto result = false;
5063  CFObjectPtr<CFArrayRef> certs(nullptr, cf_object_ptr_deleter);
5064  if (retrieve_certs_from_keychain(certs) && certs) {
5065  result = add_certs_to_x509_store(certs.get(), store);
5066  }
5067 
5068  if (retrieve_root_certs_from_keychain(certs) && certs) {
5069  result = add_certs_to_x509_store(certs.get(), store) || result;
5070  }
5071 
5072  return result;
5073 }
5074 #endif // TARGET_OS_OSX
5075 #endif // _WIN32
5076 #endif // CPPHTTPLIB_OPENSSL_SUPPORT

5084  }

5096 #ifdef CPPHTTPLIB_OPENSSL_SUPPORT
5097 inline std::pair<std::string, std::string> make_digest_authentication_header(
5098  const Request &req, const std::map<std::string, std::string> &auth,
5099  size_t cnonce_count, const std::string &cnonce, const std::string &username,
5100  const std::string &password, bool is_proxy = false) {
5101  std::string nc;
5102  {
5103  std::stringstream ss;
5104  ss << std::setfill('0') << std::setw(8) << std::hex << cnonce_count;
5105  nc = ss.str();
5106  }
5107 
5108  std::string qop;
5109  if (auth.find("qop") != auth.end()) {
5110  qop = auth.at("qop");
5111  if (qop.find("auth-int") != std::string::npos) {
5112  qop = "auth-int";
5113  } else if (qop.find("auth") != std::string::npos) {
5114  qop = "auth";
5115  } else {
5116  qop.clear();
5117  }
5118  }
5119 
5120  std::string algo = "MD5";
5121  if (auth.find("algorithm") != auth.end()) { algo = auth.at("algorithm"); }
5122 
5123  std::string response;
5124  {
5125  auto H = algo == "SHA-256" ? detail::SHA_256
5126  : algo == "SHA-512" ? detail::SHA_512
5127  : detail::MD5;
5128 
5129  auto A1 = username + ":" + auth.at("realm") + ":" + password;
5130 
5131  auto A2 = req.method + ":" + req.path;
5132  if (qop == "auth-int") { A2 += ":" + H(req.body); }
5133 
5134  if (qop.empty()) {
5135  response = H(H(A1) + ":" + auth.at("nonce") + ":" + H(A2));
5136  } else {
5137  response = H(H(A1) + ":" + auth.at("nonce") + ":" + nc + ":" + cnonce +
5138  ":" + qop + ":" + H(A2));
5139  }
5140  }
5141 
5142  auto opaque = (auth.find("opaque") != auth.end()) ? auth.at("opaque") : "";
5143 
5144  auto field = "Digest username=\"" + username + "\", realm=\"" +
5145  auth.at("realm") + "\", nonce=\"" + auth.at("nonce") +
5146  "\", uri=\"" + req.path + "\", algorithm=" + algo +
5147  (qop.empty() ? ", response=\""
5148  : ", qop=" + qop + ", nc=" + nc + ", cnonce=\"" +
5149  cnonce + "\", response=\"") +
5150  response + "\"" +
5151  (opaque.empty() ? "" : ", opaque=\"" + opaque + "\"");
5152 
5153  auto key = is_proxy ? "Proxy-Authorization" : "Authorization";
5154  return std::make_pair(key, field);
5155 }
5156 #endif
5157 
5158 inline bool parse_www_authenticate(const Response &res,
5159  std::map<std::string, std::string> &auth,
5160  bool is_proxy) {
5161  auto auth_key = is_proxy ? "Proxy-Authenticate" : "WWW-Authenticate";
5162  if (res.has_header(auth_key)) {
5163  static auto re = std::regex(R"~((?:(?:,\s*)?(.+?)=(?:"(.*?)"|([^,]*))))~");
5164  auto s = res.get_header_value(auth_key);
5165  auto pos = s.find(' ');
5166  if (pos != std::string::npos) {
5167  auto type = s.substr(0, pos);
5168  if (type == "Basic") {
5169  return false;
5170  } else if (type == "Digest") {
5171  s = s.substr(pos + 1);
5172  auto beg = std::sregex_iterator(s.begin(), s.end(), re);
5173  for (auto i = beg; i != std::sregex_iterator(); ++i) {
5174  const auto &m = *i;
5175  auto key = s.substr(static_cast<size_t>(m.position(1)),
5176  static_cast<size_t>(m.length(1)));
5177  auto val = m.length(2) > 0
5178  ? s.substr(static_cast<size_t>(m.position(2)),
5179  static_cast<size_t>(m.length(2)))
5180  : s.substr(static_cast<size_t>(m.position(3)),
5181  static_cast<size_t>(m.length(3)));
5182  auth[key] = val;
5183  }
5184  return true;
5185  }
5186  }
5187  }
5188  return false;
5189 }
5190 
5191 class ContentProviderAdapter {
5192 public:
5193  explicit ContentProviderAdapter(
5194  ContentProviderWithoutLength &&content_provider)
5195  : content_provider_(content_provider) {}
5196 
5197  bool operator()(size_t offset, size_t, DataSink &sink) {
5198  return content_provider_(offset, sink);
5199  }
5200 
5201 private:
5202  ContentProviderWithoutLength content_provider_;
5203 };

5207 inline std::string hosted_at(const std::string &hostname) {
5208  std::vector<std::string> addrs;
5209  hosted_at(hostname, addrs);
5210  if (addrs.empty()) { return std::string(); }
5211  return addrs[0];
5212 }
5213 
5214 inline void hosted_at(const std::string &hostname,
5215  std::vector<std::string> &addrs) {
5216  struct addrinfo hints;
5217  struct addrinfo *result;
5218 
5219  memset(&hints, 0, sizeof(struct addrinfo));
5220  hints.ai_family = AF_UNSPEC;
5221  hints.ai_socktype = SOCK_STREAM;
5222  hints.ai_protocol = 0;
5223 
5224  if (getaddrinfo(hostname.c_str(), nullptr, &hints, &result)) {
5225 #if defined __linux__ && !defined __ANDROID__
5226  res_init();
5227 #endif
5228  return;
5229  }
5230 
5231  for (auto rp = result; rp; rp = rp->ai_next) {
5232  const auto &addr =
5233  *reinterpret_cast<struct sockaddr_storage *>(rp->ai_addr);
5234  std::string ip;
5235  auto dummy = -1;
5236  if (detail::get_ip_and_port(addr, sizeof(struct sockaddr_storage), ip,
5237  dummy)) {
5238  addrs.push_back(ip);
5239  }
5240  }
5241 
5242  freeaddrinfo(result);
5243 }

5245 inline std::string append_query_params(const std::string &path,
5246  const Params &params) {
5247  std::string path_with_query = path;
5248  const static std::regex re("[^?]+\\?.*");
5249  auto delm = std::regex_match(path, re) ? '&' : '?';
5250  path_with_query += delm + detail::params_to_query_str(params);
5251  return path_with_query;
5252 }

5254 // Header utilities
5255 inline std::pair<std::string, std::string>
5256 make_range_header(const Ranges &ranges) {
5257  std::string field = "bytes=";
5258  auto i = 0;
5259  for (const auto &r : ranges) {
5260  if (i != 0) { field += ", "; }
5261  if (r.first != -1) { field += std::to_string(r.first); }
5262  field += '-';
5263  if (r.second != -1) { field += std::to_string(r.second); }
5264  i++;
5265  }
5266  return std::make_pair("Range", std::move(field));
5267 }

5464 inline SocketStream::SocketStream(socket_t sock, time_t read_timeout_sec,
5465  time_t read_timeout_usec,
5466  time_t write_timeout_sec,
5467  time_t write_timeout_usec)
5468  : sock_(sock), read_timeout_sec_(read_timeout_sec),
5469  read_timeout_usec_(read_timeout_usec),

5477 }

5481  is_socket_alive(sock_);
5482 }
5483 
5484 inline ssize_t SocketStream::read(char *ptr, size_t size) {
5485 #ifdef _WIN32
5486  size =
5487  (std::min)(size, static_cast<size_t>((std::numeric_limits<int>::max)()));
5488 #else
5489  size = (std::min)(size,
5490  static_cast<size_t>((std::numeric_limits<ssize_t>::max)()));
5491 #endif
5492 
5493  if (read_buff_off_ < read_buff_content_size_) {
5494  auto remaining_size = read_buff_content_size_ - read_buff_off_;
5495  if (size <= remaining_size) {
5496  memcpy(ptr, read_buff_.data() + read_buff_off_, size);
5497  read_buff_off_ += size;
5498  return static_cast<ssize_t>(size);
5499  } else {
5500  memcpy(ptr, read_buff_.data() + read_buff_off_, remaining_size);
5501  read_buff_off_ += remaining_size;
5502  return static_cast<ssize_t>(remaining_size);
5503  }
5504  }
5505 
5506  if (!is_readable()) { return -1; }
5507 
5508  read_buff_off_ = 0;
5509  read_buff_content_size_ = 0;
5510 
5511  if (size < read_buff_size_) {
5512  auto n = read_socket(sock_, read_buff_.data(), read_buff_size_,
5513  CPPHTTPLIB_RECV_FLAGS);
5514  if (n <= 0) {
5515  return n;
5516  } else if (n <= static_cast<ssize_t>(size)) {
5517  memcpy(ptr, read_buff_.data(), static_cast<size_t>(n));
5518  return n;
5519  } else {
5520  memcpy(ptr, read_buff_.data(), size);
5521  read_buff_off_ = size;
5522  read_buff_content_size_ = static_cast<size_t>(n);
5523  return static_cast<ssize_t>(size);
5524  }
5525  } else {
5526  return read_socket(sock_, ptr, size, CPPHTTPLIB_RECV_FLAGS);
5527  }
5528 }
5529 
5530 inline ssize_t SocketStream::write(const char *ptr, size_t size) {
5531  if (!is_writable()) { return -1; }
5532 
5533 #if defined(_WIN32) && !defined(_WIN64)
5534  size =
5535  (std::min)(size, static_cast<size_t>((std::numeric_limits<int>::max)()));
5536 #endif
5537 
5538  return send_socket(sock_, ptr, size, CPPHTTPLIB_SEND_FLAGS);
5539 }

5581 inline const std::string &BufferStream::get_buffer() const { return buffer; }
5582 
5583 inline PathParamsMatcher::PathParamsMatcher(const std::string &pattern) {
5584  // One past the last ending position of a path param substring
5585  std::size_t last_param_end = 0;
5586 
5587 #ifndef CPPHTTPLIB_NO_EXCEPTIONS
5588  // Needed to ensure that parameter names are unique during matcher
5589  // construction
5590  // If exceptions are disabled, only last duplicate path
5591  // parameter will be set
5592  std::unordered_set<std::string> param_name_set;
5593 #endif
5594 
5595  while (true) {
5596  const auto marker_pos = pattern.find(marker, last_param_end);
5597  if (marker_pos == std::string::npos) { break; }
5598 
5599  static_fragments_.push_back(
5600  pattern.substr(last_param_end, marker_pos - last_param_end));
5601 
5602  const auto param_name_start = marker_pos + 1;
5603 
5604  auto sep_pos = pattern.find(separator, param_name_start);
5605  if (sep_pos == std::string::npos) { sep_pos = pattern.length(); }
5606 
5607  auto param_name =
5608  pattern.substr(param_name_start, sep_pos - param_name_start);
5609 
5610 #ifndef CPPHTTPLIB_NO_EXCEPTIONS
5611  if (param_name_set.find(param_name) != param_name_set.cend()) {
5612  std::string msg = "Encountered path parameter '" + param_name +
5613  "' multiple times in route pattern '" + pattern + "'.";
5614  throw std::invalid_argument(msg);
5615  }
5616 #endif
5617 
5618  param_names_.push_back(std::move(param_name));
5619 
5620  last_param_end = sep_pos + 1;
5621  }
5622 
5623  if (last_param_end < pattern.length()) {
5624  static_fragments_.push_back(pattern.substr(last_param_end));
5625  }
5626 }
5627 
5628 inline bool PathParamsMatcher::match(Request &request) const {
5629  request.matches = std::smatch();
5630  request.path_params.clear();
5631  request.path_params.reserve(param_names_.size());
5632 
5633  // One past the position at which the path matched the pattern last time
5634  std::size_t starting_pos = 0;
5635  for (size_t i = 0; i < static_fragments_.size(); ++i) {
5636  const auto &fragment = static_fragments_[i];
5637 
5638  if (starting_pos + fragment.length() > request.path.length()) {
5639  return false;
5640  }
5641 
5642  // Avoid unnecessary allocation by using strncmp instead of substr +
5643  // comparison
5644  if (std::strncmp(request.path.c_str() + starting_pos, fragment.c_str(),
5645  fragment.length()) != 0) {
5646  return false;
5647  }
5648 
5649  starting_pos += fragment.length();
5650 
5651  // Should only happen when we have a static fragment after a param
5652  // Example: '/users/:id/subscriptions'
5653  // The 'subscriptions' fragment here does not have a corresponding param
5654  if (i >= param_names_.size()) { continue; }
5655 
5656  auto sep_pos = request.path.find(separator, starting_pos);
5657  if (sep_pos == std::string::npos) { sep_pos = request.path.length(); }
5658 
5659  const auto &param_name = param_names_[i];
5660 
5661  request.path_params.emplace(
5662  param_name, request.path.substr(starting_pos, sep_pos - starting_pos));
5663 
5664  // Mark everythin up to '/' as matched
5665  starting_pos = sep_pos + 1;
5666  }
5667  // Returns false if the path is longer than the pattern
5668  return starting_pos >= request.path.length();
5669 }
5670 
5671 inline bool RegexMatcher::match(Request &request) const {
5672  request.path_params.clear();
5673  return std::regex_match(request.path, request.matches, regex_);
5674 }
5675

5925 inline void Server::stop() {

5927  assert(svr_sock_ != INVALID_SOCKET);
5928  std::atomic<socket_t> sock(svr_sock_.exchange(INVALID_SOCKET));

5934 inline bool Server::parse_request_line(const char *s, Request &req) const {
5935  auto len = strlen(s);
5936  if (len < 2 || s[len - 2] != '\r' || s[len - 1] != '\n') { return false; }
5937  len -= 2;
5938 
5939  {
5940  size_t count = 0;
5941 
5942  detail::split(s, s + len, ' ', [&](const char *b, const char *e) {
5943  switch (count) {
5944  case 0: req.method = std::string(b, e); break;
5945  case 1: req.target = std::string(b, e); break;
5946  case 2: req.version = std::string(b, e); break;
5947  default: break;
5948  }
5949  count++;
5950  });
5951 
5952  if (count != 3) { return false; }
5953  }
5954 
5955  static const std::set<std::string> methods{
5956  "GET", "HEAD", "POST", "PUT", "DELETE",
5957  "CONNECT", "OPTIONS", "TRACE", "PATCH", "PRI"};
5958 
5959  if (methods.find(req.method) == methods.end()) { return false; }
5960 
5961  if (req.version != "HTTP/1.1" && req.version != "HTTP/1.0") { return false; }
5962 
5963  {
5964  // Skip URL fragment
5965  for (size_t i = 0; i < req.target.size(); i++) {
5966  if (req.target[i] == '#') {
5967  req.target.erase(i);
5968  break;
5969  }
5970  }
5971 
5972  size_t count = 0;
5973 
5974  detail::split(req.target.data(), req.target.data() + req.target.size(), '?',
5975  2, [&](const char *b, const char *e) {
5976  switch (count) {
5977  case 0:
5978  req.path = detail::decode_url(std::string(b, e), false);
5979  break;
5980  case 1: {
5981  if (e - b > 0) {
5982  detail::parse_query_text(std::string(b, e), req.params);
5983  }
5984  break;
5985  }
5986  default: break;
5987  }
5988  count++;
5989  });
5990 
5991  if (count > 2) { return false; }
5992  }
5993 
5994  return true;
5995 }
5996 
5997 inline bool Server::write_response(Stream &strm, bool close_connection,
5998  Request &req, Response &res) {
5999  // NOTE: `req.ranges` should be empty, otherwise it will be applied
6000  // incorrectly to the error content.
6001  req.ranges.clear();
6002  return write_response_core(strm, close_connection, req, res, false);
6003 }
6004 
6005 inline bool Server::write_response_with_content(Stream &strm,
6006  bool close_connection,
6007  const Request &req,
6008  Response &res) {
6009  return write_response_core(strm, close_connection, req, res, true);
6010 }
6011 
6012 inline bool Server::write_response_core(Stream &strm, bool close_connection,
6013  const Request &req, Response &res,
6014  bool need_apply_ranges) {
6015  assert(res.status != -1);
6016 
6017  if (400 <= res.status && error_handler_ &&
6018  error_handler_(req, res) == HandlerResponse::Handled) {
6019  need_apply_ranges = true;
6020  }
6021 
6022  std::string content_type;
6023  std::string boundary;
6024  if (need_apply_ranges) { apply_ranges(req, res, content_type, boundary); }
6025 
6026  // Prepare additional headers
6027  if (close_connection || req.get_header_value("Connection") == "close") {
6028  res.set_header("Connection", "close");
6029  } else {
6030  std::stringstream ss;
6031  ss << "timeout=" << keep_alive_timeout_sec_
6032  << ", max=" << keep_alive_max_count_;
6033  res.set_header("Keep-Alive", ss.str());
6034  }
6035 
6036  if (!res.has_header("Content-Type") &&
6037  (!res.body.empty() || res.content_length_ > 0 || res.content_provider_)) {
6038  res.set_header("Content-Type", "text/plain");
6039  }
6040 
6041  if (!res.has_header("Content-Length") && res.body.empty() &&
6042  !res.content_length_ && !res.content_provider_) {
6043  res.set_header("Content-Length", "0");
6044  }
6045 
6046  if (!res.has_header("Accept-Ranges") && req.method == "HEAD") {
6047  res.set_header("Accept-Ranges", "bytes");
6048  }
6049 
6050  if (post_routing_handler_) { post_routing_handler_(req, res); }
6051 
6052  // Response line and headers
6053  {
6054  detail::BufferStream bstrm;
6055 
6056  if (!bstrm.write_format("HTTP/1.1 %d %s\r\n", res.status,
6057  status_message(res.status))) {
6058  return false;
6059  }
6060 
6061  if (!header_writer_(bstrm, res.headers)) { return false; }
6062 
6063  // Flush buffer
6064  auto &data = bstrm.get_buffer();
6065  detail::write_data(strm, data.data(), data.size());
6066  }
6067 
6068  // Body
6069  auto ret = true;
6070  if (req.method != "HEAD") {
6071  if (!res.body.empty()) {
6072  if (!detail::write_data(strm, res.body.data(), res.body.size())) {
6073  ret = false;
6074  }
6075  } else if (res.content_provider_) {
6076  if (write_content_with_provider(strm, req, res, boundary, content_type)) {
6077  res.content_provider_success_ = true;
6078  } else {
6079  ret = false;
6080  }
6081  }
6082  }
6083 
6084  // Log
6085  if (logger_) { logger_(req, res); }
6086 
6087  return ret;
6088 }
6089 
6090 inline bool
6091 Server::write_content_with_provider(Stream &strm, const Request &req,
6092  Response &res, const std::string &boundary,
6093  const std::string &content_type) {
6094  auto is_shutting_down = [this]() {
6095  return this->svr_sock_ == INVALID_SOCKET;
6096  };
6097 
6098  if (res.content_length_ > 0) {
6099  if (req.ranges.empty()) {
6100  return detail::write_content(strm, res.content_provider_, 0,
6101  res.content_length_, is_shutting_down);
6102  } else if (req.ranges.size() == 1) {
6103  auto offset_and_length = detail::get_range_offset_and_length(
6104  req.ranges[0], res.content_length_);
6105 
6106  return detail::write_content(strm, res.content_provider_,
6107  offset_and_length.first,
6108  offset_and_length.second, is_shutting_down);
6109  } else {
6110  return detail::write_multipart_ranges_data(
6111  strm, req, res, boundary, content_type, res.content_length_,
6112  is_shutting_down);
6113  }
6114  } else {
6115  if (res.is_chunked_content_provider_) {
6116  auto type = detail::encoding_type(req, res);
6117 
6118  std::unique_ptr<detail::compressor> compressor;
6119  if (type == detail::EncodingType::Gzip) {
6120 #ifdef CPPHTTPLIB_ZLIB_SUPPORT
6121  compressor = detail::make_unique<detail::gzip_compressor>();
6122 #endif
6123  } else if (type == detail::EncodingType::Brotli) {
6124 #ifdef CPPHTTPLIB_BROTLI_SUPPORT
6125  compressor = detail::make_unique<detail::brotli_compressor>();
6126 #endif
6127  } else {
6128  compressor = detail::make_unique<detail::nocompressor>();
6129  }
6130  assert(compressor != nullptr);
6131 
6132  return detail::write_content_chunked(strm, res.content_provider_,
6133  is_shutting_down, *compressor);
6134  } else {
6135  return detail::write_content_without_length(strm, res.content_provider_,
6136  is_shutting_down);
6137  }
6138  }
6139 }
6140 
6141 inline bool Server::read_content(Stream &strm, Request &req, Response &res) {
6142  MultipartFormDataMap::iterator cur;
6143  auto file_count = 0;
6144  if (read_content_core(
6145  strm, req, res,
6146  // Regular
6147  [&](const char *buf, size_t n) {
6148  if (req.body.size() + n > req.body.max_size()) { return false; }
6149  req.body.append(buf, n);
6150  return true;
6151  },
6152  // Multipart
6153  [&](const MultipartFormData &file) {
6154  if (file_count++ == CPPHTTPLIB_MULTIPART_FORM_DATA_FILE_MAX_COUNT) {
6155  return false;
6156  }
6157  cur = req.files.emplace(file.name, file);
6158  return true;
6159  },
6160  [&](const char *buf, size_t n) {
6161  auto &content = cur->second.content;
6162  if (content.size() + n > content.max_size()) { return false; }
6163  content.append(buf, n);
6164  return true;
6165  })) {
6166  const auto &content_type = req.get_header_value("Content-Type");
6167  if (!content_type.find("application/x-www-form-urlencoded")) {
6168  if (req.body.size() > CPPHTTPLIB_FORM_URL_ENCODED_PAYLOAD_MAX_LENGTH) {
6169  res.status = StatusCode::PayloadTooLarge_413; // NOTE: should be 414?
6170  return false;
6171  }
6172  detail::parse_query_text(req.body, req.params);
6173  }
6174  return true;
6175  }
6176  return false;
6177 }
6178 
6179 inline bool Server::read_content_with_content_receiver(
6180  Stream &strm, Request &req, Response &res, ContentReceiver receiver,
6181  MultipartContentHeader multipart_header,
6182  ContentReceiver multipart_receiver) {
6183  return read_content_core(strm, req, res, std::move(receiver),
6184  std::move(multipart_header),
6185  std::move(multipart_receiver));
6186 }
6187 
6188 inline bool
6189 Server::read_content_core(Stream &strm, Request &req, Response &res,
6190  ContentReceiver receiver,
6191  MultipartContentHeader multipart_header,
6192  ContentReceiver multipart_receiver) const {
6193  detail::MultipartFormDataParser multipart_form_data_parser;
6194  ContentReceiverWithProgress out;
6195 
6196  if (req.is_multipart_form_data()) {
6197  const auto &content_type = req.get_header_value("Content-Type");
6198  std::string boundary;
6199  if (!detail::parse_multipart_boundary(content_type, boundary)) {
6200  res.status = StatusCode::BadRequest_400;
6201  return false;
6202  }
6203 
6204  multipart_form_data_parser.set_boundary(std::move(boundary));
6205  out = [&](const char *buf, size_t n, uint64_t /*off*/, uint64_t /*len*/) {
6206  /* For debug
6207  size_t pos = 0;
6208  while (pos < n) {
6209  auto read_size = (std::min)<size_t>(1, n - pos);
6210  auto ret = multipart_form_data_parser.parse(
6211  buf + pos, read_size, multipart_receiver, multipart_header);
6212  if (!ret) { return false; }
6213  pos += read_size;
6214  }
6215  return true;
6216  */
6217  return multipart_form_data_parser.parse(buf, n, multipart_receiver,
6218  multipart_header);
6219  };
6220  } else {
6221  out = [receiver](const char *buf, size_t n, uint64_t /*off*/,
6222  uint64_t /*len*/) { return receiver(buf, n); };
6223  }
6224 
6225  if (req.method == "DELETE" && !req.has_header("Content-Length")) {
6226  return true;
6227  }
6228 
6229  if (!detail::read_content(strm, req, payload_max_length_, res.status, nullptr,
6230  out, true)) {
6231  return false;
6232  }
6233 
6234  if (req.is_multipart_form_data()) {
6235  if (!multipart_form_data_parser.is_valid()) {
6236  res.status = StatusCode::BadRequest_400;
6237  return false;
6238  }
6239  }
6240 
6241  return true;
6242 }
6243 
6244 inline bool Server::handle_file_request(const Request &req, Response &res,
6245  bool head) {
6246  for (const auto &entry : base_dirs_) {
6247  // Prefix match
6248  if (!req.path.compare(0, entry.mount_point.size(), entry.mount_point)) {
6249  std::string sub_path = "/" + req.path.substr(entry.mount_point.size());
6250  if (detail::is_valid_path(sub_path)) {
6251  auto path = entry.base_dir + sub_path;
6252  if (path.back() == '/') { path += "index.html"; }
6253 
6254  if (detail::is_file(path)) {
6255  for (const auto &kv : entry.headers) {
6256  res.set_header(kv.first, kv.second);
6257  }
6258 
6259  auto mm = std::make_shared<detail::mmap>(path.c_str());
6260  if (!mm->is_open()) { return false; }
6261 
6262  res.set_content_provider(
6263  mm->size(),
6264  detail::find_content_type(path, file_extension_and_mimetype_map_,
6265  default_file_mimetype_),
6266  [mm](size_t offset, size_t length, DataSink &sink) -> bool {
6267  sink.write(mm->data() + offset, length);
6268  return true;
6269  });
6270 
6271  if (!head && file_request_handler_) {
6272  file_request_handler_(req, res);
6273  }
6274 
6275  return true;
6276  }
6277  }
6278  }
6279  }
6280  return false;
6281 }
6282 
6283 inline socket_t
6284 Server::create_server_socket(const std::string &host, int port,
6285  int socket_flags,
6286  SocketOptions socket_options) const {
6287  return detail::create_socket(
6288  host, std::string(), port, address_family_, socket_flags, tcp_nodelay_,
6289  std::move(socket_options),
6290  [](socket_t sock, struct addrinfo &ai) -> bool {
6291  if (::bind(sock, ai.ai_addr, static_cast<socklen_t>(ai.ai_addrlen))) {
6292  return false;
6293  }
6294  if (::listen(sock, CPPHTTPLIB_LISTEN_BACKLOG)) { return false; }
6295  return true;
6296  });
6297 }
6298 
6299 inline int Server::bind_internal(const std::string &host, int port,
6300  int socket_flags) {
6301  if (!is_valid()) { return -1; }
6302 
6303  svr_sock_ = create_server_socket(host, port, socket_flags, socket_options_);
6304  if (svr_sock_ == INVALID_SOCKET) { return -1; }
6305 
6306  if (port == 0) {
6307  struct sockaddr_storage addr;
6308  socklen_t addr_len = sizeof(addr);
6309  if (getsockname(svr_sock_, reinterpret_cast<struct sockaddr *>(&addr),
6310  &addr_len) == -1) {
6311  return -1;
6312  }
6313  if (addr.ss_family == AF_INET) {
6314  return ntohs(reinterpret_cast<struct sockaddr_in *>(&addr)->sin_port);
6315  } else if (addr.ss_family == AF_INET6) {
6316  return ntohs(reinterpret_cast<struct sockaddr_in6 *>(&addr)->sin6_port);
6317  } else {
6318  return -1;
6319  }
6320  } else {
6321  return port;
6322  }
6323 }
6324 
6325 inline bool Server::listen_internal() {
6326  auto ret = true;
6327  is_running_ = true;
6328  auto se = detail::scope_exit([&]() { is_running_ = false; });
6329 
6330  {
6331  std::unique_ptr<TaskQueue> task_queue(new_task_queue());
6332 
6333  while (svr_sock_ != INVALID_SOCKET) {
6334 #ifndef _WIN32
6335  if (idle_interval_sec_ > 0 || idle_interval_usec_ > 0) {
6336 #endif
6337  auto val = detail::select_read(svr_sock_, idle_interval_sec_,
6338  idle_interval_usec_);
6339  if (val == 0) { // Timeout
6340  task_queue->on_idle();
6341  continue;
6342  }
6343 #ifndef _WIN32
6344  }
6345 #endif
6346  socket_t sock = accept(svr_sock_, nullptr, nullptr);
6347 
6348  if (sock == INVALID_SOCKET) {
6349  if (errno == EMFILE) {
6350  // The per-process limit of open file descriptors has been reached.
6351  // Try to accept new connections after a short sleep.
6352  std::this_thread::sleep_for(std::chrono::milliseconds(1));
6353  continue;
6354  } else if (errno == EINTR || errno == EAGAIN) {
6355  continue;
6356  }
6357  if (svr_sock_ != INVALID_SOCKET) {
6358  detail::close_socket(svr_sock_);
6359  ret = false;
6360  } else {
6361  ; // The server socket was closed by user.
6362  }
6363  break;
6364  }
6365 
6366  {
6367 #ifdef _WIN32
6368  auto timeout = static_cast<uint32_t>(read_timeout_sec_ * 1000 +
6369  read_timeout_usec_ / 1000);
6370  setsockopt(sock, SOL_SOCKET, SO_RCVTIMEO,
6371  reinterpret_cast<const char *>(&timeout), sizeof(timeout));
6372 #else
6373  timeval tv;
6374  tv.tv_sec = static_cast<long>(read_timeout_sec_);
6375  tv.tv_usec = static_cast<decltype(tv.tv_usec)>(read_timeout_usec_);
6376  setsockopt(sock, SOL_SOCKET, SO_RCVTIMEO,
6377  reinterpret_cast<const void *>(&tv), sizeof(tv));
6378 #endif
6379  }
6380  {
6381 
6382 #ifdef _WIN32
6383  auto timeout = static_cast<uint32_t>(write_timeout_sec_ * 1000 +
6384  write_timeout_usec_ / 1000);
6385  setsockopt(sock, SOL_SOCKET, SO_SNDTIMEO,
6386  reinterpret_cast<const char *>(&timeout), sizeof(timeout));
6387 #else
6388  timeval tv;
6389  tv.tv_sec = static_cast<long>(write_timeout_sec_);
6390  tv.tv_usec = static_cast<decltype(tv.tv_usec)>(write_timeout_usec_);
6391  setsockopt(sock, SOL_SOCKET, SO_SNDTIMEO,
6392  reinterpret_cast<const void *>(&tv), sizeof(tv));
6393 #endif
6394  }
6395 
6396  if (!task_queue->enqueue(
6397  [this, sock]() { process_and_close_socket(sock); })) {
6398  detail::shutdown_socket(sock);
6399  detail::close_socket(sock);
6400  }
6401  }
6402 
6403  task_queue->shutdown();
6404  }
6405 
6406  return ret;
6407 }
6408 
6409 inline bool Server::routing(Request &req, Response &res, Stream &strm) {
6410  if (pre_routing_handler_ &&
6411  pre_routing_handler_(req, res) == HandlerResponse::Handled) {
6412  return true;
6413  }
6414 
6415  // File handler
6416  auto is_head_request = req.method == "HEAD";
6417  if ((req.method == "GET" || is_head_request) &&
6418  handle_file_request(req, res, is_head_request)) {
6419  return true;
6420  }
6421 
6422  if (detail::expect_content(req)) {
6423  // Content reader handler
6424  {
6425  ContentReader reader(
6426  [&](ContentReceiver receiver) {
6427  return read_content_with_content_receiver(
6428  strm, req, res, std::move(receiver), nullptr, nullptr);
6429  },
6430  [&](MultipartContentHeader header, ContentReceiver receiver) {
6431  return read_content_with_content_receiver(strm, req, res, nullptr,
6432  std::move(header),
6433  std::move(receiver));
6434  });
6435 
6436  if (req.method == "POST") {
6437  if (dispatch_request_for_content_reader(
6438  req, res, std::move(reader),
6439  post_handlers_for_content_reader_)) {
6440  return true;
6441  }
6442  } else if (req.method == "PUT") {
6443  if (dispatch_request_for_content_reader(
6444  req, res, std::move(reader),
6445  put_handlers_for_content_reader_)) {
6446  return true;
6447  }
6448  } else if (req.method == "PATCH") {
6449  if (dispatch_request_for_content_reader(
6450  req, res, std::move(reader),
6451  patch_handlers_for_content_reader_)) {
6452  return true;
6453  }
6454  } else if (req.method == "DELETE") {
6455  if (dispatch_request_for_content_reader(
6456  req, res, std::move(reader),
6457  delete_handlers_for_content_reader_)) {
6458  return true;
6459  }
6460  }
6461  }
6462 
6463  // Read content into `req.body`
6464  if (!read_content(strm, req, res)) { return false; }
6465  }
6466 
6467  // Regular handler
6468  if (req.method == "GET" || req.method == "HEAD") {
6469  return dispatch_request(req, res, get_handlers_);
6470  } else if (req.method == "POST") {
6471  return dispatch_request(req, res, post_handlers_);
6472  } else if (req.method == "PUT") {
6473  return dispatch_request(req, res, put_handlers_);
6474  } else if (req.method == "DELETE") {
6475  return dispatch_request(req, res, delete_handlers_);
6476  } else if (req.method == "OPTIONS") {
6477  return dispatch_request(req, res, options_handlers_);
6478  } else if (req.method == "PATCH") {
6479  return dispatch_request(req, res, patch_handlers_);
6480  }
6481 
6482  res.status = StatusCode::BadRequest_400;
6483  return false;
6484 }
6485 
6486 inline bool Server::dispatch_request(Request &req, Response &res,
6487  const Handlers &handlers) const {
6488  for (const auto &x : handlers) {
6489  const auto &matcher = x.first;
6490  const auto &handler = x.second;
6491 
6492  if (matcher->match(req)) {
6493  handler(req, res);
6494  return true;
6495  }
6496  }
6497  return false;
6498 }
6499 
6500 inline void Server::apply_ranges(const Request &req, Response &res,
6501  std::string &content_type,
6502  std::string &boundary) const {
6503  if (req.ranges.size() > 1) {
6504  auto it = res.headers.find("Content-Type");
6505  if (it != res.headers.end()) {
6506  content_type = it->second;
6507  res.headers.erase(it);
6508  }
6509 
6510  boundary = detail::make_multipart_data_boundary();
6511 
6512  res.set_header("Content-Type",
6513  "multipart/byteranges; boundary=" + boundary);
6514  }
6515 
6516  auto type = detail::encoding_type(req, res);
6517 
6518  if (res.body.empty()) {
6519  if (res.content_length_ > 0) {
6520  size_t length = 0;
6521  if (req.ranges.empty()) {
6522  length = res.content_length_;
6523  } else if (req.ranges.size() == 1) {
6524  auto offset_and_length = detail::get_range_offset_and_length(
6525  req.ranges[0], res.content_length_);
6526 
6527  length = offset_and_length.second;
6528 
6529  auto content_range = detail::make_content_range_header_field(
6530  offset_and_length, res.content_length_);
6531  res.set_header("Content-Range", content_range);
6532  } else {
6533  length = detail::get_multipart_ranges_data_length(
6534  req, boundary, content_type, res.content_length_);
6535  }
6536  res.set_header("Content-Length", std::to_string(length));
6537  } else {
6538  if (res.content_provider_) {
6539  if (res.is_chunked_content_provider_) {
6540  res.set_header("Transfer-Encoding", "chunked");
6541  if (type == detail::EncodingType::Gzip) {
6542  res.set_header("Content-Encoding", "gzip");
6543  } else if (type == detail::EncodingType::Brotli) {
6544  res.set_header("Content-Encoding", "br");
6545  }
6546  }
6547  }
6548  }
6549  } else {
6550  if (req.ranges.empty()) {
6551  ;
6552  } else if (req.ranges.size() == 1) {
6553  auto offset_and_length =
6554  detail::get_range_offset_and_length(req.ranges[0], res.body.size());
6555  auto offset = offset_and_length.first;
6556  auto length = offset_and_length.second;
6557 
6558  auto content_range = detail::make_content_range_header_field(
6559  offset_and_length, res.body.size());
6560  res.set_header("Content-Range", content_range);
6561 
6562  assert(offset + length <= res.body.size());
6563  res.body = res.body.substr(offset, length);
6564  } else {
6565  std::string data;
6566  detail::make_multipart_ranges_data(req, res, boundary, content_type,
6567  res.body.size(), data);
6568  res.body.swap(data);
6569  }
6570 
6571  if (type != detail::EncodingType::None) {
6572  std::unique_ptr<detail::compressor> compressor;
6573  std::string content_encoding;
6574 
6575  if (type == detail::EncodingType::Gzip) {
6576 #ifdef CPPHTTPLIB_ZLIB_SUPPORT
6577  compressor = detail::make_unique<detail::gzip_compressor>();
6578  content_encoding = "gzip";
6579 #endif
6580  } else if (type == detail::EncodingType::Brotli) {
6581 #ifdef CPPHTTPLIB_BROTLI_SUPPORT
6582  compressor = detail::make_unique<detail::brotli_compressor>();
6583  content_encoding = "br";
6584 #endif
6585  }
6586 
6587  if (compressor) {
6588  std::string compressed;
6589  if (compressor->compress(res.body.data(), res.body.size(), true,
6590  [&](const char *data, size_t data_len) {
6591  compressed.append(data, data_len);
6592  return true;
6593  })) {
6594  res.body.swap(compressed);
6595  res.set_header("Content-Encoding", content_encoding);
6596  }
6597  }
6598  }
6599 
6600  auto length = std::to_string(res.body.size());
6601  res.set_header("Content-Length", length);
6602  }
6603 }
6604 
6605 inline bool Server::dispatch_request_for_content_reader(
6606  Request &req, Response &res, ContentReader content_reader,
6607  const HandlersForContentReader &handlers) const {
6608  for (const auto &x : handlers) {
6609  const auto &matcher = x.first;
6610  const auto &handler = x.second;
6611 
6612  if (matcher->match(req)) {
6613  handler(req, res, content_reader);
6614  return true;
6615  }
6616  }
6617  return false;
6618 }
6619 
6620 inline bool
6621 Server::process_request(Stream &strm, bool close_connection,
6622  bool &connection_closed,
6623  const std::function<void(Request &)> &setup_request) {
6624  std::array<char, 2048> buf{};
6625 
6626  detail::stream_line_reader line_reader(strm, buf.data(), buf.size());
6627 
6628  // Connection has been closed on client
6629  if (!line_reader.getline()) { return false; }
6630 
6631  Request req;
6632 
6633  Response res;
6634  res.version = "HTTP/1.1";
6635  res.headers = default_headers_;
6636 
6637 #ifdef _WIN32
6638  // TODO: Increase FD_SETSIZE statically (libzmq), dynamically (MySQL).
6639 #else
6640 #ifndef CPPHTTPLIB_USE_POLL
6641  // Socket file descriptor exceeded FD_SETSIZE...
6642  if (strm.socket() >= FD_SETSIZE) {
6643  Headers dummy;
6644  detail::read_headers(strm, dummy);
6645  res.status = StatusCode::InternalServerError_500;
6646  return write_response(strm, close_connection, req, res);
6647  }
6648 #endif
6649 #endif
6650 
6651  // Check if the request URI doesn't exceed the limit
6652  if (line_reader.size() > CPPHTTPLIB_REQUEST_URI_MAX_LENGTH) {
6653  Headers dummy;
6654  detail::read_headers(strm, dummy);
6655  res.status = StatusCode::UriTooLong_414;
6656  return write_response(strm, close_connection, req, res);
6657  }
6658 
6659  // Request line and headers
6660  if (!parse_request_line(line_reader.ptr(), req) ||
6661  !detail::read_headers(strm, req.headers)) {
6662  res.status = StatusCode::BadRequest_400;
6663  return write_response(strm, close_connection, req, res);
6664  }
6665 
6666  if (req.get_header_value("Connection") == "close") {
6667  connection_closed = true;
6668  }
6669 
6670  if (req.version == "HTTP/1.0" &&
6671  req.get_header_value("Connection") != "Keep-Alive") {
6672  connection_closed = true;
6673  }
6674 
6675  strm.get_remote_ip_and_port(req.remote_addr, req.remote_port);
6676  req.set_header("REMOTE_ADDR", req.remote_addr);
6677  req.set_header("REMOTE_PORT", std::to_string(req.remote_port));
6678 
6679  strm.get_local_ip_and_port(req.local_addr, req.local_port);
6680  req.set_header("LOCAL_ADDR", req.local_addr);
6681  req.set_header("LOCAL_PORT", std::to_string(req.local_port));
6682 
6683  if (req.has_header("Range")) {
6684  const auto &range_header_value = req.get_header_value("Range");
6685  if (!detail::parse_range_header(range_header_value, req.ranges)) {
6686  res.status = StatusCode::RangeNotSatisfiable_416;
6687  return write_response(strm, close_connection, req, res);
6688  }
6689  }
6690 
6691  if (setup_request) { setup_request(req); }
6692 
6693  if (req.get_header_value("Expect") == "100-continue") {
6694  int status = StatusCode::Continue_100;
6695  if (expect_100_continue_handler_) {
6696  status = expect_100_continue_handler_(req, res);
6697  }
6698  switch (status) {
6699  case StatusCode::Continue_100:
6700  case StatusCode::ExpectationFailed_417:
6701  strm.write_format("HTTP/1.1 %d %s\r\n\r\n", status,
6702  status_message(status));
6703  break;
6704  default: return write_response(strm, close_connection, req, res);
6705  }
6706  }
6707 
6708  // Routing
6709  auto routed = false;
6710 #ifdef CPPHTTPLIB_NO_EXCEPTIONS
6711  routed = routing(req, res, strm);
6712 #else
6713  try {
6714  routed = routing(req, res, strm);
6715  } catch (std::exception &e) {
6716  if (exception_handler_) {
6717  auto ep = std::current_exception();
6718  exception_handler_(req, res, ep);
6719  routed = true;
6720  } else {
6721  res.status = StatusCode::InternalServerError_500;
6722  std::string val;
6723  auto s = e.what();
6724  for (size_t i = 0; s[i]; i++) {
6725  switch (s[i]) {
6726  case '\r': val += "\\r"; break;
6727  case '\n': val += "\\n"; break;
6728  default: val += s[i]; break;
6729  }
6730  }
6731  res.set_header("EXCEPTION_WHAT", val);
6732  }
6733  } catch (...) {
6734  if (exception_handler_) {
6735  auto ep = std::current_exception();
6736  exception_handler_(req, res, ep);
6737  routed = true;
6738  } else {
6739  res.status = StatusCode::InternalServerError_500;
6740  res.set_header("EXCEPTION_WHAT", "UNKNOWN");
6741  }
6742  }
6743 #endif
6744  if (routed) {
6745  if (res.status == -1) {
6746  res.status = req.ranges.empty() ? StatusCode::OK_200
6747  : StatusCode::PartialContent_206;
6748  }
6749 
6750  if (detail::range_error(req, res)) {
6751  res.body.clear();
6752  res.content_length_ = 0;
6753  res.content_provider_ = nullptr;
6754  res.status = StatusCode::RangeNotSatisfiable_416;
6755  return write_response(strm, close_connection, req, res);
6756  }
6757 
6758  return write_response_with_content(strm, close_connection, req, res);
6759  } else {
6760  if (res.status == -1) { res.status = StatusCode::NotFound_404; }
6761 
6762  return write_response(strm, close_connection, req, res);
6763  }
6764 }
6765 
6766 inline bool Server::is_valid() const { return true; }
6767 
6768 inline bool Server::process_and_close_socket(socket_t sock) {
6769  auto ret = detail::process_server_socket(
6770  svr_sock_, sock, keep_alive_max_count_, keep_alive_timeout_sec_,
6771  read_timeout_sec_, read_timeout_usec_, write_timeout_sec_,
6772  write_timeout_usec_,
6773  [this](Stream &strm, bool close_connection, bool &connection_closed) {
6774  return process_request(strm, close_connection, connection_closed,
6775  nullptr);
6776  });
6777 
6778  detail::shutdown_socket(sock);
6779  detail::close_socket(sock);
6780  return ret;
6781 }

6805 inline void ClientImpl::copy_settings(const ClientImpl &rhs) {
6806  client_cert_path_ = rhs.client_cert_path_;
6807  client_key_path_ = rhs.client_key_path_;
6808  connection_timeout_sec_ = rhs.connection_timeout_sec_;
6809  read_timeout_sec_ = rhs.read_timeout_sec_;
6810  read_timeout_usec_ = rhs.read_timeout_usec_;
6811  write_timeout_sec_ = rhs.write_timeout_sec_;
6812  write_timeout_usec_ = rhs.write_timeout_usec_;
6813  basic_auth_username_ = rhs.basic_auth_username_;
6814  basic_auth_password_ = rhs.basic_auth_password_;
6815  bearer_token_auth_token_ = rhs.bearer_token_auth_token_;
6816 #ifdef CPPHTTPLIB_OPENSSL_SUPPORT
6817  digest_auth_username_ = rhs.digest_auth_username_;
6818  digest_auth_password_ = rhs.digest_auth_password_;
6819 #endif
6820  keep_alive_ = rhs.keep_alive_;
6821  follow_location_ = rhs.follow_location_;
6822  url_encode_ = rhs.url_encode_;
6823  address_family_ = rhs.address_family_;
6824  tcp_nodelay_ = rhs.tcp_nodelay_;
6825  socket_options_ = rhs.socket_options_;
6826  compress_ = rhs.compress_;
6827  decompress_ = rhs.decompress_;
6828  interface_ = rhs.interface_;
6829  proxy_host_ = rhs.proxy_host_;
6830  proxy_port_ = rhs.proxy_port_;
6831  proxy_basic_auth_username_ = rhs.proxy_basic_auth_username_;
6832  proxy_basic_auth_password_ = rhs.proxy_basic_auth_password_;
6833  proxy_bearer_token_auth_token_ = rhs.proxy_bearer_token_auth_token_;
6834 #ifdef CPPHTTPLIB_OPENSSL_SUPPORT
6835  proxy_digest_auth_username_ = rhs.proxy_digest_auth_username_;
6836  proxy_digest_auth_password_ = rhs.proxy_digest_auth_password_;
6837 #endif
6838 #ifdef CPPHTTPLIB_OPENSSL_SUPPORT
6839  ca_cert_file_path_ = rhs.ca_cert_file_path_;
6840  ca_cert_dir_path_ = rhs.ca_cert_dir_path_;
6841  ca_cert_store_ = rhs.ca_cert_store_;
6842 #endif
6843 #ifdef CPPHTTPLIB_OPENSSL_SUPPORT
6844  server_certificate_verification_ = rhs.server_certificate_verification_;
6845 #endif
6846  logger_ = rhs.logger_;
6847 }

6849 inline socket_t ClientImpl::create_client_socket(Error &error) const {
6850  if (!proxy_host_.empty() && proxy_port_ != -1) {
6851  return detail::create_client_socket(
6852  proxy_host_, std::string(), proxy_port_, address_family_, tcp_nodelay_,
6853  socket_options_, connection_timeout_sec_, connection_timeout_usec_,
6854  read_timeout_sec_, read_timeout_usec_, write_timeout_sec_,
6855  write_timeout_usec_, interface_, error);
6856  }
6857 
6858  // Check is custom IP specified for host_
6859  std::string ip;
6860  auto it = addr_map_.find(host_);
6861  if (it != addr_map_.end()) { ip = it->second; }
6862 
6863  return detail::create_client_socket(
6864  host_, ip, port_, address_family_, tcp_nodelay_, socket_options_,
6865  connection_timeout_sec_, connection_timeout_usec_, read_timeout_sec_,
6866  read_timeout_usec_, write_timeout_sec_, write_timeout_usec_, interface_,
6867  error);
6868 }
6869 
6870 inline bool ClientImpl::create_and_connect_socket(Socket &socket,
6871  Error &error) {
6872  auto sock = create_client_socket(error);
6873  if (sock == INVALID_SOCKET) { return false; }
6874  socket.sock = sock;
6875  return true;
6876 }
6877 
6878 inline void ClientImpl::shutdown_ssl(Socket & /*socket*/,
6879  bool /*shutdown_gracefully*/) {
6880  // If there are any requests in flight from threads other than us, then it's
6881  // a thread-unsafe race because individual ssl* objects are not thread-safe.
6882  assert(socket_requests_in_flight_ == 0 ||
6883  socket_requests_are_from_thread_ == std::this_thread::get_id());
6884 }
6885 
6886 inline void ClientImpl::shutdown_socket(Socket &socket) const {
6887  if (socket.sock == INVALID_SOCKET) { return; }
6888  detail::shutdown_socket(socket.sock);
6889 }
6890 
6891 inline void ClientImpl::close_socket(Socket &socket) {
6892  // If there are requests in flight in another thread, usually closing
6893  // the socket will be fine and they will simply receive an error when
6894  // using the closed socket, but it is still a bug since rarely the OS
6895  // may reassign the socket id to be used for a new socket, and then
6896  // suddenly they will be operating on a live socket that is different
6897  // than the one they intended!
6898  assert(socket_requests_in_flight_ == 0 ||
6899  socket_requests_are_from_thread_ == std::this_thread::get_id());
6900 
6901  // It is also a bug if this happens while SSL is still active
6902 #ifdef CPPHTTPLIB_OPENSSL_SUPPORT
6903  assert(socket.ssl == nullptr);
6904 #endif
6905  if (socket.sock == INVALID_SOCKET) { return; }
6906  detail::close_socket(socket.sock);
6907  socket.sock = INVALID_SOCKET;
6908 }
6909 
6910 inline bool ClientImpl::read_response_line(Stream &strm, const Request &req,
6911  Response &res) const {
6912  std::array<char, 2048> buf{};
6913 
6914  detail::stream_line_reader line_reader(strm, buf.data(), buf.size());
6915 
6916  if (!line_reader.getline()) { return false; }
6917 
6918 #ifdef CPPHTTPLIB_ALLOW_LF_AS_LINE_TERMINATOR
6919  const static std::regex re("(HTTP/1\\.[01]) (\\d{3})(?: (.*?))?\r?\n");
6920 #else
6921  const static std::regex re("(HTTP/1\\.[01]) (\\d{3})(?: (.*?))?\r\n");
6922 #endif
6923 
6924  std::cmatch m;
6925  if (!std::regex_match(line_reader.ptr(), m, re)) {
6926  return req.method == "CONNECT";
6927  }
6928  res.version = std::string(m[1]);
6929  res.status = std::stoi(std::string(m[2]));
6930  res.reason = std::string(m[3]);
6931 
6932  // Ignore '100 Continue'
6933  while (res.status == StatusCode::Continue_100) {
6934  if (!line_reader.getline()) { return false; } // CRLF
6935  if (!line_reader.getline()) { return false; } // next response line
6936 
6937  if (!std::regex_match(line_reader.ptr(), m, re)) { return false; }
6938  res.version = std::string(m[1]);
6939  res.status = std::stoi(std::string(m[2]));
6940  res.reason = std::string(m[3]);
6941  }
6942 
6943  return true;
6944 }
6945 
6946 inline bool ClientImpl::send(Request &req, Response &res, Error &error) {
6947  std::lock_guard<std::recursive_mutex> request_mutex_guard(request_mutex_);
6948  auto ret = send_(req, res, error);
6949  if (error == Error::SSLPeerCouldBeClosed_) {
6950  assert(!ret);
6951  ret = send_(req, res, error);
6952  }
6953  return ret;
6954 }
6955 
6956 inline bool ClientImpl::send_(Request &req, Response &res, Error &error) {
6957  {
6958  std::lock_guard<std::mutex> guard(socket_mutex_);
6959 
6960  // Set this to false immediately - if it ever gets set to true by the end of
6961  // the request, we know another thread instructed us to close the socket.
6962  socket_should_be_closed_when_request_is_done_ = false;
6963 
6964  auto is_alive = false;
6965  if (socket_.is_open()) {
6966  is_alive = detail::is_socket_alive(socket_.sock);
6967  if (!is_alive) {
6968  // Attempt to avoid sigpipe by shutting down nongracefully if it seems
6969  // like the other side has already closed the connection Also, there
6970  // cannot be any requests in flight from other threads since we locked
6971  // request_mutex_, so safe to close everything immediately
6972  const bool shutdown_gracefully = false;
6973  shutdown_ssl(socket_, shutdown_gracefully);
6974  shutdown_socket(socket_);
6975  close_socket(socket_);
6976  }
6977  }
6978 
6979  if (!is_alive) {
6980  if (!create_and_connect_socket(socket_, error)) { return false; }
6981 
6982 #ifdef CPPHTTPLIB_OPENSSL_SUPPORT
6983  // TODO: refactoring
6984  if (is_ssl()) {
6985  auto &scli = static_cast<SSLClient &>(*this);
6986  if (!proxy_host_.empty() && proxy_port_ != -1) {
6987  auto success = false;
6988  if (!scli.connect_with_proxy(socket_, res, success, error)) {
6989  return success;
6990  }
6991  }
6992 
6993  if (!scli.initialize_ssl(socket_, error)) { return false; }
6994  }
6995 #endif
6996  }
6997 
6998  // Mark the current socket as being in use so that it cannot be closed by
6999  // anyone else while this request is ongoing, even though we will be
7000  // releasing the mutex.
7001  if (socket_requests_in_flight_ > 1) {
7002  assert(socket_requests_are_from_thread_ == std::this_thread::get_id());
7003  }
7004  socket_requests_in_flight_ += 1;
7005  socket_requests_are_from_thread_ = std::this_thread::get_id();
7006  }
7007 
7008  for (const auto &header : default_headers_) {
7009  if (req.headers.find(header.first) == req.headers.end()) {
7010  req.headers.insert(header);
7011  }
7012  }
7013 
7014  auto ret = false;
7015  auto close_connection = !keep_alive_;
7016 
7017  auto se = detail::scope_exit([&]() {
7018  // Briefly lock mutex in order to mark that a request is no longer ongoing
7019  std::lock_guard<std::mutex> guard(socket_mutex_);
7020  socket_requests_in_flight_ -= 1;
7021  if (socket_requests_in_flight_ <= 0) {
7022  assert(socket_requests_in_flight_ == 0);
7023  socket_requests_are_from_thread_ = std::thread::id();
7024  }
7025 
7026  if (socket_should_be_closed_when_request_is_done_ || close_connection ||
7027  !ret) {
7028  shutdown_ssl(socket_, true);
7029  shutdown_socket(socket_);
7030  close_socket(socket_);
7031  }
7032  });
7033 
7034  ret = process_socket(socket_, [&](Stream &strm) {
7035  return handle_request(strm, req, res, close_connection, error);
7036  });
7037 
7038  if (!ret) {
7039  if (error == Error::Success) { error = Error::Unknown; }
7040  }
7041 
7042  return ret;
7043 }
7044 
7045 inline Result ClientImpl::send(const Request &req) {
7046  auto req2 = req;
7047  return send_(std::move(req2));
7048 }
7049 
7050 inline Result ClientImpl::send_(Request &&req) {
7051  auto res = detail::make_unique<Response>();
7052  auto error = Error::Success;
7053  auto ret = send(req, *res, error);
7054  return Result{ret ? std::move(res) : nullptr, error, std::move(req.headers)};
7055 }
7056 
7057 inline bool ClientImpl::handle_request(Stream &strm, Request &req,
7058  Response &res, bool close_connection,
7059  Error &error) {
7060  if (req.path.empty()) {
7061  error = Error::Connection;
7062  return false;
7063  }
7064 
7065  auto req_save = req;
7066 
7067  bool ret;
7068 
7069  if (!is_ssl() && !proxy_host_.empty() && proxy_port_ != -1) {
7070  auto req2 = req;
7071  req2.path = "http://" + host_and_port_ + req.path;
7072  ret = process_request(strm, req2, res, close_connection, error);
7073  req = req2;
7074  req.path = req_save.path;
7075  } else {
7076  ret = process_request(strm, req, res, close_connection, error);
7077  }
7078 
7079  if (!ret) { return false; }
7080 
7081  if (res.get_header_value("Connection") == "close" ||
7082  (res.version == "HTTP/1.0" && res.reason != "Connection established")) {
7083  // TODO this requires a not-entirely-obvious chain of calls to be correct
7084  // for this to be safe.
7085 
7086  // This is safe to call because handle_request is only called by send_
7087  // which locks the request mutex during the process. It would be a bug
7088  // to call it from a different thread since it's a thread-safety issue
7089  // to do these things to the socket if another thread is using the socket.
7090  std::lock_guard<std::mutex> guard(socket_mutex_);
7091  shutdown_ssl(socket_, true);
7092  shutdown_socket(socket_);
7093  close_socket(socket_);
7094  }
7095 
7096  if (300 < res.status && res.status < 400 && follow_location_) {
7097  req = req_save;
7098  ret = redirect(req, res, error);
7099  }
7100 
7101 #ifdef CPPHTTPLIB_OPENSSL_SUPPORT
7102  if ((res.status == StatusCode::Unauthorized_401 ||
7103  res.status == StatusCode::ProxyAuthenticationRequired_407) &&
7104  req.authorization_count_ < 5) {
7105  auto is_proxy = res.status == StatusCode::ProxyAuthenticationRequired_407;
7106  const auto &username =
7107  is_proxy ? proxy_digest_auth_username_ : digest_auth_username_;
7108  const auto &password =
7109  is_proxy ? proxy_digest_auth_password_ : digest_auth_password_;
7110 
7111  if (!username.empty() && !password.empty()) {
7112  std::map<std::string, std::string> auth;
7113  if (detail::parse_www_authenticate(res, auth, is_proxy)) {
7114  Request new_req = req;
7115  new_req.authorization_count_ += 1;
7116  new_req.headers.erase(is_proxy ? "Proxy-Authorization"
7117  : "Authorization");
7118  new_req.headers.insert(detail::make_digest_authentication_header(
7119  req, auth, new_req.authorization_count_, detail::random_string(10),
7120  username, password, is_proxy));
7121 
7122  Response new_res;
7123 
7124  ret = send(new_req, new_res, error);
7125  if (ret) { res = new_res; }
7126  }
7127  }
7128  }
7129 #endif
7130 
7131  return ret;
7132 }
7133 
7134 inline bool ClientImpl::redirect(Request &req, Response &res, Error &error) {
7135  if (req.redirect_count_ == 0) {
7136  error = Error::ExceedRedirectCount;
7137  return false;
7138  }
7139 
7140  auto location = res.get_header_value("location");
7141  if (location.empty()) { return false; }
7142 
7143  const static std::regex re(
7144  R"((?:(https?):)?(?://(?:\[([\d:]+)\]|([^:/?#]+))(?::(\d+))?)?([^?#]*)(\?[^#]*)?(?:#.*)?)");
7145 
7146  std::smatch m;
7147  if (!std::regex_match(location, m, re)) { return false; }
7148 
7149  auto scheme = is_ssl() ? "https" : "http";
7150 
7151  auto next_scheme = m[1].str();
7152  auto next_host = m[2].str();
7153  if (next_host.empty()) { next_host = m[3].str(); }
7154  auto port_str = m[4].str();
7155  auto next_path = m[5].str();
7156  auto next_query = m[6].str();
7157 
7158  auto next_port = port_;
7159  if (!port_str.empty()) {
7160  next_port = std::stoi(port_str);
7161  } else if (!next_scheme.empty()) {
7162  next_port = next_scheme == "https" ? 443 : 80;
7163  }
7164 
7165  if (next_scheme.empty()) { next_scheme = scheme; }
7166  if (next_host.empty()) { next_host = host_; }
7167  if (next_path.empty()) { next_path = "/"; }
7168 
7169  auto path = detail::decode_url(next_path, true) + next_query;
7170 
7171  if (next_scheme == scheme && next_host == host_ && next_port == port_) {
7172  return detail::redirect(*this, req, res, path, location, error);
7173  } else {
7174  if (next_scheme == "https") {
7175 #ifdef CPPHTTPLIB_OPENSSL_SUPPORT
7176  SSLClient cli(next_host, next_port);
7177  cli.copy_settings(*this);
7178  if (ca_cert_store_) { cli.set_ca_cert_store(ca_cert_store_); }
7179  return detail::redirect(cli, req, res, path, location, error);
7180 #else
7181  return false;
7182 #endif
7183  } else {
7184  ClientImpl cli(next_host, next_port);
7185  cli.copy_settings(*this);
7186  return detail::redirect(cli, req, res, path, location, error);
7187  }
7188  }
7189 }
7190 
7191 inline bool ClientImpl::write_content_with_provider(Stream &strm,
7192  const Request &req,
7193  Error &error) const {
7194  auto is_shutting_down = []() { return false; };
7195 
7196  if (req.is_chunked_content_provider_) {
7197  // TODO: Brotli support
7198  std::unique_ptr<detail::compressor> compressor;
7199 #ifdef CPPHTTPLIB_ZLIB_SUPPORT
7200  if (compress_) {
7201  compressor = detail::make_unique<detail::gzip_compressor>();
7202  } else
7203 #endif
7204  {
7205  compressor = detail::make_unique<detail::nocompressor>();
7206  }
7207 
7208  return detail::write_content_chunked(strm, req.content_provider_,
7209  is_shutting_down, *compressor, error);
7210  } else {
7211  return detail::write_content(strm, req.content_provider_, 0,
7212  req.content_length_, is_shutting_down, error);
7213  }
7214 }
7215 
7216 inline bool ClientImpl::write_request(Stream &strm, Request &req,
7217  bool close_connection, Error &error) {
7218  // Prepare additional headers
7219  if (close_connection) {
7220  if (!req.has_header("Connection")) {
7221  req.set_header("Connection", "close");
7222  }
7223  }
7224 
7225  if (!req.has_header("Host")) {
7226  if (is_ssl()) {
7227  if (port_ == 443) {
7228  req.set_header("Host", host_);
7229  } else {
7230  req.set_header("Host", host_and_port_);
7231  }
7232  } else {
7233  if (port_ == 80) {
7234  req.set_header("Host", host_);
7235  } else {
7236  req.set_header("Host", host_and_port_);
7237  }
7238  }
7239  }
7240 
7241  if (!req.has_header("Accept")) { req.set_header("Accept", "*/*"); }
7242 
7243 #ifndef CPPHTTPLIB_NO_DEFAULT_USER_AGENT
7244  if (!req.has_header("User-Agent")) {
7245  auto agent = std::string("cpp-httplib/") + CPPHTTPLIB_VERSION;
7246  req.set_header("User-Agent", agent);
7247  }
7248 #endif
7249 
7250  if (req.body.empty()) {
7251  if (req.content_provider_) {
7252  if (!req.is_chunked_content_provider_) {
7253  if (!req.has_header("Content-Length")) {
7254  auto length = std::to_string(req.content_length_);
7255  req.set_header("Content-Length", length);
7256  }
7257  }
7258  } else {
7259  if (req.method == "POST" || req.method == "PUT" ||
7260  req.method == "PATCH") {
7261  req.set_header("Content-Length", "0");
7262  }
7263  }
7264  } else {
7265  if (!req.has_header("Content-Type")) {
7266  req.set_header("Content-Type", "text/plain");
7267  }
7268 
7269  if (!req.has_header("Content-Length")) {
7270  auto length = std::to_string(req.body.size());
7271  req.set_header("Content-Length", length);
7272  }
7273  }
7274 
7275  if (!basic_auth_password_.empty() || !basic_auth_username_.empty()) {
7276  if (!req.has_header("Authorization")) {
7277  req.headers.insert(make_basic_authentication_header(
7278  basic_auth_username_, basic_auth_password_, false));
7279  }
7280  }
7281 
7282  if (!proxy_basic_auth_username_.empty() &&
7283  !proxy_basic_auth_password_.empty()) {
7284  if (!req.has_header("Proxy-Authorization")) {
7285  req.headers.insert(make_basic_authentication_header(
7286  proxy_basic_auth_username_, proxy_basic_auth_password_, true));
7287  }
7288  }
7289 
7290  if (!bearer_token_auth_token_.empty()) {
7291  if (!req.has_header("Authorization")) {
7292  req.headers.insert(make_bearer_token_authentication_header(
7293  bearer_token_auth_token_, false));
7294  }
7295  }
7296 
7297  if (!proxy_bearer_token_auth_token_.empty()) {
7298  if (!req.has_header("Proxy-Authorization")) {
7299  req.headers.insert(make_bearer_token_authentication_header(
7300  proxy_bearer_token_auth_token_, true));
7301  }
7302  }
7303 
7304  // Request line and headers
7305  {
7306  detail::BufferStream bstrm;
7307 
7308  const auto &path = url_encode_ ? detail::encode_url(req.path) : req.path;
7309  bstrm.write_format("%s %s HTTP/1.1\r\n", req.method.c_str(), path.c_str());
7310 
7311  header_writer_(bstrm, req.headers);
7312 
7313  // Flush buffer
7314  auto &data = bstrm.get_buffer();
7315  if (!detail::write_data(strm, data.data(), data.size())) {
7316  error = Error::Write;
7317  return false;
7318  }
7319  }
7320 
7321  // Body
7322  if (req.body.empty()) {
7323  return write_content_with_provider(strm, req, error);
7324  }
7325 
7326  if (!detail::write_data(strm, req.body.data(), req.body.size())) {
7327  error = Error::Write;
7328  return false;
7329  }
7330 
7331  return true;
7332 }
7333 
7334 inline std::unique_ptr<Response> ClientImpl::send_with_content_provider(
7335  Request &req, const char *body, size_t content_length,
7336  ContentProvider content_provider,
7337  ContentProviderWithoutLength content_provider_without_length,
7338  const std::string &content_type, Error &error) {
7339  if (!content_type.empty()) { req.set_header("Content-Type", content_type); }
7340 
7341 #ifdef CPPHTTPLIB_ZLIB_SUPPORT
7342  if (compress_) { req.set_header("Content-Encoding", "gzip"); }
7343 #endif
7344 
7345 #ifdef CPPHTTPLIB_ZLIB_SUPPORT
7346  if (compress_ && !content_provider_without_length) {
7347  // TODO: Brotli support
7348  detail::gzip_compressor compressor;
7349 
7350  if (content_provider) {
7351  auto ok = true;
7352  size_t offset = 0;
7353  DataSink data_sink;
7354 
7355  data_sink.write = [&](const char *data, size_t data_len) -> bool {
7356  if (ok) {
7357  auto last = offset + data_len == content_length;
7358 
7359  auto ret = compressor.compress(
7360  data, data_len, last,
7361  [&](const char *compressed_data, size_t compressed_data_len) {
7362  req.body.append(compressed_data, compressed_data_len);
7363  return true;
7364  });
7365 
7366  if (ret) {
7367  offset += data_len;
7368  } else {
7369  ok = false;
7370  }
7371  }
7372  return ok;
7373  };
7374 
7375  while (ok && offset < content_length) {
7376  if (!content_provider(offset, content_length - offset, data_sink)) {
7377  error = Error::Canceled;
7378  return nullptr;
7379  }
7380  }
7381  } else {
7382  if (!compressor.compress(body, content_length, true,
7383  [&](const char *data, size_t data_len) {
7384  req.body.append(data, data_len);
7385  return true;
7386  })) {
7387  error = Error::Compression;
7388  return nullptr;
7389  }
7390  }
7391  } else
7392 #endif
7393  {
7394  if (content_provider) {
7395  req.content_length_ = content_length;
7396  req.content_provider_ = std::move(content_provider);
7397  req.is_chunked_content_provider_ = false;
7398  } else if (content_provider_without_length) {
7399  req.content_length_ = 0;
7400  req.content_provider_ = detail::ContentProviderAdapter(
7401  std::move(content_provider_without_length));
7402  req.is_chunked_content_provider_ = true;
7403  req.set_header("Transfer-Encoding", "chunked");
7404  } else {
7405  req.body.assign(body, content_length);
7406  }
7407  }
7408 
7409  auto res = detail::make_unique<Response>();
7410  return send(req, *res, error) ? std::move(res) : nullptr;
7411 }
7412 
7413 inline Result ClientImpl::send_with_content_provider(
7414  const std::string &method, const std::string &path, const Headers &headers,
7415  const char *body, size_t content_length, ContentProvider content_provider,
7416  ContentProviderWithoutLength content_provider_without_length,
7417  const std::string &content_type) {
7418  Request req;
7419  req.method = method;
7420  req.headers = headers;
7421  req.path = path;
7422 
7423  auto error = Error::Success;
7424 
7425  auto res = send_with_content_provider(
7426  req, body, content_length, std::move(content_provider),
7427  std::move(content_provider_without_length), content_type, error);
7428 
7429  return Result{std::move(res), error, std::move(req.headers)};
7430 }
7431 
7432 inline std::string
7433 ClientImpl::adjust_host_string(const std::string &host) const {
7434  if (host.find(':') != std::string::npos) { return "[" + host + "]"; }
7435  return host;
7436 }
7437 
7438 inline bool ClientImpl::process_request(Stream &strm, Request &req,
7439  Response &res, bool close_connection,
7440  Error &error) {
7441  // Send request
7442  if (!write_request(strm, req, close_connection, error)) { return false; }
7443 
7444 #ifdef CPPHTTPLIB_OPENSSL_SUPPORT
7445  if (is_ssl()) {
7446  auto is_proxy_enabled = !proxy_host_.empty() && proxy_port_ != -1;
7447  if (!is_proxy_enabled) {
7448  char buf[1];
7449  if (SSL_peek(socket_.ssl, buf, 1) == 0 &&
7450  SSL_get_error(socket_.ssl, 0) == SSL_ERROR_ZERO_RETURN) {
7451  error = Error::SSLPeerCouldBeClosed_;
7452  return false;
7453  }
7454  }
7455  }
7456 #endif
7457 
7458  // Receive response and headers
7459  if (!read_response_line(strm, req, res) ||
7460  !detail::read_headers(strm, res.headers)) {
7461  error = Error::Read;
7462  return false;
7463  }
7464 
7465  // Body
7466  if ((res.status != StatusCode::NoContent_204) && req.method != "HEAD" &&
7467  req.method != "CONNECT") {
7468  auto redirect = 300 < res.status && res.status < 400 && follow_location_;
7469 
7470  if (req.response_handler && !redirect) {
7471  if (!req.response_handler(res)) {
7472  error = Error::Canceled;
7473  return false;
7474  }
7475  }
7476 
7477  auto out =
7478  req.content_receiver
7479  ? static_cast<ContentReceiverWithProgress>(
7480  [&](const char *buf, size_t n, uint64_t off, uint64_t len) {
7481  if (redirect) { return true; }
7482  auto ret = req.content_receiver(buf, n, off, len);
7483  if (!ret) { error = Error::Canceled; }
7484  return ret;
7485  })
7486  : static_cast<ContentReceiverWithProgress>(
7487  [&](const char *buf, size_t n, uint64_t /*off*/,
7488  uint64_t /*len*/) {
7489  if (res.body.size() + n > res.body.max_size()) {
7490  return false;
7491  }
7492  res.body.append(buf, n);
7493  return true;
7494  });
7495 
7496  auto progress = [&](uint64_t current, uint64_t total) {
7497  if (!req.progress || redirect) { return true; }
7498  auto ret = req.progress(current, total);
7499  if (!ret) { error = Error::Canceled; }
7500  return ret;
7501  };
7502 
7503  int dummy_status;
7504  if (!detail::read_content(strm, res, (std::numeric_limits<size_t>::max)(),
7505  dummy_status, std::move(progress), std::move(out),
7506  decompress_)) {
7507  if (error != Error::Canceled) { error = Error::Read; }
7508  return false;
7509  }
7510  }
7511 
7512  // Log
7513  if (logger_) { logger_(req, res); }
7514 
7515  return true;
7516 }
7517 
7518 inline ContentProviderWithoutLength ClientImpl::get_multipart_content_provider(
7519  const std::string &boundary, const MultipartFormDataItems &items,
7520  const MultipartFormDataProviderItems &provider_items) const {
7521  size_t cur_item = 0;
7522  size_t cur_start = 0;
7523  // cur_item and cur_start are copied to within the std::function and maintain
7524  // state between successive calls
7525  return [&, cur_item, cur_start](size_t offset,
7526  DataSink &sink) mutable -> bool {
7527  if (!offset && !items.empty()) {
7528  sink.os << detail::serialize_multipart_formdata(items, boundary, false);
7529  return true;
7530  } else if (cur_item < provider_items.size()) {
7531  if (!cur_start) {
7532  const auto &begin = detail::serialize_multipart_formdata_item_begin(
7533  provider_items[cur_item], boundary);
7534  offset += begin.size();
7535  cur_start = offset;
7536  sink.os << begin;
7537  }
7538 
7539  DataSink cur_sink;
7540  auto has_data = true;
7541  cur_sink.write = sink.write;
7542  cur_sink.done = [&]() { has_data = false; };
7543 
7544  if (!provider_items[cur_item].provider(offset - cur_start, cur_sink)) {
7545  return false;
7546  }
7547 
7548  if (!has_data) {
7549  sink.os << detail::serialize_multipart_formdata_item_end();
7550  cur_item++;
7551  cur_start = 0;
7552  }
7553  return true;
7554  } else {
7555  sink.os << detail::serialize_multipart_formdata_finish(boundary);
7556  sink.done();
7557  return true;
7558  }
7559  };
7560 }

7567  write_timeout_usec_, std::move(callback));

7642  ResponseHandler response_handler,
7643  ContentReceiver content_receiver,
7644  Progress progress) {
7645  Request req;
7646  req.method = "GET";
7647  req.path = path;
7648  req.headers = headers;
7649  req.response_handler = std::move(response_handler);
7650  req.content_receiver =
7651  [content_receiver](const char *data, size_t data_length,
7652  uint64_t /*offset*/, uint64_t /*total_length*/) {
7653  return content_receiver(data, data_length);
7654  };
7655  req.progress = std::move(progress);
7656 
7657  return send_(std::move(req));
7658 }

8002 
8003 inline Result ClientImpl::Delete(const std::string &path,
8004  const Headers &headers, const char *body,
8005  size_t content_length,
8006  const std::string &content_type) {
8007  Request req;
8008  req.method = "DELETE";
8009  req.headers = headers;
8010  req.path = path;
8011 
8012  if (!content_type.empty()) { req.set_header("Content-Type", content_type); }
8013  req.body.assign(body, content_length);
8014 
8015  return send_(std::move(req));
8016 }

8044 
8045 inline void ClientImpl::stop() {
8046  std::lock_guard<std::mutex> guard(socket_mutex_);
8047 
8048  // If there is anything ongoing right now, the ONLY thread-safe thing we can
8049  // do is to shutdown_socket, so that threads using this socket suddenly
8050  // discover they can't read/write any more and error out. Everything else
8051  // (closing the socket, shutting ssl down) is unsafe because these actions are
8052  // not thread-safe.
8053  if (socket_requests_in_flight_ > 0) {
8054  shutdown_socket(socket_);
8055 
8056  // Aside from that, we set a flag for the socket to be closed when we're
8057  // done.
8058  socket_should_be_closed_when_request_is_done_ = true;
8059  return;
8060  }
8061 
8062  // Otherwise, still holding the mutex, we can shut everything down ourselves
8063  shutdown_ssl(socket_, true);
8064  shutdown_socket(socket_);
8065  close_socket(socket_);
8066 }

8184 inline X509_STORE *ClientImpl::create_ca_cert_store(const char *ca_cert,
8185  std::size_t size) const {
8186  auto mem = BIO_new_mem_buf(ca_cert, static_cast<int>(size));
8187  if (!mem) { return nullptr; }
8188 
8189  auto inf = PEM_X509_INFO_read_bio(mem, nullptr, nullptr, nullptr);
8190  if (!inf) {
8191  BIO_free_all(mem);
8192  return nullptr;
8193  }
8194 
8195  auto cts = X509_STORE_new();
8196  if (cts) {
8197  for (auto i = 0; i < static_cast<int>(sk_X509_INFO_num(inf)); i++) {
8198  auto itmp = sk_X509_INFO_value(inf, i);
8199  if (!itmp) { continue; }
8200 
8201  if (itmp->x509) { X509_STORE_add_cert(cts, itmp->x509); }
8202  if (itmp->crl) { X509_STORE_add_crl(cts, itmp->crl); }
8203  }
8204  }
8205 
8206  sk_X509_INFO_pop_free(inf, X509_INFO_free);
8207  BIO_free_all(mem);
8208  return cts;
8209 }

8221  * SSL Implementation
8222  */

8224 namespace detail {

8226 template <typename U, typename V>
8227 inline SSL *ssl_new(socket_t sock, SSL_CTX *ctx, std::mutex &ctx_mutex,
8228  U SSL_connect_or_accept, V setup) {
8229  SSL *ssl = nullptr;
8230  {
8231  std::lock_guard<std::mutex> guard(ctx_mutex);
8232  ssl = SSL_new(ctx);
8233  }
8234 
8235  if (ssl) {
8236  set_nonblocking(sock, true);
8237  auto bio = BIO_new_socket(static_cast<int>(sock), BIO_NOCLOSE);
8238  BIO_set_nbio(bio, 1);
8239  SSL_set_bio(ssl, bio, bio);
8240 
8241  if (!setup(ssl) || SSL_connect_or_accept(ssl) != 1) {
8242  SSL_shutdown(ssl);
8243  {
8244  std::lock_guard<std::mutex> guard(ctx_mutex);
8245  SSL_free(ssl);
8246  }
8247  set_nonblocking(sock, false);
8248  return nullptr;
8249  }
8250  BIO_set_nbio(bio, 0);
8251  set_nonblocking(sock, false);
8252  }
8253 
8254  return ssl;
8255 }
8256 
8257 inline void ssl_delete(std::mutex &ctx_mutex, SSL *ssl,
8258  bool shutdown_gracefully) {
8259  // sometimes we may want to skip this to try to avoid SIGPIPE if we know
8260  // the remote has closed the network connection
8261  // Note that it is not always possible to avoid SIGPIPE, this is merely a
8262  // best-efforts.
8263  if (shutdown_gracefully) { SSL_shutdown(ssl); }
8264 
8265  std::lock_guard<std::mutex> guard(ctx_mutex);
8266  SSL_free(ssl);
8267 }
8268 
8269 template <typename U>
8270 bool ssl_connect_or_accept_nonblocking(socket_t sock, SSL *ssl,
8271  U ssl_connect_or_accept,
8272  time_t timeout_sec,
8273  time_t timeout_usec) {
8274  auto res = 0;
8275  while ((res = ssl_connect_or_accept(ssl)) != 1) {
8276  auto err = SSL_get_error(ssl, res);
8277  switch (err) {
8278  case SSL_ERROR_WANT_READ:
8279  if (select_read(sock, timeout_sec, timeout_usec) > 0) { continue; }
8280  break;
8281  case SSL_ERROR_WANT_WRITE:
8282  if (select_write(sock, timeout_sec, timeout_usec) > 0) { continue; }
8283  break;
8284  default: break;
8285  }
8286  return false;
8287  }
8288  return true;
8289 }
8290 
8291 template <typename T>
8292 inline bool process_server_socket_ssl(
8293  const std::atomic<socket_t> &svr_sock, SSL *ssl, socket_t sock,
8294  size_t keep_alive_max_count, time_t keep_alive_timeout_sec,
8295  time_t read_timeout_sec, time_t read_timeout_usec, time_t write_timeout_sec,
8296  time_t write_timeout_usec, T callback) {
8297  return process_server_socket_core(
8298  svr_sock, sock, keep_alive_max_count, keep_alive_timeout_sec,
8299  [&](bool close_connection, bool &connection_closed) {
8300  SSLSocketStream strm(sock, ssl, read_timeout_sec, read_timeout_usec,
8301  write_timeout_sec, write_timeout_usec);
8302  return callback(strm, close_connection, connection_closed);
8303  });
8304 }
8305 
8306 template <typename T>
8307 inline bool
8308 process_client_socket_ssl(SSL *ssl, socket_t sock, time_t read_timeout_sec,
8309  time_t read_timeout_usec, time_t write_timeout_sec,
8310  time_t write_timeout_usec, T callback) {
8311  SSLSocketStream strm(sock, ssl, read_timeout_sec, read_timeout_usec,
8312  write_timeout_sec, write_timeout_usec);
8313  return callback(strm);
8314 }

8321  }

8326  time_t read_timeout_sec,

8328  time_t write_timeout_sec,
8329  time_t write_timeout_usec)
8330  : sock_(sock), ssl_(ssl), read_timeout_sec_(read_timeout_sec),
8331  read_timeout_usec_(read_timeout_usec),
8332  write_timeout_sec_(write_timeout_sec),
