8339 inline bool SSLSocketStream::is_readable() const {
8340  return detail::select_read(sock_, read_timeout_sec_, read_timeout_usec_) > 0;
8341 }
8342 
8343 inline bool SSLSocketStream::is_writable() const {
8344  return select_write(sock_, write_timeout_sec_, write_timeout_usec_) > 0 &&
8345  is_socket_alive(sock_);
8346 }
8347 
8348 inline ssize_t SSLSocketStream::read(char *ptr, size_t size) {
8349  if (SSL_pending(ssl_) > 0) {
8350  return SSL_read(ssl_, ptr, static_cast<int>(size));
8351  } else if (is_readable()) {
8352  auto ret = SSL_read(ssl_, ptr, static_cast<int>(size));
8353  if (ret < 0) {
8354  auto err = SSL_get_error(ssl_, ret);
8355  auto n = 1000;
8356 #ifdef _WIN32
8357  while (--n >= 0 && (err == SSL_ERROR_WANT_READ ||
8358  (err == SSL_ERROR_SYSCALL &&
8359  WSAGetLastError() == WSAETIMEDOUT))) {
8360 #else
8361  while (--n >= 0 && err == SSL_ERROR_WANT_READ) {
8362 #endif
8363  if (SSL_pending(ssl_) > 0) {
8364  return SSL_read(ssl_, ptr, static_cast<int>(size));
8365  } else if (is_readable()) {
8366  std::this_thread::sleep_for(std::chrono::milliseconds(1));
8367  ret = SSL_read(ssl_, ptr, static_cast<int>(size));
8368  if (ret >= 0) { return ret; }
8369  err = SSL_get_error(ssl_, ret);
8370  } else {
8371  return -1;
8372  }
8373  }
8374  }
8375  return ret;
8376  }
8377  return -1;
8378 }
8379 
8380 inline ssize_t SSLSocketStream::write(const char *ptr, size_t size) {
8381  if (is_writable()) {
8382  auto handle_size = static_cast<int>(
8383  std::min<size_t>(size, (std::numeric_limits<int>::max)()));
8384 
8385  auto ret = SSL_write(ssl_, ptr, static_cast<int>(handle_size));
8386  if (ret < 0) {
8387  auto err = SSL_get_error(ssl_, ret);
8388  auto n = 1000;
8389 #ifdef _WIN32
8390  while (--n >= 0 && (err == SSL_ERROR_WANT_WRITE ||
8391  (err == SSL_ERROR_SYSCALL &&
8392  WSAGetLastError() == WSAETIMEDOUT))) {
8393 #else
8394  while (--n >= 0 && err == SSL_ERROR_WANT_WRITE) {
8395 #endif
8396  if (is_writable()) {
8397  std::this_thread::sleep_for(std::chrono::milliseconds(1));
8398  ret = SSL_write(ssl_, ptr, static_cast<int>(handle_size));
8399  if (ret >= 0) { return ret; }
8400  err = SSL_get_error(ssl_, ret);
8401  } else {
8402  return -1;
8403  }
8404  }
8405  }
8406  return ret;
8407  }
8408  return -1;
8409 }

8427 // SSL HTTP server implementation
8428 inline SSLServer::SSLServer(const char *cert_path, const char *private_key_path,
8429  const char *client_ca_cert_file_path,
8430  const char *client_ca_cert_dir_path,
8431  const char *private_key_password) {
8432  ctx_ = SSL_CTX_new(TLS_server_method());
8433 
8434  if (ctx_) {
8435  SSL_CTX_set_options(ctx_,
8436  SSL_OP_NO_COMPRESSION |
8437  SSL_OP_NO_SESSION_RESUMPTION_ON_RENEGOTIATION);
8438 
8439  SSL_CTX_set_min_proto_version(ctx_, TLS1_1_VERSION);
8440 
8441  // add default password callback before opening encrypted private key
8442  if (private_key_password != nullptr && (private_key_password[0] != '\0')) {
8443  SSL_CTX_set_default_passwd_cb_userdata(
8444  ctx_,
8445  reinterpret_cast<void *>(const_cast<char *>(private_key_password)));
8446  }
8447 
8448  if (SSL_CTX_use_certificate_chain_file(ctx_, cert_path) != 1 ||
8449  SSL_CTX_use_PrivateKey_file(ctx_, private_key_path, SSL_FILETYPE_PEM) !=
8450  1) {
8451  SSL_CTX_free(ctx_);
8452  ctx_ = nullptr;
8453  } else if (client_ca_cert_file_path || client_ca_cert_dir_path) {
8454  SSL_CTX_load_verify_locations(ctx_, client_ca_cert_file_path,
8455  client_ca_cert_dir_path);
8456 
8457  SSL_CTX_set_verify(
8458  ctx_, SSL_VERIFY_PEER | SSL_VERIFY_FAIL_IF_NO_PEER_CERT, nullptr);
8459  }
8460  }
8461 }
8462 
8463 inline SSLServer::SSLServer(X509 *cert, EVP_PKEY *private_key,
8464  X509_STORE *client_ca_cert_store) {
8465  ctx_ = SSL_CTX_new(TLS_server_method());
8466 
8467  if (ctx_) {
8468  SSL_CTX_set_options(ctx_,
8469  SSL_OP_NO_COMPRESSION |
8470  SSL_OP_NO_SESSION_RESUMPTION_ON_RENEGOTIATION);
8471 
8472  SSL_CTX_set_min_proto_version(ctx_, TLS1_1_VERSION);
8473 
8474  if (SSL_CTX_use_certificate(ctx_, cert) != 1 ||
8475  SSL_CTX_use_PrivateKey(ctx_, private_key) != 1) {
8476  SSL_CTX_free(ctx_);
8477  ctx_ = nullptr;
8478  } else if (client_ca_cert_store) {
8479  SSL_CTX_set_cert_store(ctx_, client_ca_cert_store);
8480 
8481  SSL_CTX_set_verify(
8482  ctx_, SSL_VERIFY_PEER | SSL_VERIFY_FAIL_IF_NO_PEER_CERT, nullptr);
8483  }
8484  }
8485 }
8486 
8487 inline SSLServer::SSLServer(
8488  const std::function<bool(SSL_CTX &ssl_ctx)> &setup_ssl_ctx_callback) {
8489  ctx_ = SSL_CTX_new(TLS_method());
8490  if (ctx_) {
8491  if (!setup_ssl_ctx_callback(*ctx_)) {
8492  SSL_CTX_free(ctx_);
8493  ctx_ = nullptr;
8494  }
8495  }
8496 }
8497 
8498 inline SSLServer::~SSLServer() {
8499  if (ctx_) { SSL_CTX_free(ctx_); }
8500 }
8501 
8502 inline bool SSLServer::is_valid() const { return ctx_; }
8503 
8504 inline SSL_CTX *SSLServer::ssl_context() const { return ctx_; }
8505 
8506 inline bool SSLServer::process_and_close_socket(socket_t sock) {
8507  auto ssl = detail::ssl_new(
8508  sock, ctx_, ctx_mutex_,
8509  [&](SSL *ssl2) {
8510  return detail::ssl_connect_or_accept_nonblocking(
8511  sock, ssl2, SSL_accept, read_timeout_sec_, read_timeout_usec_);
8512  },
8513  [](SSL * /*ssl2*/) { return true; });
8514 
8515  auto ret = false;
8516  if (ssl) {
8517  ret = detail::process_server_socket_ssl(
8518  svr_sock_, ssl, sock, keep_alive_max_count_, keep_alive_timeout_sec_,
8519  read_timeout_sec_, read_timeout_usec_, write_timeout_sec_,
8520  write_timeout_usec_,
8521  [this, ssl](Stream &strm, bool close_connection,
8522  bool &connection_closed) {
8523  return process_request(strm, close_connection, connection_closed,
8524  [&](Request &req) { req.ssl = ssl; });
8525  });
8526 
8527  // Shutdown gracefully if the result seemed successful, non-gracefully if
8528  // the connection appeared to be closed.
8529  const bool shutdown_gracefully = ret;
8530  detail::ssl_delete(ctx_mutex_, ssl, shutdown_gracefully);
8531  }
8532 
8533  detail::shutdown_socket(sock);
8534  detail::close_socket(sock);
8535  return ret;
8536 }

8539 inline SSLClient::SSLClient(const std::string &host)

8543  : SSLClient(host, port, std::string(), std::string()) {}

8545 inline SSLClient::SSLClient(const std::string &host, int port,
8546  const std::string &client_cert_path,
8547  const std::string &client_key_path)
8548  : ClientImpl(host, port, client_cert_path, client_key_path) {
8549  ctx_ = SSL_CTX_new(TLS_client_method());
8550 
8551  detail::split(&host_[0], &host_[host_.size()], '.',
8552  [&](const char *b, const char *e) {
8553  host_components_.emplace_back(b, e);
8554  });
8555 
8556  if (!client_cert_path.empty() && !client_key_path.empty()) {
8557  if (SSL_CTX_use_certificate_file(ctx_, client_cert_path.c_str(),
8558  SSL_FILETYPE_PEM) != 1 ||
8559  SSL_CTX_use_PrivateKey_file(ctx_, client_key_path.c_str(),
8560  SSL_FILETYPE_PEM) != 1) {
8561  SSL_CTX_free(ctx_);
8562  ctx_ = nullptr;
8563  }
8564  }
8565 }
8566 
8567 inline SSLClient::SSLClient(const std::string &host, int port,
8568  X509 *client_cert, EVP_PKEY *client_key)
8569  : ClientImpl(host, port) {
8570  ctx_ = SSL_CTX_new(TLS_client_method());
8571 
8572  detail::split(&host_[0], &host_[host_.size()], '.',
8573  [&](const char *b, const char *e) {
8574  host_components_.emplace_back(b, e);
8575  });
8576 
8577  if (client_cert != nullptr && client_key != nullptr) {
8578  if (SSL_CTX_use_certificate(ctx_, client_cert) != 1 ||
8579  SSL_CTX_use_PrivateKey(ctx_, client_key) != 1) {
8580  SSL_CTX_free(ctx_);
8581  ctx_ = nullptr;
8582  }
8583  }
8584 }
8585 
8586 inline SSLClient::~SSLClient() {
8587  if (ctx_) { SSL_CTX_free(ctx_); }
8588  // Make sure to shut down SSL since shutdown_ssl will resolve to the
8589  // base function rather than the derived function once we get to the
8590  // base class destructor, and won't free the SSL (causing a leak).
8591  shutdown_ssl_impl(socket_, true);
8592 }
8593 
8594 inline bool SSLClient::is_valid() const { return ctx_; }
8595 
8596 inline void SSLClient::set_ca_cert_store(X509_STORE *ca_cert_store) {
8597  if (ca_cert_store) {
8598  if (ctx_) {
8599  if (SSL_CTX_get_cert_store(ctx_) != ca_cert_store) {
8600  // Free memory allocated for old cert and use new store `ca_cert_store`
8601  SSL_CTX_set_cert_store(ctx_, ca_cert_store);
8602  }
8603  } else {
8604  X509_STORE_free(ca_cert_store);
8605  }
8606  }
8607 }

8624 // Assumes that socket_mutex_ is locked and that there are no requests in flight
8625 inline bool SSLClient::connect_with_proxy(Socket &socket, Response &res,
8626  bool &success, Error &error) {
8627  success = true;
8628  Response proxy_res;
8629  if (!detail::process_client_socket(
8630  socket.sock, read_timeout_sec_, read_timeout_usec_,
8631  write_timeout_sec_, write_timeout_usec_, [&](Stream &strm) {
8632  Request req2;
8633  req2.method = "CONNECT";
8634  req2.path = host_and_port_;
8635  return process_request(strm, req2, proxy_res, false, error);
8636  })) {
8637  // Thread-safe to close everything because we are assuming there are no
8638  // requests in flight
8639  shutdown_ssl(socket, true);
8640  shutdown_socket(socket);
8641  close_socket(socket);
8642  success = false;
8643  return false;
8644  }
8645 
8646  if (proxy_res.status == StatusCode::ProxyAuthenticationRequired_407) {
8647  if (!proxy_digest_auth_username_.empty() &&
8648  !proxy_digest_auth_password_.empty()) {
8649  std::map<std::string, std::string> auth;
8650  if (detail::parse_www_authenticate(proxy_res, auth, true)) {
8651  proxy_res = Response();
8652  if (!detail::process_client_socket(
8653  socket.sock, read_timeout_sec_, read_timeout_usec_,
8654  write_timeout_sec_, write_timeout_usec_, [&](Stream &strm) {
8655  Request req3;
8656  req3.method = "CONNECT";
8657  req3.path = host_and_port_;
8658  req3.headers.insert(detail::make_digest_authentication_header(
8659  req3, auth, 1, detail::random_string(10),
8660  proxy_digest_auth_username_, proxy_digest_auth_password_,
8661  true));
8662  return process_request(strm, req3, proxy_res, false, error);
8663  })) {
8664  // Thread-safe to close everything because we are assuming there are
8665  // no requests in flight
8666  shutdown_ssl(socket, true);
8667  shutdown_socket(socket);
8668  close_socket(socket);
8669  success = false;
8670  return false;
8671  }
8672  }
8673  }
8674  }
8675 
8676  // If status code is not 200, proxy request is failed.
8677  // Set error to ProxyConnection and return proxy response
8678  // as the response of the request
8679  if (proxy_res.status != StatusCode::OK_200) {
8680  error = Error::ProxyConnection;
8681  res = std::move(proxy_res);
8682  // Thread-safe to close everything because we are assuming there are
8683  // no requests in flight
8684  shutdown_ssl(socket, true);
8685  shutdown_socket(socket);
8686  close_socket(socket);
8687  return false;
8688  }
8689 
8690  return true;
8691 }
8692 
8693 inline bool SSLClient::load_certs() {
8694  auto ret = true;
8695 
8696  std::call_once(initialize_cert_, [&]() {
8697  std::lock_guard<std::mutex> guard(ctx_mutex_);
8698  if (!ca_cert_file_path_.empty()) {
8699  if (!SSL_CTX_load_verify_locations(ctx_, ca_cert_file_path_.c_str(),
8700  nullptr)) {
8701  ret = false;
8702  }
8703  } else if (!ca_cert_dir_path_.empty()) {
8704  if (!SSL_CTX_load_verify_locations(ctx_, nullptr,
8705  ca_cert_dir_path_.c_str())) {
8706  ret = false;
8707  }
8708  } else {
8709  auto loaded = false;
8710 #ifdef _WIN32
8711  loaded =
8712  detail::load_system_certs_on_windows(SSL_CTX_get_cert_store(ctx_));
8713 #elif defined(CPPHTTPLIB_USE_CERTS_FROM_MACOSX_KEYCHAIN) && defined(__APPLE__)
8714 #if TARGET_OS_OSX
8715  loaded = detail::load_system_certs_on_macos(SSL_CTX_get_cert_store(ctx_));
8716 #endif // TARGET_OS_OSX
8717 #endif // _WIN32
8718  if (!loaded) { SSL_CTX_set_default_verify_paths(ctx_); }
8719  }
8720  });
8721 
8722  return ret;
8723 }
8724 
8725 inline bool SSLClient::initialize_ssl(Socket &socket, Error &error) {
8726  auto ssl = detail::ssl_new(
8727  socket.sock, ctx_, ctx_mutex_,
8728  [&](SSL *ssl2) {
8729  if (server_certificate_verification_) {
8730  if (!load_certs()) {
8731  error = Error::SSLLoadingCerts;
8732  return false;
8733  }
8734  SSL_set_verify(ssl2, SSL_VERIFY_NONE, nullptr);
8735  }
8736 
8737  if (!detail::ssl_connect_or_accept_nonblocking(
8738  socket.sock, ssl2, SSL_connect, connection_timeout_sec_,
8739  connection_timeout_usec_)) {
8740  error = Error::SSLConnection;
8741  return false;
8742  }
8743 
8744  if (server_certificate_verification_) {
8745  verify_result_ = SSL_get_verify_result(ssl2);
8746 
8747  if (verify_result_ != X509_V_OK) {
8748  error = Error::SSLServerVerification;
8749  return false;
8750  }
8751 
8752  auto server_cert = SSL_get1_peer_certificate(ssl2);
8753 
8754  if (server_cert == nullptr) {
8755  error = Error::SSLServerVerification;
8756  return false;
8757  }
8758 
8759  if (!verify_host(server_cert)) {
8760  X509_free(server_cert);
8761  error = Error::SSLServerVerification;
8762  return false;
8763  }
8764  X509_free(server_cert);
8765  }
8766 
8767  return true;
8768  },
8769  [&](SSL *ssl2) {
8770  // NOTE: Direct call instead of using the OpenSSL macro to suppress
8771  // -Wold-style-cast warning
8772  // SSL_set_tlsext_host_name(ssl2, host_.c_str());
8773  SSL_ctrl(ssl2, SSL_CTRL_SET_TLSEXT_HOSTNAME, TLSEXT_NAMETYPE_host_name,
8774  static_cast<void *>(const_cast<char *>(host_.c_str())));
8775  return true;
8776  });
8777 
8778  if (ssl) {
8779  socket.ssl = ssl;
8780  return true;
8781  }
8782 
8783  shutdown_socket(socket);
8784  close_socket(socket);
8785  return false;
8786 }
8787 
8788 inline void SSLClient::shutdown_ssl(Socket &socket, bool shutdown_gracefully) {
8789  shutdown_ssl_impl(socket, shutdown_gracefully);
8790 }
8791 
8792 inline void SSLClient::shutdown_ssl_impl(Socket &socket,
8793  bool shutdown_gracefully) {
8794  if (socket.sock == INVALID_SOCKET) {
8795  assert(socket.ssl == nullptr);
8796  return;
8797  }
8798  if (socket.ssl) {
8799  detail::ssl_delete(ctx_mutex_, socket.ssl, shutdown_gracefully);
8800  socket.ssl = nullptr;
8801  }
8802  assert(socket.ssl == nullptr);
8803 }
8804 
8805 inline bool
8806 SSLClient::process_socket(const Socket &socket,
8807  std::function<bool(Stream &strm)> callback) {
8808  assert(socket.ssl);
8809  return detail::process_client_socket_ssl(
8810  socket.ssl, socket.sock, read_timeout_sec_, read_timeout_usec_,
8811  write_timeout_sec_, write_timeout_usec_, std::move(callback));
8812 }

8814 inline bool SSLClient::is_ssl() const { return true; }
8815 
8816 inline bool SSLClient::verify_host(X509 *server_cert) const {
8817  /* Quote from RFC2818 section 3.1 "Server Identity"
8818 
8819  If a subjectAltName extension of type dNSName is present, that MUST
8820  be used as the identity. Otherwise, the (most specific) Common Name
8821  field in the Subject field of the certificate MUST be used. Although
8822  the use of the Common Name is existing practice, it is deprecated and
8823  Certification Authorities are encouraged to use the dNSName instead.
8824 
8825  Matching is performed using the matching rules specified by
8826  [RFC2459]. If more than one identity of a given type is present in
8827  the certificate (e.g., more than one dNSName name, a match in any one
8828  of the set is considered acceptable.) Names may contain the wildcard
8829  character * which is considered to match any single domain name
8830  component or component fragment. E.g., *.a.com matches foo.a.com but
8831  not bar.foo.a.com. f*.com matches foo.com but not bar.com.
8832 
8833  In some cases, the URI is specified as an IP address rather than a
8834  hostname. In this case, the iPAddress subjectAltName must be present
8835  in the certificate and must exactly match the IP in the URI.
8836 
8837  */
8838  return verify_host_with_subject_alt_name(server_cert) ||
8839  verify_host_with_common_name(server_cert);
8840 }
8841 
8842 inline bool
8843 SSLClient::verify_host_with_subject_alt_name(X509 *server_cert) const {
8844  auto ret = false;
8845 
8846  auto type = GEN_DNS;
8847 
8848  struct in6_addr addr6 {};
8849  struct in_addr addr {};
8850  size_t addr_len = 0;
8851 
8852 #ifndef __MINGW32__
8853  if (inet_pton(AF_INET6, host_.c_str(), &addr6)) {
8854  type = GEN_IPADD;
8855  addr_len = sizeof(struct in6_addr);
8856  } else if (inet_pton(AF_INET, host_.c_str(), &addr)) {
8857  type = GEN_IPADD;
8858  addr_len = sizeof(struct in_addr);
8859  }
8860 #endif
8861 
8862  auto alt_names = static_cast<const struct stack_st_GENERAL_NAME *>(
8863  X509_get_ext_d2i(server_cert, NID_subject_alt_name, nullptr, nullptr));
8864 
8865  if (alt_names) {
8866  auto dsn_matched = false;
8867  auto ip_matched = false;
8868 
8869  auto count = sk_GENERAL_NAME_num(alt_names);
8870 
8871  for (decltype(count) i = 0; i < count && !dsn_matched; i++) {
8872  auto val = sk_GENERAL_NAME_value(alt_names, i);
8873  if (val->type == type) {
8874  auto name =
8875  reinterpret_cast<const char *>(ASN1_STRING_get0_data(val->d.ia5));
8876  auto name_len = static_cast<size_t>(ASN1_STRING_length(val->d.ia5));
8877 
8878  switch (type) {
8879  case GEN_DNS: dsn_matched = check_host_name(name, name_len); break;
8880 
8881  case GEN_IPADD:
8882  if (!memcmp(&addr6, name, addr_len) ||
8883  !memcmp(&addr, name, addr_len)) {
8884  ip_matched = true;
8885  }
8886  break;
8887  }
8888  }
8889  }
8890 
8891  if (dsn_matched || ip_matched) { ret = true; }
8892  }
8893 
8894  GENERAL_NAMES_free(const_cast<STACK_OF(GENERAL_NAME) *>(
8895  reinterpret_cast<const STACK_OF(GENERAL_NAME) *>(alt_names)));
8896  return ret;
8897 }
8898 
8899 inline bool SSLClient::verify_host_with_common_name(X509 *server_cert) const {
8900  const auto subject_name = X509_get_subject_name(server_cert);
8901 
8902  if (subject_name != nullptr) {
8903  char name[BUFSIZ];
8904  auto name_len = X509_NAME_get_text_by_NID(subject_name, NID_commonName,
8905  name, sizeof(name));
8906 
8907  if (name_len != -1) {
8908  return check_host_name(name, static_cast<size_t>(name_len));
8909  }
8910  }
8911 
8912  return false;
8913 }
8914 
8915 inline bool SSLClient::check_host_name(const char *pattern,
8916  size_t pattern_len) const {
8917  if (host_.size() == pattern_len && host_ == pattern) { return true; }
8918 
8919  // Wildcard match
8920  // https://bugs.launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/firefox-3.0/+bug/376484
8921  std::vector<std::string> pattern_components;
8922  detail::split(&pattern[0], &pattern[pattern_len], '.',
8923  [&](const char *b, const char *e) {
8924  pattern_components.emplace_back(b, e);
8925  });
8926 
8927  if (host_components_.size() != pattern_components.size()) { return false; }
8928 
8929  auto itr = pattern_components.begin();
8930  for (const auto &h : host_components_) {
8931  auto &p = *itr;
8932  if (p != h && p != "*") {
8933  auto partial_match = (p.size() > 0 && p[p.size() - 1] == '*' &&
8934  !p.compare(0, p.size() - 1, h));
8935  if (!partial_match) { return false; }
8936  }
8937  ++itr;
8938  }
8939 
8940  return true;
8941 }
8942 #endif
8943 
8944 // Universal client implementation
8945 inline Client::Client(const std::string &scheme_host_port)
8946  : Client(scheme_host_port, std::string(), std::string()) {}
8947 
8948 inline Client::Client(const std::string &scheme_host_port,
8949  const std::string &client_cert_path,
8950  const std::string &client_key_path) {
8951  const static std::regex re(
8952  R"((?:([a-z]+):\/\/)?(?:\[([\d:]+)\]|([^:/?#]+))(?::(\d+))?)");
8953 
8954  std::smatch m;
8955  if (std::regex_match(scheme_host_port, m, re)) {
8956  auto scheme = m[1].str();
8957 
8958 #ifdef CPPHTTPLIB_OPENSSL_SUPPORT
8959  if (!scheme.empty() && (scheme != "http" && scheme != "https")) {
8960 #else
8961  if (!scheme.empty() && scheme != "http") {
8962 #endif
8963 #ifndef CPPHTTPLIB_NO_EXCEPTIONS
8964  std::string msg = "'" + scheme + "' scheme is not supported.";
8965  throw std::invalid_argument(msg);
8966 #endif
8967  return;
8968  }
8969 
8970  auto is_ssl = scheme == "https";
8971 
8972  auto host = m[2].str();
8973  if (host.empty()) { host = m[3].str(); }
8974 
8975  auto port_str = m[4].str();
8976  auto port = !port_str.empty() ? std::stoi(port_str) : (is_ssl ? 443 : 80);
8977 
8978  if (is_ssl) {
8979 #ifdef CPPHTTPLIB_OPENSSL_SUPPORT
8980  cli_ = detail::make_unique<SSLClient>(host, port, client_cert_path,
8981  client_key_path);
8982  is_ssl_ = is_ssl;
8983 #endif
8984  } else {
8985  cli_ = detail::make_unique<ClientImpl>(host, port, client_cert_path,
8986  client_key_path);
8987  }
8988  } else {
8989  cli_ = detail::make_unique<ClientImpl>(scheme_host_port, 80,
8990  client_cert_path, client_key_path);
8991  }
8992 }
8993

8995  : cli_(detail::make_unique<ClientImpl>(host, port)) {}

8999  const std::string &client_key_path)
9000  : cli_(detail::make_unique<ClientImpl>(host, port, client_cert_path,
9001  client_key_path)) {}
